72namespace nlohmann
73{
74 namespace detail
75 {
77 struct position_t
78 {
80 std::size_t chars_read_total = 0;
82 std::size_t chars_read_current_line = 0;
84 std::size_t lines_read = 0;
85
87 constexpr operator size_t() const
88 {
89 return chars_read_total;
90 }
91 };

149#if defined(JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_ENCODE)
150#undef JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_ENCODE
151#endif
152#define JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_ENCODE(major,minor,revision) (((major) * 1000000) + ((minor) * 1000) + (revision))
153
154#if defined(JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_DECODE_MAJOR)
155#undef JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_DECODE_MAJOR
156#endif
157#define JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_DECODE_MAJOR(version) ((version) / 1000000)
158
159#if defined(JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_DECODE_MINOR)
160#undef JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_DECODE_MINOR
161#endif
162#define JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_DECODE_MINOR(version) (((version) % 1000000) / 1000)
163
164#if defined(JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_DECODE_REVISION)
165#undef JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_DECODE_REVISION
166#endif
167#define JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_DECODE_REVISION(version) ((version) % 1000)
168
169#if defined(JSON_HEDLEY_GNUC_VERSION)
170#undef JSON_HEDLEY_GNUC_VERSION
171#endif
172#if defined(__GNUC__) && defined(__GNUC_PATCHLEVEL__)
173#define JSON_HEDLEY_GNUC_VERSION JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_ENCODE(__GNUC__, __GNUC_MINOR__, __GNUC_PATCHLEVEL__)
174#elif defined(__GNUC__)
175#define JSON_HEDLEY_GNUC_VERSION JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_ENCODE(__GNUC__, __GNUC_MINOR__, 0)
176#endif
177
178#if defined(JSON_HEDLEY_GNUC_VERSION_CHECK)
179#undef JSON_HEDLEY_GNUC_VERSION_CHECK
180#endif
181#if defined(JSON_HEDLEY_GNUC_VERSION)
182#define JSON_HEDLEY_GNUC_VERSION_CHECK(major,minor,patch) (JSON_HEDLEY_GNUC_VERSION >= JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_ENCODE(major, minor, patch))
183#else
184#define JSON_HEDLEY_GNUC_VERSION_CHECK(major,minor,patch) (0)
185#endif

187#if defined(JSON_HEDLEY_MSVC_VERSION)
188#undef JSON_HEDLEY_MSVC_VERSION
189#endif
190#if defined(_MSC_FULL_VER) && (_MSC_FULL_VER >= 140000000)
191#define JSON_HEDLEY_MSVC_VERSION JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_ENCODE(_MSC_FULL_VER / 10000000, (_MSC_FULL_VER % 10000000) / 100000, (_MSC_FULL_VER % 100000) / 100)
192#elif defined(_MSC_FULL_VER)
193#define JSON_HEDLEY_MSVC_VERSION JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_ENCODE(_MSC_FULL_VER / 1000000, (_MSC_FULL_VER % 1000000) / 10000, (_MSC_FULL_VER % 10000) / 10)
194#elif defined(_MSC_VER)
195#define JSON_HEDLEY_MSVC_VERSION JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_ENCODE(_MSC_VER / 100, _MSC_VER % 100, 0)
196#endif
197
198#if defined(JSON_HEDLEY_MSVC_VERSION_CHECK)
199#undef JSON_HEDLEY_MSVC_VERSION_CHECK
200#endif
201#if !defined(_MSC_VER)
202#define JSON_HEDLEY_MSVC_VERSION_CHECK(major,minor,patch) (0)
203#elif defined(_MSC_VER) && (_MSC_VER >= 1400)
204#define JSON_HEDLEY_MSVC_VERSION_CHECK(major,minor,patch) (_MSC_FULL_VER >= ((major * 10000000) + (minor * 100000) + (patch)))
205#elif defined(_MSC_VER) && (_MSC_VER >= 1200)
206#define JSON_HEDLEY_MSVC_VERSION_CHECK(major,minor,patch) (_MSC_FULL_VER >= ((major * 1000000) + (minor * 10000) + (patch)))
207#else
208#define JSON_HEDLEY_MSVC_VERSION_CHECK(major,minor,patch) (_MSC_VER >= ((major * 100) + (minor)))
209#endif

1349#if \
1350 JSON_HEDLEY_HAS_BUILTIN(__builtin_expect_with_probability) || \
1351 JSON_HEDLEY_GCC_VERSION_CHECK(9,0,0)
1352# define JSON_HEDLEY_PREDICT(expr, value, probability) __builtin_expect_with_probability( (expr), (value), (probability))
1353# define JSON_HEDLEY_PREDICT_TRUE(expr, probability) __builtin_expect_with_probability(!!(expr), 1 , (probability))
1354# define JSON_HEDLEY_PREDICT_FALSE(expr, probability) __builtin_expect_with_probability(!!(expr), 0 , (probability))
1355# define JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(expr) __builtin_expect (!!(expr), 1 )
1356# define JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(expr) __builtin_expect (!!(expr), 0 )
1357#elif \
1358 JSON_HEDLEY_HAS_BUILTIN(__builtin_expect) || \
1359 JSON_HEDLEY_GCC_VERSION_CHECK(3,0,0) || \
1360 JSON_HEDLEY_INTEL_VERSION_CHECK(13,0,0) || \
1361 (JSON_HEDLEY_SUNPRO_VERSION_CHECK(5,15,0) && defined(__cplusplus)) || \
1362 JSON_HEDLEY_ARM_VERSION_CHECK(4,1,0) || \
1363 JSON_HEDLEY_IBM_VERSION_CHECK(10,1,0) || \
1364 JSON_HEDLEY_TI_VERSION_CHECK(15,12,0) || \
1365 JSON_HEDLEY_TI_ARMCL_VERSION_CHECK(4,7,0) || \
1366 JSON_HEDLEY_TI_CL430_VERSION_CHECK(3,1,0) || \
1367 JSON_HEDLEY_TI_CL2000_VERSION_CHECK(6,1,0) || \
1368 JSON_HEDLEY_TI_CL6X_VERSION_CHECK(6,1,0) || \
1369 JSON_HEDLEY_TI_CL7X_VERSION_CHECK(1,2,0) || \
1370 JSON_HEDLEY_TI_CLPRU_VERSION_CHECK(2,1,0) || \
1371 JSON_HEDLEY_TINYC_VERSION_CHECK(0,9,27) || \
1372 JSON_HEDLEY_CRAY_VERSION_CHECK(8,1,0)
1373# define JSON_HEDLEY_PREDICT(expr, expected, probability) \
1374 (((probability) >= 0.9) ? __builtin_expect((expr), (expected)) : (JSON_HEDLEY_STATIC_CAST(void, expected), (expr)))
1375# define JSON_HEDLEY_PREDICT_TRUE(expr, probability) \
1376 (__extension__ ({ \
1377 double hedley_probability_ = (probability); \
1378 ((hedley_probability_ >= 0.9) ? __builtin_expect(!!(expr), 1) : ((hedley_probability_ <= 0.1) ? __builtin_expect(!!(expr), 0) : !!(expr))); \
1379 }))
1380# define JSON_HEDLEY_PREDICT_FALSE(expr, probability) \
1381 (__extension__ ({ \
1382 double hedley_probability_ = (probability); \
1383 ((hedley_probability_ >= 0.9) ? __builtin_expect(!!(expr), 0) : ((hedley_probability_ <= 0.1) ? __builtin_expect(!!(expr), 1) : !!(expr))); \
1384 }))
1385# define JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(expr) __builtin_expect(!!(expr), 1)
1386# define JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(expr) __builtin_expect(!!(expr), 0)
1387#else
1388# define JSON_HEDLEY_PREDICT(expr, expected, probability) (JSON_HEDLEY_STATIC_CAST(void, expected), (expr))
1389# define JSON_HEDLEY_PREDICT_TRUE(expr, probability) (!!(expr))
1390# define JSON_HEDLEY_PREDICT_FALSE(expr, probability) (!!(expr))
1391# define JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(expr) (!!(expr))
1392# define JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(expr) (!!(expr))
1393#endif
1394#if !defined(JSON_HEDLEY_UNPREDICTABLE)
1395#define JSON_HEDLEY_UNPREDICTABLE(expr) JSON_HEDLEY_PREDICT(expr, 1, 0.5)
1396#endif

1731#if \
1732 JSON_HEDLEY_HAS_BUILTIN(__builtin_constant_p) || \
1733 JSON_HEDLEY_GCC_VERSION_CHECK(3,4,0) || \
1734 JSON_HEDLEY_INTEL_VERSION_CHECK(13,0,0) || \
1735 JSON_HEDLEY_TINYC_VERSION_CHECK(0,9,19) || \
1736 JSON_HEDLEY_ARM_VERSION_CHECK(4,1,0) || \
1737 JSON_HEDLEY_IBM_VERSION_CHECK(13,1,0) || \
1738 JSON_HEDLEY_TI_CL6X_VERSION_CHECK(6,1,0) || \
1739 (JSON_HEDLEY_SUNPRO_VERSION_CHECK(5,10,0) && !defined(__cplusplus)) || \
1740 JSON_HEDLEY_CRAY_VERSION_CHECK(8,1,0)
1741#define JSON_HEDLEY_IS_CONSTANT(expr) __builtin_constant_p(expr)
1742#endif
1743#if !defined(__cplusplus)
1744# if \
1745 JSON_HEDLEY_HAS_BUILTIN(__builtin_types_compatible_p) || \
1746 JSON_HEDLEY_GCC_VERSION_CHECK(3,4,0) || \
1747 JSON_HEDLEY_INTEL_VERSION_CHECK(13,0,0) || \
1748 JSON_HEDLEY_IBM_VERSION_CHECK(13,1,0) || \
1749 JSON_HEDLEY_CRAY_VERSION_CHECK(8,1,0) || \
1750 JSON_HEDLEY_ARM_VERSION_CHECK(5,4,0) || \
1751 JSON_HEDLEY_TINYC_VERSION_CHECK(0,9,24)
1752#if defined(__INTPTR_TYPE__)
1753#define JSON_HEDLEY_IS_CONSTEXPR_(expr) __builtin_types_compatible_p(__typeof__((1 ? (void*) ((__INTPTR_TYPE__) ((expr) * 0)) : (int*) 0)), int*)
1754#else
1755#include <stdint.h>
1756#define JSON_HEDLEY_IS_CONSTEXPR_(expr) __builtin_types_compatible_p(__typeof__((1 ? (void*) ((intptr_t) ((expr) * 0)) : (int*) 0)), int*)
1757#endif
1758# elif \
1759 ( \
1760 defined(__STDC_VERSION__) && (__STDC_VERSION__ >= 201112L) && \
1761 !defined(JSON_HEDLEY_SUNPRO_VERSION) && \
1762 !defined(JSON_HEDLEY_PGI_VERSION) && \
1763 !defined(JSON_HEDLEY_IAR_VERSION)) || \
1764 JSON_HEDLEY_HAS_EXTENSION(c_generic_selections) || \
1765 JSON_HEDLEY_GCC_VERSION_CHECK(4,9,0) || \
1766 JSON_HEDLEY_INTEL_VERSION_CHECK(17,0,0) || \
1767 JSON_HEDLEY_IBM_VERSION_CHECK(12,1,0) || \
1768 JSON_HEDLEY_ARM_VERSION_CHECK(5,3,0)
1769#if defined(__INTPTR_TYPE__)
1770#define JSON_HEDLEY_IS_CONSTEXPR_(expr) _Generic((1 ? (void*) ((__INTPTR_TYPE__) ((expr) * 0)) : (int*) 0), int*: 1, void*: 0)
1771#else
1772#include <stdint.h>
1773#define JSON_HEDLEY_IS_CONSTEXPR_(expr) _Generic((1 ? (void*) ((intptr_t) * 0) : (int*) 0), int*: 1, void*: 0)
1774#endif
1775# elif \
1776 defined(JSON_HEDLEY_GCC_VERSION) || \
1777 defined(JSON_HEDLEY_INTEL_VERSION) || \
1778 defined(JSON_HEDLEY_TINYC_VERSION) || \
1779 defined(JSON_HEDLEY_TI_ARMCL_VERSION) || \
1780 JSON_HEDLEY_TI_CL430_VERSION_CHECK(18,12,0) || \
1781 defined(JSON_HEDLEY_TI_CL2000_VERSION) || \
1782 defined(JSON_HEDLEY_TI_CL6X_VERSION) || \
1783 defined(JSON_HEDLEY_TI_CL7X_VERSION) || \
1784 defined(JSON_HEDLEY_TI_CLPRU_VERSION) || \
1785 defined(__clang__)
1786# define JSON_HEDLEY_IS_CONSTEXPR_(expr) ( \
1787 sizeof(void) != \
1788 sizeof(*( \
1789 1 ? \
1790 ((void*) ((expr) * 0L) ) : \
1791 ((struct { char v[sizeof(void) * 2]; } *) 1) \
1792 ) \
1793 ) \
1794 )
1795# endif
1796#endif
1797#if defined(JSON_HEDLEY_IS_CONSTEXPR_)
1798#if !defined(JSON_HEDLEY_IS_CONSTANT)
1799#define JSON_HEDLEY_IS_CONSTANT(expr) JSON_HEDLEY_IS_CONSTEXPR_(expr)
1800#endif
1801#define JSON_HEDLEY_REQUIRE_CONSTEXPR(expr) (JSON_HEDLEY_IS_CONSTEXPR_(expr) ? (expr) : (-1))
1802#else
1803#if !defined(JSON_HEDLEY_IS_CONSTANT)

1805#endif
1806#define JSON_HEDLEY_REQUIRE_CONSTEXPR(expr) (expr)

2099#define NLOHMANN_JSON_SERIALIZE_ENUM(ENUM_TYPE, ...) \
2100 template<typename BasicJsonType> \
2101 inline void to_json(BasicJsonType& j, const ENUM_TYPE& e) \
2102{ \
2103 static_assert(std::is_enum<ENUM_TYPE>::value, #ENUM_TYPE " must be an enum!"); \
2104 static const std::pair<ENUM_TYPE, BasicJsonType> m[] = __VA_ARGS__; \
2105 auto it = std::find_if(std::begin(m), std::end(m), \
2106 [e](const std::pair<ENUM_TYPE, BasicJsonType>& ej_pair) -> bool \
2107{ \
2108 return ej_pair.first == e; \
2109 }); \
2110 j = ((it != std::end(m)) ? it : std::begin(m))->second; \
2111 } \
2112 template<typename BasicJsonType> \
2113 inline void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, ENUM_TYPE& e) \
2114{ \
2115 static_assert(std::is_enum<ENUM_TYPE>::value, #ENUM_TYPE " must be an enum!"); \
2116 static const std::pair<ENUM_TYPE, BasicJsonType> m[] = __VA_ARGS__; \
2117 auto it = std::find_if(std::begin(m), std::end(m), \
2118 [&j](const std::pair<ENUM_TYPE, BasicJsonType>& ej_pair) -> bool \
2119{ \
2120 return ej_pair.second == j; \
2121 }); \
2122 e = ((it != std::end(m)) ? it : std::begin(m))->first; \
2123 }

2129 template<template<typename, typename, typename...> class ObjectType, \
2130 template<typename, typename...> class ArrayType, \
2131 class StringType, class BooleanType, class NumberIntegerType, \
2132 class NumberUnsignedType, class NumberFloatType, \
2133 template<typename> class AllocatorType, \
2134 template<typename, typename = void> class JSONSerializer, \
2135 class BinaryType>
2136
2137#define NLOHMANN_BASIC_JSON_TPL \
2138 basic_json<ObjectType, ArrayType, StringType, BooleanType, \
2139 NumberIntegerType, NumberUnsignedType, NumberFloatType, \
2140 AllocatorType, JSONSerializer, BinaryType>

2343 class exception : public std::exception
2344 {
2345 public:
2347 JSON_HEDLEY_RETURNS_NON_NULL
2348 const char* what() const noexcept override
2349 {
2350 return m.what();
2351 }
2352
2354 const int id;
2355
2356 protected:
2357 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(3)
2358 exception(int id_, const char* what_arg) : id(id_), m(what_arg) {}
2359
2360 static std::string name(const std::string& ename, int id_)
2361 {
2362 return "[json.exception." + ename + "." + std::to_string(id_) + "] ";
2363 }
2364
2365 private:
2367 std::runtime_error m;
2368 };
2369
2415 class parse_error : public exception
2416 {
2417 public:
2427 static parse_error create(int id_, const position_t& pos, const std::string& what_arg)
2428 {
2429 std::string w = exception::name("parse_error", id_) + "parse error" +
2430 position_string(pos) + ": " + what_arg;
2431 return parse_error(id_, pos.chars_read_total, w.c_str());
2432 }
2433
2434 static parse_error create(int id_, std::size_t byte_, const std::string& what_arg)
2435 {
2436 std::string w = exception::name("parse_error", id_) + "parse error" +
2437 (byte_ != 0 ? (" at byte " + std::to_string(byte_)) : "") +
2438 ": " + what_arg;
2439 return parse_error(id_, byte_, w.c_str());
2440 }
2441
2451 const std::size_t byte;
2452
2453 private:
2454 parse_error(int id_, std::size_t byte_, const char* what_arg)
2455 : exception(id_, what_arg), byte(byte_) {}
2456
2457 static std::string position_string(const position_t& pos)
2458 {
2459 return " at line " + std::to_string(pos.lines_read + 1) +
2460 ", column " + std::to_string(pos.chars_read_current_line);
2461 }
2462 };

2675 // implementation of C++14 index_sequence and affiliates
2676 // source: https://stackoverflow.com/a/32223343
2677 template<std::size_t... Ints>
2678 struct index_sequence
2679 {
2680 using type = index_sequence;
2681 using value_type = std::size_t;
2682 static constexpr std::size_t size() noexcept
2683 {
2684 return sizeof...(Ints);
2685 }
2686 };
2687
2688 template<class Sequence1, class Sequence2>
2689 struct merge_and_renumber;
2690
2691 template<std::size_t... I1, std::size_t... I2>
2692 struct merge_and_renumber<index_sequence<I1...>, index_sequence<I2...>>
2693 : index_sequence < I1..., (sizeof...(I1) + I2)... > {};
2694
2695 template<std::size_t N>
2696 struct make_index_sequence
2697 : merge_and_renumber < typename make_index_sequence < N / 2 >::type,
2698 typename make_index_sequence < N - N / 2 >::type > {};
2699
2700 template<> struct make_index_sequence<0> : index_sequence<> {};
2701 template<> struct make_index_sequence<1> : index_sequence<0> {};
2702
2703 template<typename... Ts>
2704 using index_sequence_for = make_index_sequence<sizeof...(Ts)>;
2705
2706 // dispatch utility (taken from ranges-v3)
2707 template<unsigned N> struct priority_tag : priority_tag < N - 1 > {};
2708 template<> struct priority_tag<0> {};
2709
2710 // taken from ranges-v3
2711 template<typename T>
2712 struct static_const
2713 {
2714 static constexpr T value{};
2715 };
2716
2717 template<typename T>
2718 constexpr T static_const<T>::value;
2719 } // namespace detail

2761 It,

2763 typename It::reference, typename It::iterator_category >>
2764 {
2765 using difference_type = typename It::difference_type;
2766 using value_type = typename It::value_type;
2767 using pointer = typename It::pointer;
2768 using reference = typename It::reference;
2769 using iterator_category = typename It::iterator_category;

2772 // This is required as some compilers implement std::iterator_traits in a way that
2773 // doesn't work with SFINAE. See https://github.com/nlohmann/json/issues/1341.
2774 template<typename T, typename = void>
2775 struct iterator_traits
2776 {
2777 };
2778
2779 template<typename T>
2780 struct iterator_traits < T, enable_if_t < !std::is_pointer<T>::value >>
2781 : iterator_types<T>
2782 {
2783 };
2784
2785 template<typename T>
2786 struct iterator_traits<T*, enable_if_t<std::is_object<T>::value>>
2787 {
2788 using iterator_category = std::random_access_iterator_tag;
2789 using value_type = T;
2790 using difference_type = ptrdiff_t;
2791 using pointer = T*;
2792 using reference = T&;
2793 };

2814 struct nonesuch
2815 {
2816 nonesuch() = delete;
2817 ~nonesuch() = delete;
2818 nonesuch(nonesuch const&) = delete;
2819 nonesuch(nonesuch const&&) = delete;
2820 void operator=(nonesuch const&) = delete;
2821 void operator=(nonesuch&&) = delete;
2822 };
2823
2824 template<class Default,
2825 class AlwaysVoid,
2826 template<class...> class Op,
2827 class... Args>
2828 struct detector
2829 {
2830 using value_t = std::false_type;
2831 using type = Default;
2832 };
2833
2834 template<class Default, template<class...> class Op, class... Args>
2835 struct detector<Default, void_t<Op<Args...>>, Op, Args...>
2836 {
2837 using value_t = std::true_type;
2838 using type = Op<Args...>;
2839 };
2840
2841 template<template<class...> class Op, class... Args>
2842 using is_detected = typename detector<nonesuch, void, Op, Args...>::value_t;
2843
2844 template<template<class...> class Op, class... Args>
2845 using detected_t = typename detector<nonesuch, void, Op, Args...>::type;
2846
2847 template<class Default, template<class...> class Op, class... Args>
2848 using detected_or = detector<Default, void, Op, Args...>;
2849
2850 template<class Default, template<class...> class Op, class... Args>
2851 using detected_or_t = typename detected_or<Default, Op, Args...>::type;
2852
2853 template<class Expected, template<class...> class Op, class... Args>
2854 using is_detected_exact = std::is_same<Expected, detected_t<Op, Args...>>;
2855
2856 template<class To, template<class...> class Op, class... Args>
2857 using is_detected_convertible =
2858 std::is_convertible<detected_t<Op, Args...>, To>;
2859 } // namespace detail
2860} // namespace nlohmann

2959 // Note to maintainers:
2960 //
2961 // Every trait in this file expects a non CV-qualified type.
2962 // The only exceptions are in the 'aliases for detected' section
2963 // (i.e. those of the form: decltype(T::member_function(std::declval<T>())))
2964 //
2965 // In this case, T has to be properly CV-qualified to constraint the function arguments
2966 // (e.g. to_json(BasicJsonType&, const T&))
2967

2969
2970 NLOHMANN_BASIC_JSON_TPL_DECLARATION
2971 struct is_basic_json<NLOHMANN_BASIC_JSON_TPL> : std::true_type {};

3023 // trait checking if JSONSerializer<T>::from_json(json const&, udt&) exists
3024 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T, typename = void>
3025 struct has_from_json : std::false_type {};
3026
3027 // trait checking if j.get<T> is valid
3028 // use this trait instead of std::is_constructible or std::is_convertible,
3029 // both rely on, or make use of implicit conversions, and thus fail when T
3030 // has several constructors/operator= (see https://github.com/nlohmann/json/issues/958)
3031 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
3032 struct is_getable
3033 {
3034 static constexpr bool value = is_detected<get_template_function, const BasicJsonType&, T>::value;
3035 };

3037 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
3038 struct has_from_json < BasicJsonType, T,
3039 enable_if_t < !is_basic_json<T>::value >>
3040 {
3041 using serializer = typename BasicJsonType::template json_serializer<T, void>;
3042
3043 static constexpr bool value =
3044 is_detected_exact<void, from_json_function, serializer,
3045 const BasicJsonType&, T&>::value;
3046 };

3058 static constexpr bool value =
3059 is_detected_exact<T, from_json_function, serializer,
3060 const BasicJsonType&>::value;
3061 };

3109 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleObjectType,

3115 BasicJsonType, CompatibleObjectType,

3122 // macOS's is_constructible does not play well with nonesuch...
3123 static constexpr bool value =
3124 std::is_constructible<typename object_t::key_type,
3125 typename CompatibleObjectType::key_type>::value &&
3126 std::is_constructible<typename object_t::mapped_type,
3127 typename CompatibleObjectType::mapped_type>::value;
3128 };
3129
3130 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleObjectType>
3131 struct is_compatible_object_type
3132 : is_compatible_object_type_impl<BasicJsonType, CompatibleObjectType> {};

3141 enable_if_t < is_detected<mapped_type_t, ConstructibleObjectType>::value&&
3142 is_detected<key_type_t, ConstructibleObjectType>::value >>
3143 {
3144 using object_t = typename BasicJsonType::object_t;
3145
3146 static constexpr bool value =
3147 (std::is_default_constructible<ConstructibleObjectType>::value &&
3148 (std::is_move_assignable<ConstructibleObjectType>::value ||
3149 std::is_copy_assignable<ConstructibleObjectType>::value) &&
3150 (std::is_constructible<typename ConstructibleObjectType::key_type,
3151 typename object_t::key_type>::value &&
3152 std::is_same <
3153 typename object_t::mapped_type,
3154 typename ConstructibleObjectType::mapped_type >::value)) ||
3155 (has_from_json<BasicJsonType,
3156 typename ConstructibleObjectType::mapped_type>::value ||
3157 has_non_default_from_json <
3158 BasicJsonType,
3159 typename ConstructibleObjectType::mapped_type >::value);
3160 };

3207 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType>
3208 struct is_compatible_array_type_impl <
3209 BasicJsonType, CompatibleArrayType,
3210 enable_if_t < is_detected<value_type_t, CompatibleArrayType>::value&&
3211 is_detected<iterator_t, CompatibleArrayType>::value&&
3212 // This is needed because json_reverse_iterator has a ::iterator type...
3213 // Therefore it is detected as a CompatibleArrayType.
3214 // The real fix would be to have an Iterable concept.
3215 !is_iterator_traits <
3216 iterator_traits<CompatibleArrayType >>::value >>

3230 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleArrayType>
3231 struct is_constructible_array_type_impl <
3232 BasicJsonType, ConstructibleArrayType,
3233 enable_if_t<std::is_same<ConstructibleArrayType,
3234 typename BasicJsonType::value_type>::value >>
3235 : std::true_type {};

3237 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleArrayType>
3238 struct is_constructible_array_type_impl <
3239 BasicJsonType, ConstructibleArrayType,
3240 enable_if_t < !std::is_same<ConstructibleArrayType,
3241 typename BasicJsonType::value_type>::value&&
3242 std::is_default_constructible<ConstructibleArrayType>::value&&
3243 (std::is_move_assignable<ConstructibleArrayType>::value ||
3244 std::is_copy_assignable<ConstructibleArrayType>::value)&&
3245 is_detected<value_type_t, ConstructibleArrayType>::value&&
3246 is_detected<iterator_t, ConstructibleArrayType>::value&&
3247 is_complete_type <
3248 detected_t<value_type_t, ConstructibleArrayType >>::value >>
3249 {
3250 static constexpr bool value =
3251 // This is needed because json_reverse_iterator has a ::iterator type,
3252 // furthermore, std::back_insert_iterator (and other iterators) have a
3253 // base class `iterator`... Therefore it is detected as a
3254 // ConstructibleArrayType. The real fix would be to have an Iterable
3255 // concept.
3256 !is_iterator_traits<iterator_traits<ConstructibleArrayType>>::value &&
3257
3258 (std::is_same<typename ConstructibleArrayType::value_type,
3259 typename BasicJsonType::array_t::value_type>::value ||
3260 has_from_json<BasicJsonType,
3261 typename ConstructibleArrayType::value_type>::value ||
3262 has_non_default_from_json <
3263 BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleArrayType::value_type >::value);
3264 };

3268 : is_constructible_array_type_impl<BasicJsonType, ConstructibleArrayType> {};

3274 template<typename RealIntegerType, typename CompatibleNumberIntegerType>
3275 struct is_compatible_integer_type_impl <
3276 RealIntegerType, CompatibleNumberIntegerType,
3277 enable_if_t < std::is_integral<RealIntegerType>::value&&
3278 std::is_integral<CompatibleNumberIntegerType>::value&&
3279 !std::is_same<bool, CompatibleNumberIntegerType>::value >>
3280 {
3281 // is there an assert somewhere on overflows?
3282 using RealLimits = std::numeric_limits<RealIntegerType>;
3283 using CompatibleLimits = std::numeric_limits<CompatibleNumberIntegerType>;
3284
3285 static constexpr auto value =
3286 std::is_constructible<RealIntegerType,
3287 CompatibleNumberIntegerType>::value &&
3288 CompatibleLimits::is_integer &&
3289 RealLimits::is_signed == CompatibleLimits::is_signed;
3290 };

3302 BasicJsonType, CompatibleType,

3306 has_to_json<BasicJsonType, CompatibleType>::value;

3313 // https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/types/conjunction
3314 template<class...> struct conjunction : std::true_type { };
3315 template<class B1> struct conjunction<B1> : B1 { };
3316 template<class B1, class... Bn>
3317 struct conjunction<B1, Bn...>
3318 : std::conditional<bool(B1::value), conjunction<Bn...>, B1>::type {};
3319
3320 template<typename T1, typename T2>
3321 struct is_constructible_tuple : std::false_type {};
3322
3323 template<typename T1, typename... Args>
3324 struct is_constructible_tuple<T1, std::tuple<Args...>> : conjunction<std::is_constructible<T1, Args>...> {};

3341 // JSON type enumeration //
3343
3368 enum class value_t : std::uint8_t
3369 {
3370 null,
3371 object,
3372 array,
3373 string,
3374 boolean,
3375 number_integer,
3376 number_unsigned,
3377 number_float,
3378 binary,
3379 discarded
3380 };
3381
3395 inline bool operator<(const value_t lhs, const value_t rhs) noexcept
3396 {
3397 static constexpr std::array<std::uint8_t, 9> order = {{
3398 0 /* null */, 3 /* object */, 4 /* array */, 5 /* string */,
3399 1 /* boolean */, 2 /* integer */, 2 /* unsigned */, 2 /* float */,
3400 6 /* binary */
3401 }
3402 };
3403
3404 const auto l_index = static_cast<std::size_t>(lhs);
3405 const auto r_index = static_cast<std::size_t>(rhs);
3406 return l_index < order.size() && r_index < order.size() && order[l_index] < order[r_index];
3407 }
3408 } // namespace detail
3409} // namespace nlohmann

3416 template<typename BasicJsonType>
3417 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, typename std::nullptr_t& n)
3418 {
3419 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!j.is_null()))
3420 {
3421 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be null, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
3422 }
3423 n = nullptr;
3424 }

3426 // overloads for basic_json template parameters
3427 template < typename BasicJsonType, typename ArithmeticType,
3428 enable_if_t < std::is_arithmetic<ArithmeticType>::value&&
3429 !std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t>::value,
3430 int > = 0 >
3431 void get_arithmetic_value(const BasicJsonType& j, ArithmeticType& val)
3432 {
3433 switch (static_cast<value_t>(j))
3434 {
3435 case value_t::number_unsigned:
3436 {
3437 val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t*>());
3438 break;
3439 }
3440 case value_t::number_integer:
3441 {
3442 val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t*>());
3443 break;
3444 }
3445 case value_t::number_float:
3446 {
3447 val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t*>());
3448 break;
3449 }
3450
3451 default:
3452 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be number, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
3453 }
3454 }

3520 // forward_list doesn't have an insert method
3521 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T, typename Allocator,
3522 enable_if_t<is_getable<BasicJsonType, T>::value, int> = 0>
3523 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::forward_list<T, Allocator>& l)
3524 {
3525 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!j.is_array()))
3526 {
3527 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
3528 }
3529 l.clear();
3530 std::transform(j.rbegin(), j.rend(),
3531 std::front_inserter(l), [](const BasicJsonType & i)
3532 {
3533 return i.template get<T>();
3534 });
3535 }
3536
3537 // valarray doesn't have an insert method
3538 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T,
3539 enable_if_t<is_getable<BasicJsonType, T>::value, int> = 0>
3540 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::valarray<T>& l)
3541 {
3542 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!j.is_array()))
3543 {
3544 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
3545 }
3546 l.resize(j.size());
3547 std::transform(j.begin(), j.end(), std::begin(l),
3548 [](const BasicJsonType & elem)
3549 {
3550 return elem.template get<T>();
3551 });
3552 }

3554 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T, std::size_t N>
3555 auto from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, T (&arr)[N])
3556 -> decltype(j.template get<T>(), void())
3557 {
3558 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < N; ++i)
3559 {
3560 arr[i] = j.at(i).template get<T>();
3561 }
3562 }

3581 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleArrayType>
3582 auto from_json_array_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, ConstructibleArrayType& arr, priority_tag<1> /*unused*/)
3583 -> decltype(
3584 arr.reserve(std::declval<typename ConstructibleArrayType::size_type>()),
3585 j.template get<typename ConstructibleArrayType::value_type>(),
3586 void())
3587 {
3588 using std::end;
3589
3590 ConstructibleArrayType ret;
3591 ret.reserve(j.size());
3592 std::transform(j.begin(), j.end(),
3593 std::inserter(ret, end(ret)), [](const BasicJsonType & i)
3594 {
3595 // get<BasicJsonType>() returns *this, this won't call a from_json
3596 // method when value_type is BasicJsonType
3597 return i.template get<typename ConstructibleArrayType::value_type>();
3598 });
3599 arr = std::move(ret);
3600 }
3601
3602 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleArrayType>
3603 void from_json_array_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, ConstructibleArrayType& arr,
3604 priority_tag<0> /*unused*/)
3605 {
3606 using std::end;
3607
3608 ConstructibleArrayType ret;
3609 std::transform(
3610 j.begin(), j.end(), std::inserter(ret, end(ret)),
3611 [](const BasicJsonType & i)
3612 {
3613 // get<BasicJsonType>() returns *this, this won't call a from_json
3614 // method when value_type is BasicJsonType
3615 return i.template get<typename ConstructibleArrayType::value_type>();
3616 });
3617 arr = std::move(ret);
3618 }

3620 template < typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleArrayType,
3621 enable_if_t <
3622 is_constructible_array_type<BasicJsonType, ConstructibleArrayType>::value&&
3623 !is_constructible_object_type<BasicJsonType, ConstructibleArrayType>::value&&
3624 !is_constructible_string_type<BasicJsonType, ConstructibleArrayType>::value&&
3625 !std::is_same<ConstructibleArrayType, typename BasicJsonType::binary_t>::value&&
3626 !is_basic_json<ConstructibleArrayType>::value,
3627 int > = 0 >
3628 auto from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, ConstructibleArrayType& arr)
3629 -> decltype(from_json_array_impl(j, arr, priority_tag<3> {}),
3630 j.template get<typename ConstructibleArrayType::value_type>(),
3631 void())
3632 {
3633 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!j.is_array()))
3634 {
3635 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " +
3636 std::string(j.type_name())));
3637 }
3638
3639 from_json_array_impl(j, arr, priority_tag<3> {});
3640 }

3653 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleObjectType,
3654 enable_if_t<is_constructible_object_type<BasicJsonType, ConstructibleObjectType>::value, int> = 0>
3655 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, ConstructibleObjectType& obj)
3656 {
3657 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!j.is_object()))
3658 {
3659 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be object, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
3660 }
3661
3662 ConstructibleObjectType ret;
3663 auto inner_object = j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::object_t*>();
3664 using value_type = typename ConstructibleObjectType::value_type;
3665 std::transform(
3666 inner_object->begin(), inner_object->end(),
3667 std::inserter(ret, ret.begin()),
3668 [](typename BasicJsonType::object_t::value_type const & p)
3669 {
3670 return value_type(p.first, p.second.template get<typename ConstructibleObjectType::mapped_type>());
3671 });
3672 obj = std::move(ret);
3673 }
3674
3675 // overload for arithmetic types, not chosen for basic_json template arguments
3676 // (BooleanType, etc..); note: Is it really necessary to provide explicit
3677 // overloads for boolean_t etc. in case of a custom BooleanType which is not
3678 // an arithmetic type?
3679 template < typename BasicJsonType, typename ArithmeticType,
3680 enable_if_t <
3681 std::is_arithmetic<ArithmeticType>::value&&
3682 !std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t>::value&&
3683 !std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t>::value&&
3684 !std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t>::value&&
3685 !std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t>::value,
3686 int > = 0 >
3687 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, ArithmeticType& val)
3688 {
3689 switch (static_cast<value_t>(j))
3690 {
3691 case value_t::number_unsigned:
3692 {
3693 val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t*>());
3694 break;
3695 }
3696 case value_t::number_integer:
3697 {
3698 val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t*>());
3699 break;
3700 }
3701 case value_t::number_float:
3702 {
3703 val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t*>());
3704 break;
3705 }
3706 case value_t::boolean:
3707 {
3708 val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t*>());
3709 break;
3710 }
3711
3712 default:
3713 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be number, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
3714 }
3715 }

3718 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::pair<A1, A2>& p)
3719 {
3720 p = {j.at(0).template get<A1>(), j.at(1).template get<A2>()};

3723 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename Tuple, std::size_t... Idx>
3724 void from_json_tuple_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, Tuple& t, index_sequence<Idx...> /*unused*/)
3725 {
3726 t = std::make_tuple(j.at(Idx).template get<typename std::tuple_element<Idx, Tuple>::type>()...);
3727 }

3729 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename... Args>
3730 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::tuple<Args...>& t)
3731 {
3732 from_json_tuple_impl(j, t, index_sequence_for<Args...> {});
3733 }

3735 template < typename BasicJsonType, typename Key, typename Value, typename Compare, typename Allocator,
3736 typename = enable_if_t < !std::is_constructible <
3737 typename BasicJsonType::string_t, Key >::value >>
3738 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::map<Key, Value, Compare, Allocator>& m)
3739 {
3740 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!j.is_array()))
3741 {
3742 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
3743 }
3744 m.clear();
3745 for (const auto& p : j)
3746 {
3747 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!p.is_array()))
3748 {
3749 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(p.type_name())));
3750 }
3751 m.emplace(p.at(0).template get<Key>(), p.at(1).template get<Value>());
3752 }
3753 }
3754
3755 template < typename BasicJsonType, typename Key, typename Value, typename Hash, typename KeyEqual, typename Allocator,
3756 typename = enable_if_t < !std::is_constructible <
3757 typename BasicJsonType::string_t, Key >::value >>
3758 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::unordered_map<Key, Value, Hash, KeyEqual, Allocator>& m)
3759 {
3760 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!j.is_array()))
3761 {
3762 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
3763 }
3764 m.clear();
3765 for (const auto& p : j)
3766 {
3767 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!p.is_array()))
3768 {
3769 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(p.type_name())));
3770 }
3771 m.emplace(p.at(0).template get<Key>(), p.at(1).template get<Value>());
3772 }
3773 }
3774
3775 struct from_json_fn
3776 {
3777 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
3778 auto operator()(const BasicJsonType& j, T& val) const
3779 noexcept(noexcept(from_json(j, val)))
3780 -> decltype(from_json(j, val), void())
3781 {
3782 return from_json(j, val);
3783 }
3784 };
3785 } // namespace detail
3786
3790 namespace
3791 {
3792 constexpr const auto& from_json = detail::static_const<detail::from_json_fn>::value;
3793 } // namespace
3794} // namespace nlohmann

3825 template<typename string_type>
3826 void int_to_string( string_type& target, std::size_t value )
3827 {
3828 // For ADL
3829 using std::to_string;
3830 target = to_string(value);
3831 }
3832 template<typename IteratorType> class iteration_proxy_value
3833 {
3834 public:
3835 using difference_type = std::ptrdiff_t;
3836 using value_type = iteration_proxy_value;
3837 using pointer = value_type * ;
3838 using reference = value_type & ;
3839 using iterator_category = std::input_iterator_tag;
3840 using string_type = typename std::remove_cv< typename std::remove_reference<decltype( std::declval<IteratorType>().key() ) >::type >::type;
3841
3842 private:
3844 IteratorType anchor;
3846 std::size_t array_index = 0;
3848 mutable std::size_t array_index_last = 0;
3850 mutable string_type array_index_str = "0";
3852 const string_type empty_str = "";
3853
3854 public:
3855 explicit iteration_proxy_value(IteratorType it) noexcept : anchor(it) {}
3856
3858 iteration_proxy_value& operator*()
3859 {
3860 return *this;
3861 }
3862
3864 iteration_proxy_value& operator++()
3865 {
3866 ++anchor;
3867 ++array_index;
3868
3869 return *this;
3870 }
3871
3873 bool operator==(const iteration_proxy_value& o) const
3874 {
3875 return anchor == o.anchor;
3876 }
3877
3879 bool operator!=(const iteration_proxy_value& o) const
3880 {
3881 return anchor != o.anchor;
3882 }
3883
3885 const string_type& key() const
3886 {
3887 JSON_ASSERT(anchor.m_object != nullptr);
3888
3889 switch (anchor.m_object->type())
3890 {
3891 // use integer array index as key
3892 case value_t::array:
3893 {
3894 if (array_index != array_index_last)
3895 {
3896 int_to_string( array_index_str, array_index );
3897 array_index_last = array_index;
3898 }
3899 return array_index_str;
3900 }
3901
3902 // use key from the object
3903 case value_t::object:
3904 return anchor.key();
3905
3906 // use an empty key for all primitive types
3907 default:
3908 return empty_str;
3909 }
3910 }
3911
3913 typename IteratorType::reference value() const
3914 {
3915 return anchor.value();
3916 }
3917 };
3918
3920 template<typename IteratorType> class iteration_proxy
3921 {
3922 private:
3924 typename IteratorType::reference container;
3925
3926 public:
3928 explicit iteration_proxy(typename IteratorType::reference cont) noexcept
3929 : container(cont) {}
3930
3932 iteration_proxy_value<IteratorType> begin() noexcept
3933 {
3934 return iteration_proxy_value<IteratorType>(container.begin());
3935 }
3936
3938 iteration_proxy_value<IteratorType> end() noexcept
3939 {
3940 return iteration_proxy_value<IteratorType>(container.end());
3941 }
3942 };
3943 // Structured Bindings Support
3944 // For further reference see https://blog.tartanllama.xyz/structured-bindings/
3945 // And see https://github.com/nlohmann/json/pull/1391
3946 template<std::size_t N, typename IteratorType, enable_if_t<N == 0, int> = 0>
3947 auto get(const nlohmann::detail::iteration_proxy_value<IteratorType>& i) -> decltype(i.key())
3948 {
3949 return i.key();
3950 }
3951 // Structured Bindings Support
3952 // For further reference see https://blog.tartanllama.xyz/structured-bindings/
3953 // And see https://github.com/nlohmann/json/pull/1391
3954 template<std::size_t N, typename IteratorType, enable_if_t<N == 1, int> = 0>
3955 auto get(const nlohmann::detail::iteration_proxy_value<IteratorType>& i) -> decltype(i.value())
3956 {
3957 return i.value();
3958 }
3959 } // namespace detail
3960} // namespace nlohmann

4156 j.m_value = value_t::array;
4157 j.m_value.array->resize(arr.size());
4158 if (arr.size() > 0)
4159 {
4160 std::copy(std::begin(arr), std::end(arr), j.m_value.array->begin());
4161 }
4162 j.assert_invariant();

4423 template<typename BinaryType>
4424 class byte_container_with_subtype : public BinaryType
4425 {
4426 public:
4428 using container_type = BinaryType;
4429
4430 byte_container_with_subtype() noexcept(noexcept(container_type()))
4431 : container_type()
4432 {}
4433
4434 byte_container_with_subtype(const container_type& b) noexcept(noexcept(container_type(b)))
4435 : container_type(b)
4436 {}
4437
4438 byte_container_with_subtype(container_type&& b) noexcept(noexcept(container_type(std::move(b))))
4439 : container_type(std::move(b))
4440 {}
4441
4442 byte_container_with_subtype(const container_type& b, std::uint8_t subtype) noexcept(noexcept(container_type(b)))
4443 : container_type(b)
4444 , m_subtype(subtype)
4445 , m_has_subtype(true)
4446 {}
4447
4448 byte_container_with_subtype(container_type&& b, std::uint8_t subtype) noexcept(noexcept(container_type(std::move(b))))
4449 : container_type(std::move(b))
4450 , m_subtype(subtype)
4451 , m_has_subtype(true)
4452 {}
4453
4454 bool operator==(const byte_container_with_subtype& rhs) const
4455 {
4456 return std::tie(static_cast<const BinaryType&>(*this), m_subtype, m_has_subtype) ==
4457 std::tie(static_cast<const BinaryType&>(rhs), rhs.m_subtype, rhs.m_has_subtype);
4458 }
4459
4460 bool operator!=(const byte_container_with_subtype& rhs) const
4461 {
4462 return !(rhs == *this);
4463 }
4464
4483 void set_subtype(std::uint8_t subtype) noexcept
4484 {
4485 m_subtype = subtype;
4486 m_has_subtype = true;
4487 }
4488
4510 constexpr std::uint8_t subtype() const noexcept
4511 {
4512 return m_subtype;
4513 }
4514
4531 constexpr bool has_subtype() const noexcept
4532 {
4533 return m_has_subtype;
4534 }
4535
4555 void clear_subtype() noexcept
4556 {
4557 m_subtype = 0;
4558 m_has_subtype = false;
4559 }
4560
4561 private:
4562 std::uint8_t m_subtype = 0;
4563 bool m_has_subtype = false;
4564 };
4565
4566} // namespace nlohmann

4578#include <functional> // hash

4582 namespace detail

4584
4585 // boost::hash_combine
4586 inline std::size_t combine(std::size_t seed, std::size_t h) noexcept
4587 {
4588 seed ^= h + 0x9e3779b9 + (seed << 6U) + (seed >> 2U);
4589 return seed;
4590 }
4591
4603 template<typename BasicJsonType>
4604 std::size_t hash(const BasicJsonType& j)
4605 {
4606 using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
4607 using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
4608 using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
4609 using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
4610
4611 const auto type = static_cast<std::size_t>(j.type());
4612 switch (j.type())
4613 {
4614 case BasicJsonType::value_t::null:
4615 case BasicJsonType::value_t::discarded:
4616 {
4617 return combine(type, 0);
4618 }
4619
4620 case BasicJsonType::value_t::object:
4621 {
4622 auto seed = combine(type, j.size());
4623 for (const auto& element : j.items())
4624 {
4625 const auto h = std::hash<string_t> {}(element.key());
4626 seed = combine(seed, h);
4627 seed = combine(seed, hash(element.value()));
4628 }
4629 return seed;
4630 }
4631
4632 case BasicJsonType::value_t::array:
4633 {
4634 auto seed = combine(type, j.size());
4635 for (const auto& element : j)
4636 {
4637 seed = combine(seed, hash(element));
4638 }
4639 return seed;
4640 }
4641
4642 case BasicJsonType::value_t::string:
4643 {
4644 const auto h = std::hash<string_t> {}(j.template get_ref<const string_t&>());
4645 return combine(type, h);
4646 }
4647
4648 case BasicJsonType::value_t::boolean:
4649 {
4650 const auto h = std::hash<bool> {}(j.template get<bool>());
4651 return combine(type, h);
4652 }
4653
4654 case BasicJsonType::value_t::number_integer:
4655 {
4656 const auto h = std::hash<number_integer_t> {}(j.template get<number_integer_t>());
4657 return combine(type, h);
4658 }
4659
4660 case nlohmann::detail::value_t::number_unsigned:
4661 {
4662 const auto h = std::hash<number_unsigned_t> {}(j.template get<number_unsigned_t>());
4663 return combine(type, h);
4664 }
4665
4666 case nlohmann::detail::value_t::number_float:
4667 {
4668 const auto h = std::hash<number_float_t> {}(j.template get<number_float_t>());
4669 return combine(type, h);
4670 }
4671
4672 case nlohmann::detail::value_t::binary:
4673 {
4674 auto seed = combine(type, j.get_binary().size());
4675 const auto h = std::hash<bool> {}(j.get_binary().has_subtype());
4676 seed = combine(seed, h);
4677 seed = combine(seed, j.get_binary().subtype());
4678 for (const auto byte : j.get_binary())
4679 {
4680 seed = combine(seed, std::hash<std::uint8_t> {}(byte));
4681 }
4682 return seed;
4683 }
4684
4685 default: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
4686 JSON_ASSERT(false); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
4687 }
4688 }
4689
4690 } // namespace detail
4691} // namespace nlohmann

4781 class input_stream_adapter
4782 {
4783 public:
4784 using char_type = char;
4785
4786 ~input_stream_adapter()
4787 {
4788 // clear stream flags; we use underlying streambuf I/O, do not
4789 // maintain ifstream flags, except eof
4790 if (is != nullptr)
4791 {
4792 is->clear(is->rdstate() & std::ios::eofbit);
4793 }
4794 }
4795
4796 explicit input_stream_adapter(std::istream& i)
4797 : is(&i), sb(i.rdbuf())
4798 {}
4799
4800 // delete because of pointer members
4801 input_stream_adapter(const input_stream_adapter&) = delete;
4802 input_stream_adapter& operator=(input_stream_adapter&) = delete;
4803 input_stream_adapter& operator=(input_stream_adapter&& rhs) = delete;
4804
4805 input_stream_adapter(input_stream_adapter&& rhs) noexcept : is(rhs.is), sb(rhs.sb)
4806 {
4807 rhs.is = nullptr;
4808 rhs.sb = nullptr;
4809 }
4810
4811 // std::istream/std::streambuf use std::char_traits<char>::to_int_type, to
4812 // ensure that std::char_traits<char>::eof() and the character 0xFF do not
4813 // end up as the same value, eg. 0xFFFFFFFF.
4814 std::char_traits<char>::int_type get_character()
4815 {
4816 auto res = sb->sbumpc();
4817 // set eof manually, as we don't use the istream interface.
4818 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(res == EOF))
4819 {
4820 is->clear(is->rdstate() | std::ios::eofbit);
4821 }
4822 return res;
4823 }
4824
4825 private:
4827 std::istream* is = nullptr;
4828 std::streambuf* sb = nullptr;
4829 };

4831 // General-purpose iterator-based adapter. It might not be as fast as
4832 // theoretically possible for some containers, but it is extremely versatile.
4833 template<typename IteratorType>
4834 class iterator_input_adapter
4835 {
4836 public:
4837 using char_type = typename std::iterator_traits<IteratorType>::value_type;
4838
4839 iterator_input_adapter(IteratorType first, IteratorType last)
4840 : current(std::move(first)), end(std::move(last)) {}
4841
4842 typename std::char_traits<char_type>::int_type get_character()
4843 {
4844 if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(current != end))
4845 {
4846 auto result = std::char_traits<char_type>::to_int_type(*current);
4847 std::advance(current, 1);
4848 return result;
4849 }
4850 else
4851 {
4852 return std::char_traits<char_type>::eof();
4853 }
4854 }
4855
4856 private:
4857 IteratorType current;
4858 IteratorType end;
4859
4860 template<typename BaseInputAdapter, size_t T>
4861 friend struct wide_string_input_helper;
4862
4863 bool empty() const
4864 {
4865 return current == end;
4866 }
4867
4868 };
4869
4870
4871 template<typename BaseInputAdapter, size_t T>
4872 struct wide_string_input_helper;
4873
4874 template<typename BaseInputAdapter>
4875 struct wide_string_input_helper<BaseInputAdapter, 4>
4876 {
4877 // UTF-32
4878 static void fill_buffer(BaseInputAdapter& input,
4879 std::array<std::char_traits<char>::int_type, 4>& utf8_bytes,
4880 size_t& utf8_bytes_index,
4881 size_t& utf8_bytes_filled)
4882 {
4883 utf8_bytes_index = 0;
4884
4885 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(input.empty()))
4886 {
4887 utf8_bytes[0] = std::char_traits<char>::eof();
4888 utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
4889 }
4890 else
4891 {
4892 // get the current character
4893 const auto wc = input.get_character();
4894
4895 // UTF-32 to UTF-8 encoding
4896 if (wc < 0x80)
4897 {
4898 utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(wc);
4899 utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
4900 }
4901 else if (wc <= 0x7FF)
4902 {
4903 utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0xC0u | ((static_cast<unsigned int>(wc) >> 6u) & 0x1Fu));
4904 utf8_bytes[1] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(wc) & 0x3Fu));
4905 utf8_bytes_filled = 2;
4906 }
4907 else if (wc <= 0xFFFF)
4908 {
4909 utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0xE0u | ((static_cast<unsigned int>(wc) >> 12u) & 0x0Fu));
4910 utf8_bytes[1] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | ((static_cast<unsigned int>(wc) >> 6u) & 0x3Fu));
4911 utf8_bytes[2] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(wc) & 0x3Fu));
4912 utf8_bytes_filled = 3;
4913 }
4914 else if (wc <= 0x10FFFF)
4915 {
4916 utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0xF0u | ((static_cast<unsigned int>(wc) >> 18u) & 0x07u));
4917 utf8_bytes[1] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | ((static_cast<unsigned int>(wc) >> 12u) & 0x3Fu));
4918 utf8_bytes[2] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | ((static_cast<unsigned int>(wc) >> 6u) & 0x3Fu));
4919 utf8_bytes[3] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(wc) & 0x3Fu));
4920 utf8_bytes_filled = 4;
4921 }
4922 else
4923 {
4924 // unknown character
4925 utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(wc);
4926 utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
4927 }
4928 }
4929 }
4930 };
4931
4932 template<typename BaseInputAdapter>
4933 struct wide_string_input_helper<BaseInputAdapter, 2>
4934 {
4935 // UTF-16
4936 static void fill_buffer(BaseInputAdapter& input,
4937 std::array<std::char_traits<char>::int_type, 4>& utf8_bytes,
4938 size_t& utf8_bytes_index,
4939 size_t& utf8_bytes_filled)
4940 {
4941 utf8_bytes_index = 0;
4942
4943 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(input.empty()))
4944 {
4945 utf8_bytes[0] = std::char_traits<char>::eof();
4946 utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
4947 }
4948 else
4949 {
4950 // get the current character
4951 const auto wc = input.get_character();
4952
4953 // UTF-16 to UTF-8 encoding
4954 if (wc < 0x80)
4955 {
4956 utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(wc);
4957 utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
4958 }
4959 else if (wc <= 0x7FF)
4960 {
4961 utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0xC0u | ((static_cast<unsigned int>(wc) >> 6u)));
4962 utf8_bytes[1] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(wc) & 0x3Fu));
4963 utf8_bytes_filled = 2;
4964 }
4965 else if (0xD800 > wc || wc >= 0xE000)
4966 {
4967 utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0xE0u | ((static_cast<unsigned int>(wc) >> 12u)));
4968 utf8_bytes[1] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | ((static_cast<unsigned int>(wc) >> 6u) & 0x3Fu));
4969 utf8_bytes[2] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(wc) & 0x3Fu));
4970 utf8_bytes_filled = 3;
4971 }
4972 else
4973 {
4974 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!input.empty()))
4975 {
4976 const auto wc2 = static_cast<unsigned int>(input.get_character());
4977 const auto charcode = 0x10000u + (((static_cast<unsigned int>(wc) & 0x3FFu) << 10u) | (wc2 & 0x3FFu));
4978 utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0xF0u | (charcode >> 18u));
4979 utf8_bytes[1] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | ((charcode >> 12u) & 0x3Fu));
4980 utf8_bytes[2] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | ((charcode >> 6u) & 0x3Fu));
4981 utf8_bytes[3] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | (charcode & 0x3Fu));
4982 utf8_bytes_filled = 4;
4983 }
4984 else
4985 {
4986 utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(wc);
4987 utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
4988 }
4989 }
4990 }
4991 }
4992 };
4993
4994 // Wraps another input apdater to convert wide character types into individual bytes.
4995 template<typename BaseInputAdapter, typename WideCharType>
4996 class wide_string_input_adapter
4997 {
4998 public:
4999 using char_type = char;
5000
5001 wide_string_input_adapter(BaseInputAdapter base)
5002 : base_adapter(base) {}
5003
5004 typename std::char_traits<char>::int_type get_character() noexcept
5005 {
5006 // check if buffer needs to be filled
5007 if (utf8_bytes_index == utf8_bytes_filled)
5008 {
5009 fill_buffer<sizeof(WideCharType)>();
5010
5011 JSON_ASSERT(utf8_bytes_filled > 0);
5012 JSON_ASSERT(utf8_bytes_index == 0);
5013 }
5014
5015 // use buffer
5016 JSON_ASSERT(utf8_bytes_filled > 0);
5017 JSON_ASSERT(utf8_bytes_index < utf8_bytes_filled);
5018 return utf8_bytes[utf8_bytes_index++];
5019 }
5020
5021 private:
5022 BaseInputAdapter base_adapter;
5023
5024 template<size_t T>
5025 void fill_buffer()
5026 {
5027 wide_string_input_helper<BaseInputAdapter, T>::fill_buffer(base_adapter, utf8_bytes, utf8_bytes_index, utf8_bytes_filled);
5028 }
5029
5031 std::array<std::char_traits<char>::int_type, 4> utf8_bytes = {{0, 0, 0, 0}};
5032
5034 std::size_t utf8_bytes_index = 0;
5036 std::size_t utf8_bytes_filled = 0;
5037 };
5038

5040 template<typename IteratorType, typename Enable = void>
5041 struct iterator_input_adapter_factory
5042 {
5043 using iterator_type = IteratorType;
5044 using char_type = typename std::iterator_traits<iterator_type>::value_type;
5045 using adapter_type = iterator_input_adapter<iterator_type>;
5046
5047 static adapter_type create(IteratorType first, IteratorType last)
5048 {
5049 return adapter_type(std::move(first), std::move(last));
5050 }
5051 };
5052
5053 template<typename T>
5054 struct is_iterator_of_multibyte
5055 {
5056 using value_type = typename std::iterator_traits<T>::value_type;
5057 enum
5058 {
5059 value = sizeof(value_type) > 1
5060 };
5061 };
5062
5063 template<typename IteratorType>
5064 struct iterator_input_adapter_factory<IteratorType, enable_if_t<is_iterator_of_multibyte<IteratorType>::value>>
5065 {
5066 using iterator_type = IteratorType;
5067 using char_type = typename std::iterator_traits<iterator_type>::value_type;
5068 using base_adapter_type = iterator_input_adapter<iterator_type>;
5069 using adapter_type = wide_string_input_adapter<base_adapter_type, char_type>;
5070
5071 static adapter_type create(IteratorType first, IteratorType last)
5072 {
5073 return adapter_type(base_adapter_type(std::move(first), std::move(last)));
5074 }
5075 };
5076
5077 // General purpose iterator-based input
5078 template<typename IteratorType>
5079 typename iterator_input_adapter_factory<IteratorType>::adapter_type input_adapter(IteratorType first, IteratorType last)
5080 {
5081 using factory_type = iterator_input_adapter_factory<IteratorType>;
5082 return factory_type::create(first, last);
5083 }
5084
5085 // Convenience shorthand from container to iterator
5086 template<typename ContainerType>
5087 auto input_adapter(const ContainerType& container) -> decltype(input_adapter(begin(container), end(container)))
5088 {
5089 // Enable ADL
5090 using std::begin;
5091 using std::end;
5092
5093 return input_adapter(begin(container), end(container));
5094 }

5099 return file_input_adapter(file);

5111
5112 using contiguous_bytes_input_adapter = decltype(input_adapter(std::declval<const char*>(), std::declval<const char*>()));
5113
5114 // Null-delimited strings, and the like.
5115 template < typename CharT,
5116 typename std::enable_if <
5117 std::is_pointer<CharT>::value&&
5118 !std::is_array<CharT>::value&&
5119 std::is_integral<typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type>::value&&
5120 sizeof(typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type) == 1,
5121 int >::type = 0 >
5122 contiguous_bytes_input_adapter input_adapter(CharT b)
5123 {
5124 auto length = std::strlen(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(b));
5125 const auto* ptr = reinterpret_cast<const char*>(b);
5126 return input_adapter(ptr, ptr + length);
5127 }
5128
5129 template<typename T, std::size_t N>
5130 auto input_adapter(T (&array)[N]) -> decltype(input_adapter(array, array + N))
5131 {
5132 return input_adapter(array, array + N);
5133 }

5135 // This class only handles inputs of input_buffer_adapter type.
5136 // It's required so that expressions like {ptr, len} can be implicitely casted
5137 // to the correct adapter.
5138 class span_input_adapter
5139 {
5140 public:
5141 template < typename CharT,
5142 typename std::enable_if <
5143 std::is_pointer<CharT>::value&&
5144 std::is_integral<typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type>::value&&
5145 sizeof(typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type) == 1,
5146 int >::type = 0 >
5147 span_input_adapter(CharT b, std::size_t l)
5148 : ia(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(b), reinterpret_cast<const char*>(b) + l) {}
5149
5150 template<class IteratorType,
5151 typename std::enable_if<
5152 std::is_same<typename iterator_traits<IteratorType>::iterator_category, std::random_access_iterator_tag>::value,
5153 int>::type = 0>
5154 span_input_adapter(IteratorType first, IteratorType last)
5155 : ia(input_adapter(first, last)) {}
5156
5157 contiguous_bytes_input_adapter&& get()
5158 {
5159 return std::move(ia);
5160 }
5161
5162 private:
5163 contiguous_bytes_input_adapter ia;
5164 };

5318 template<typename BasicJsonType>
5319 class json_sax_dom_parser
5320 {
5321 public:
5322 using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
5323 using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
5324 using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
5325 using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
5326 using binary_t = typename BasicJsonType::binary_t;
5327
5333 explicit json_sax_dom_parser(BasicJsonType& r, const bool allow_exceptions_ = true)
5334 : root(r), allow_exceptions(allow_exceptions_)
5335 {}
5336
5337 // make class move-only
5338 json_sax_dom_parser(const json_sax_dom_parser&) = delete;
5339 json_sax_dom_parser(json_sax_dom_parser&&) = default;
5340 json_sax_dom_parser& operator=(const json_sax_dom_parser&) = delete;
5341 json_sax_dom_parser& operator=(json_sax_dom_parser&&) = default;
5342 ~json_sax_dom_parser() = default;
5343
5344 bool null()
5345 {
5346 handle_value(nullptr);
5347 return true;
5348 }
5349
5350 bool boolean(bool val)
5351 {
5352 handle_value(val);
5353 return true;
5354 }
5355
5356 bool number_integer(number_integer_t val)
5357 {
5358 handle_value(val);
5359 return true;
5360 }
5361
5362 bool number_unsigned(number_unsigned_t val)
5363 {
5364 handle_value(val);
5365 return true;
5366 }
5367
5368 bool number_float(number_float_t val, const string_t& /*unused*/)
5369 {
5370 handle_value(val);
5371 return true;
5372 }
5373
5374 bool string(string_t& val)
5375 {
5376 handle_value(val);
5377 return true;
5378 }
5379
5380 bool binary(binary_t& val)
5381 {
5382 handle_value(std::move(val));
5383 return true;
5384 }
5385
5386 bool start_object(std::size_t len)
5387 {
5388 ref_stack.push_back(handle_value(BasicJsonType::value_t::object));
5389
5390 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(len != std::size_t(-1) && len > ref_stack.back()->max_size()))
5391 {
5392 JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(408,
5393 "excessive object size: " + std::to_string(len)));
5394 }
5395
5396 return true;
5397 }
5398
5399 bool key(string_t& val)
5400 {
5401 // add null at given key and store the reference for later
5402 object_element = &(ref_stack.back()->m_value.object->operator[](val));
5403 return true;
5404 }
5405
5406 bool end_object()
5407 {
5408 ref_stack.pop_back();
5409 return true;
5410 }
5411
5412 bool start_array(std::size_t len)
5413 {
5414 ref_stack.push_back(handle_value(BasicJsonType::value_t::array));
5415
5416 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(len != std::size_t(-1) && len > ref_stack.back()->max_size()))
5417 {
5418 JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(408,
5419 "excessive array size: " + std::to_string(len)));
5420 }
5421
5422 return true;
5423 }
5424
5425 bool end_array()
5426 {
5427 ref_stack.pop_back();
5428 return true;
5429 }
5430
5431 template<class Exception>
5432 bool parse_error(std::size_t /*unused*/, const std::string& /*unused*/,
5433 const Exception& ex)
5434 {
5435 errored = true;
5436 static_cast<void>(ex);
5437 if (allow_exceptions)
5438 {
5439 JSON_THROW(ex);
5440 }
5441 return false;
5442 }
5443
5444 constexpr bool is_errored() const
5445 {
5446 return errored;
5447 }
5448
5449 private:
5456 template<typename Value>
5457 JSON_HEDLEY_RETURNS_NON_NULL
5458 BasicJsonType* handle_value(Value&& v)
5459 {
5460 if (ref_stack.empty())
5461 {
5462 root = BasicJsonType(std::forward<Value>(v));
5463 return &root;
5464 }
5465
5466 JSON_ASSERT(ref_stack.back()->is_array() || ref_stack.back()->is_object());
5467
5468 if (ref_stack.back()->is_array())
5469 {
5470 ref_stack.back()->m_value.array->emplace_back(std::forward<Value>(v));
5471 return &(ref_stack.back()->m_value.array->back());
5472 }
5473
5474 JSON_ASSERT(ref_stack.back()->is_object());
5475 JSON_ASSERT(object_element);
5476 *object_element = BasicJsonType(std::forward<Value>(v));
5477 return object_element;
5478 }
5479
5481 BasicJsonType& root;
5483 std::vector<BasicJsonType*> ref_stack {};
5485 BasicJsonType* object_element = nullptr;
5487 bool errored = false;
5489 const bool allow_exceptions = true;
5490 };
5491
5492 template<typename BasicJsonType>
5493 class json_sax_dom_callback_parser
5494 {
5495 public:
5496 using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
5497 using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
5498 using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
5499 using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
5500 using binary_t = typename BasicJsonType::binary_t;
5501 using parser_callback_t = typename BasicJsonType::parser_callback_t;
5502 using parse_event_t = typename BasicJsonType::parse_event_t;
5503
5504 json_sax_dom_callback_parser(BasicJsonType& r,
5505 const parser_callback_t cb,
5506 const bool allow_exceptions_ = true)
5507 : root(r), callback(cb), allow_exceptions(allow_exceptions_)
5508 {
5509 keep_stack.push_back(true);
5510 }
5511
5512 // make class move-only
5513 json_sax_dom_callback_parser(const json_sax_dom_callback_parser&) = delete;
5514 json_sax_dom_callback_parser(json_sax_dom_callback_parser&&) = default;
5515 json_sax_dom_callback_parser& operator=(const json_sax_dom_callback_parser&) = delete;
5516 json_sax_dom_callback_parser& operator=(json_sax_dom_callback_parser&&) = default;
5517 ~json_sax_dom_callback_parser() = default;
5518
5519 bool null()
5520 {
5521 handle_value(nullptr);
5522 return true;
5523 }
5524
5525 bool boolean(bool val)
5526 {
5527 handle_value(val);
5528 return true;
5529 }
5530
5531 bool number_integer(number_integer_t val)
5532 {
5533 handle_value(val);
5534 return true;
5535 }
5536
5537 bool number_unsigned(number_unsigned_t val)
5538 {
5539 handle_value(val);
5540 return true;
5541 }
5542
5543 bool number_float(number_float_t val, const string_t& /*unused*/)
5544 {
5545 handle_value(val);
5546 return true;
5547 }
5548
5549 bool string(string_t& val)
5550 {
5551 handle_value(val);
5552 return true;
5553 }
5554
5555 bool binary(binary_t& val)
5556 {
5557 handle_value(std::move(val));
5558 return true;
5559 }
5560
5561 bool start_object(std::size_t len)
5562 {
5563 // check callback for object start
5564 const bool keep = callback(static_cast<int>(ref_stack.size()), parse_event_t::object_start, discarded);
5565 keep_stack.push_back(keep);
5566
5567 auto val = handle_value(BasicJsonType::value_t::object, true);
5568 ref_stack.push_back(val.second);
5569
5570 // check object limit
5571 if (ref_stack.back() && JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(len != std::size_t(-1) && len > ref_stack.back()->max_size()))
5572 {
5573 JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(408, "excessive object size: " + std::to_string(len)));
5574 }
5575
5576 return true;
5577 }
5578
5579 bool key(string_t& val)
5580 {
5581 BasicJsonType k = BasicJsonType(val);
5582
5583 // check callback for key
5584 const bool keep = callback(static_cast<int>(ref_stack.size()), parse_event_t::key, k);
5585 key_keep_stack.push_back(keep);
5586
5587 // add discarded value at given key and store the reference for later
5588 if (keep && ref_stack.back())
5589 {
5590 object_element = &(ref_stack.back()->m_value.object->operator[](val) = discarded);
5591 }
5592
5593 return true;
5594 }
5595
5596 bool end_object()
5597 {
5598 if (ref_stack.back() && !callback(static_cast<int>(ref_stack.size()) - 1, parse_event_t::object_end, *ref_stack.back()))
5599 {
5600 // discard object
5601 *ref_stack.back() = discarded;
5602 }
5603
5604 JSON_ASSERT(!ref_stack.empty());
5605 JSON_ASSERT(!keep_stack.empty());
5606 ref_stack.pop_back();
5607 keep_stack.pop_back();
5608
5609 if (!ref_stack.empty() && ref_stack.back() && ref_stack.back()->is_structured())
5610 {
5611 // remove discarded value
5612 for (auto it = ref_stack.back()->begin(); it != ref_stack.back()->end(); ++it)
5613 {
5614 if (it->is_discarded())
5615 {
5616 ref_stack.back()->erase(it);
5617 break;
5618 }
5619 }
5620 }
5621
5622 return true;
5623 }
5624
5625 bool start_array(std::size_t len)
5626 {
5627 const bool keep = callback(static_cast<int>(ref_stack.size()), parse_event_t::array_start, discarded);
5628 keep_stack.push_back(keep);
5629
5630 auto val = handle_value(BasicJsonType::value_t::array, true);
5631 ref_stack.push_back(val.second);
5632
5633 // check array limit
5634 if (ref_stack.back() && JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(len != std::size_t(-1) && len > ref_stack.back()->max_size()))
5635 {
5636 JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(408, "excessive array size: " + std::to_string(len)));
5637 }
5638
5639 return true;
5640 }
5641
5642 bool end_array()
5643 {
5644 bool keep = true;
5645
5646 if (ref_stack.back())
5647 {
5648 keep = callback(static_cast<int>(ref_stack.size()) - 1, parse_event_t::array_end, *ref_stack.back());
5649 if (!keep)
5650 {
5651 // discard array
5652 *ref_stack.back() = discarded;
5653 }
5654 }
5655
5656 JSON_ASSERT(!ref_stack.empty());
5657 JSON_ASSERT(!keep_stack.empty());
5658 ref_stack.pop_back();
5659 keep_stack.pop_back();
5660
5661 // remove discarded value
5662 if (!keep && !ref_stack.empty() && ref_stack.back()->is_array())
5663 {
5664 ref_stack.back()->m_value.array->pop_back();
5665 }
5666
5667 return true;
5668 }
5669
5670 template<class Exception>
5671 bool parse_error(std::size_t /*unused*/, const std::string& /*unused*/,
5672 const Exception& ex)
5673 {
5674 errored = true;
5675 static_cast<void>(ex);
5676 if (allow_exceptions)
5677 {
5678 JSON_THROW(ex);
5679 }
5680 return false;
5681 }
5682
5683 constexpr bool is_errored() const
5684 {
5685 return errored;
5686 }
5687
5688 private:
5704 template<typename Value>
5705 std::pair<bool, BasicJsonType*> handle_value(Value&& v, const bool skip_callback = false)
5706 {
5707 JSON_ASSERT(!keep_stack.empty());
5708
5709 // do not handle this value if we know it would be added to a discarded
5710 // container
5711 if (!keep_stack.back())
5712 {
5713 return {false, nullptr};
5714 }
5715
5716 // create value
5717 auto value = BasicJsonType(std::forward<Value>(v));
5718
5719 // check callback
5720 const bool keep = skip_callback || callback(static_cast<int>(ref_stack.size()), parse_event_t::value, value);
5721
5722 // do not handle this value if we just learnt it shall be discarded
5723 if (!keep)
5724 {
5725 return {false, nullptr};
5726 }
5727
5728 if (ref_stack.empty())
5729 {
5730 root = std::move(value);
5731 return {true, &root};
5732 }
5733
5734 // skip this value if we already decided to skip the parent
5735 // (https://github.com/nlohmann/json/issues/971#issuecomment-413678360)
5736 if (!ref_stack.back())
5737 {
5738 return {false, nullptr};
5739 }
5740
5741 // we now only expect arrays and objects
5742 JSON_ASSERT(ref_stack.back()->is_array() || ref_stack.back()->is_object());
5743
5744 // array
5745 if (ref_stack.back()->is_array())
5746 {
5747 ref_stack.back()->m_value.array->push_back(std::move(value));
5748 return {true, &(ref_stack.back()->m_value.array->back())};
5749 }
5750
5751 // object
5752 JSON_ASSERT(ref_stack.back()->is_object());
5753 // check if we should store an element for the current key
5754 JSON_ASSERT(!key_keep_stack.empty());
5755 const bool store_element = key_keep_stack.back();
5756 key_keep_stack.pop_back();
5757
5758 if (!store_element)
5759 {
5760 return {false, nullptr};
5761 }
5762
5763 JSON_ASSERT(object_element);
5764 *object_element = std::move(value);
5765 return {true, object_element};
5766 }
5767
5769 BasicJsonType& root;
5771 std::vector<BasicJsonType*> ref_stack {};
5773 std::vector<bool> keep_stack {};
5775 std::vector<bool> key_keep_stack {};
5777 BasicJsonType* object_element = nullptr;
5779 bool errored = false;
5781 const parser_callback_t callback = nullptr;
5783 const bool allow_exceptions = true;
5785 BasicJsonType discarded = BasicJsonType::value_t::discarded;
5786 };
5787

5794 using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
5795 using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
5796 using binary_t = typename BasicJsonType::binary_t;
5797

5799 {
5800 return true;
5801 }
5802

5892 // lexer //
5894
5895 template<typename BasicJsonType>
5896 class lexer_base
5897 {
5898 public:
5900 enum class token_type
5901 {
5902 uninitialized,
5903 literal_true,
5904 literal_false,
5905 literal_null,
5906 value_string,
5907 value_unsigned,
5908 value_integer,
5909 value_float,
5910 begin_array,
5911 begin_object,
5912 end_array,
5913 end_object,
5914 name_separator,
5915 value_separator,
5916 parse_error,
5917 end_of_input,
5918 literal_or_value
5919 };
5920
5922 JSON_HEDLEY_RETURNS_NON_NULL
5923 JSON_HEDLEY_CONST
5924 static const char* token_type_name(const token_type t) noexcept
5925 {
5926 switch (t)
5927 {
5928 case token_type::uninitialized:
5929 return "<uninitialized>";
5930 case token_type::literal_true:
5931 return "true literal";
5932 case token_type::literal_false:
5933 return "false literal";
5934 case token_type::literal_null:
5935 return "null literal";
5936 case token_type::value_string:
5937 return "string literal";
5938 case token_type::value_unsigned:
5939 case token_type::value_integer:
5940 case token_type::value_float:
5941 return "number literal";
5942 case token_type::begin_array:
5943 return "'['";
5944 case token_type::begin_object:
5945 return "'{'";
5946 case token_type::end_array:
5947 return "']'";
5948 case token_type::end_object:
5949 return "'}'";
5950 case token_type::name_separator:
5951 return "':'";
5952 case token_type::value_separator:
5953 return "','";
5954 case token_type::parse_error:
5955 return "<parse error>";
5956 case token_type::end_of_input:
5957 return "end of input";
5958 case token_type::literal_or_value:
5959 return "'[', '{', or a literal";
5960 // LCOV_EXCL_START
5961 default: // catch non-enum values
5962 return "unknown token";
5963 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
5964 }
5965 }
5966 };
5972 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename InputAdapterType>
5973 class lexer : public lexer_base<BasicJsonType>
5974 {
5975 using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
5976 using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
5977 using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
5978 using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
5979 using char_type = typename InputAdapterType::char_type;
5980 using char_int_type = typename std::char_traits<char_type>::int_type;
5981
5982 public:
5983 using token_type = typename lexer_base<BasicJsonType>::token_type;
5984
5985 explicit lexer(InputAdapterType&& adapter, bool ignore_comments_ = false)
5986 : ia(std::move(adapter))
5987 , ignore_comments(ignore_comments_)
5988 , decimal_point_char(static_cast<char_int_type>(get_decimal_point()))
5989 {}
5990
5991 // delete because of pointer members
5992 lexer(const lexer&) = delete;
5993 lexer(lexer&&) = default;
5994 lexer& operator=(lexer&) = delete;
5995 lexer& operator=(lexer&&) = default;
5996 ~lexer() = default;
5997
5998 private:
6000 // locales
6002
6004 JSON_HEDLEY_PURE
6005 static char get_decimal_point() noexcept
6006 {
6007 const auto* loc = localeconv();
6008 JSON_ASSERT(loc != nullptr);
6009 return (loc->decimal_point == nullptr) ? '.' : *(loc->decimal_point);
6010 }
6011
6013 // scan functions
6015
6031 int get_codepoint()
6032 {
6033 // this function only makes sense after reading `\u`
6034 JSON_ASSERT(current == 'u');
6035 int codepoint = 0;
6036
6037 const auto factors = { 12u, 8u, 4u, 0u };
6038 for (const auto factor : factors)
6039 {
6040 get();
6041
6042 if (current >= '0' && current <= '9')
6043 {
6044 codepoint += static_cast<int>((static_cast<unsigned int>(current) - 0x30u) << factor);
6045 }
6046 else if (current >= 'A' && current <= 'F')
6047 {
6048 codepoint += static_cast<int>((static_cast<unsigned int>(current) - 0x37u) << factor);
6049 }
6050 else if (current >= 'a' && current <= 'f')
6051 {
6052 codepoint += static_cast<int>((static_cast<unsigned int>(current) - 0x57u) << factor);
6053 }
6054 else
6055 {
6056 return -1;
6057 }
6058 }
6059
6060 JSON_ASSERT(0x0000 <= codepoint && codepoint <= 0xFFFF);
6061 return codepoint;
6062 }
6063
6079 bool next_byte_in_range(std::initializer_list<char_int_type> ranges)
6080 {
6081 JSON_ASSERT(ranges.size() == 2 || ranges.size() == 4 || ranges.size() == 6);
6082 add(current);
6083
6084 for (auto range = ranges.begin(); range != ranges.end(); ++range)
6085 {
6086 get();
6087 if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(*range <= current && current <= *(++range)))
6088 {
6089 add(current);
6090 }
6091 else
6092 {
6093 error_message = "invalid string: ill-formed UTF-8 byte";
6094 return false;
6095 }
6096 }
6097
6098 return true;
6099 }
6100
6116 token_type scan_string()
6117 {
6118 // reset token_buffer (ignore opening quote)
6119 reset();
6120
6121 // we entered the function by reading an open quote
6122 JSON_ASSERT(current == '\"');
6123
6124 while (true)
6125 {
6126 // get next character
6127 switch (get())
6128 {
6129 // end of file while parsing string
6130 case std::char_traits<char_type>::eof():
6131 {
6132 error_message = "invalid string: missing closing quote";
6133 return token_type::parse_error;
6134 }
6135
6136 // closing quote
6137 case '\"':
6138 {
6139 return token_type::value_string;
6140 }
6141
6142 // escapes
6143 case '\\':
6144 {
6145 switch (get())
6146 {
6147 // quotation mark
6148 case '\"':
6149 add('\"');
6150 break;
6151 // reverse solidus
6152 case '\\':
6153 add('\\');
6154 break;
6155 // solidus
6156 case '/':
6157 add('/');
6158 break;
6159 // backspace
6160 case 'b':
6161 add('\b');
6162 break;
6163 // form feed
6164 case 'f':
6165 add('\f');
6166 break;
6167 // line feed
6168 case 'n':
6169 add('\n');
6170 break;
6171 // carriage return
6172 case 'r':
6173 add('\r');
6174 break;
6175 // tab
6176 case 't':
6177 add('\t');
6178 break;
6179
6180 // unicode escapes
6181 case 'u':
6182 {
6183 const int codepoint1 = get_codepoint();
6184 int codepoint = codepoint1; // start with codepoint1
6185
6186 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(codepoint1 == -1))
6187 {
6188 error_message = "invalid string: '\\u' must be followed by 4 hex digits";
6189 return token_type::parse_error;
6190 }
6191
6192 // check if code point is a high surrogate
6193 if (0xD800 <= codepoint1 && codepoint1 <= 0xDBFF)
6194 {
6195 // expect next \uxxxx entry
6196 if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(get() == '\\' && get() == 'u'))
6197 {
6198 const int codepoint2 = get_codepoint();
6199
6200 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(codepoint2 == -1))
6201 {
6202 error_message = "invalid string: '\\u' must be followed by 4 hex digits";
6203 return token_type::parse_error;
6204 }
6205
6206 // check if codepoint2 is a low surrogate
6207 if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(0xDC00 <= codepoint2 && codepoint2 <= 0xDFFF))
6208 {
6209 // overwrite codepoint
6210 codepoint = static_cast<int>(
6211 // high surrogate occupies the most significant 22 bits
6212 (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint1) << 10u)
6213 // low surrogate occupies the least significant 15 bits
6214 + static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint2)
6215 // there is still the 0xD800, 0xDC00 and 0x10000 noise
6216 // in the result so we have to subtract with:
6217 // (0xD800 << 10) + DC00 - 0x10000 = 0x35FDC00
6218 - 0x35FDC00u);
6219 }
6220 else
6221 {
6222 error_message = "invalid string: surrogate U+D800..U+DBFF must be followed by U+DC00..U+DFFF";
6223 return token_type::parse_error;
6224 }
6225 }
6226 else
6227 {
6228 error_message = "invalid string: surrogate U+D800..U+DBFF must be followed by U+DC00..U+DFFF";
6229 return token_type::parse_error;
6230 }
6231 }
6232 else
6233 {
6234 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(0xDC00 <= codepoint1 && codepoint1 <= 0xDFFF))
6235 {
6236 error_message = "invalid string: surrogate U+DC00..U+DFFF must follow U+D800..U+DBFF";
6237 return token_type::parse_error;
6238 }
6239 }
6240
6241 // result of the above calculation yields a proper codepoint
6242 JSON_ASSERT(0x00 <= codepoint && codepoint <= 0x10FFFF);
6243
6244 // translate codepoint into bytes
6245 if (codepoint < 0x80)
6246 {
6247 // 1-byte characters: 0xxxxxxx (ASCII)
6248 add(static_cast<char_int_type>(codepoint));
6249 }
6250 else if (codepoint <= 0x7FF)
6251 {
6252 // 2-byte characters: 110xxxxx 10xxxxxx
6253 add(static_cast<char_int_type>(0xC0u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) >> 6u)));
6254 add(static_cast<char_int_type>(0x80u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) & 0x3Fu)));
6255 }
6256 else if (codepoint <= 0xFFFF)
6257 {
6258 // 3-byte characters: 1110xxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx
6259 add(static_cast<char_int_type>(0xE0u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) >> 12u)));
6260 add(static_cast<char_int_type>(0x80u | ((static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) >> 6u) & 0x3Fu)));
6261 add(static_cast<char_int_type>(0x80u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) & 0x3Fu)));
6262 }
6263 else
6264 {
6265 // 4-byte characters: 11110xxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx
6266 add(static_cast<char_int_type>(0xF0u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) >> 18u)));
6267 add(static_cast<char_int_type>(0x80u | ((static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) >> 12u) & 0x3Fu)));
6268 add(static_cast<char_int_type>(0x80u | ((static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) >> 6u) & 0x3Fu)));
6269 add(static_cast<char_int_type>(0x80u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) & 0x3Fu)));
6270 }
6271
6272 break;
6273 }
6274
6275 // other characters after escape
6276 default:
6277 error_message = "invalid string: forbidden character after backslash";
6278 return token_type::parse_error;
6279 }
6280
6281 break;
6282 }
6283
6284 // invalid control characters
6285 case 0x00:
6286 {
6287 error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0000 (NUL) must be escaped to \\u0000";
6288 return token_type::parse_error;
6289 }
6290
6291 case 0x01:
6292 {
6293 error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0001 (SOH) must be escaped to \\u0001";
6294 return token_type::parse_error;
6295 }
6296
6297 case 0x02:
6298 {
6299 error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0002 (STX) must be escaped to \\u0002";
6300 return token_type::parse_error;
6301 }

6617 case 0xE0:

6620 {
6621 return token_type::parse_error;
6622 }
6623 break;
