6627 // U+E000..U+FFFF: bytes EE..EF 80..BF 80..BF
6628 case 0xE1:
6629 case 0xE2:
6630 case 0xE3:
6631 case 0xE4:
6632 case 0xE5:
6633 case 0xE6:
6634 case 0xE7:
6635 case 0xE8:
6636 case 0xE9:
6637 case 0xEA:
6638 case 0xEB:
6639 case 0xEC:
6640 case 0xEE:
6641 case 0xEF:
6642 {
6643 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!(next_byte_in_range({0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF}))))
6644 {
6645 return token_type::parse_error;
6646 }
6647 break;
6648 }
6649
6650 // U+D000..U+D7FF: bytes ED 80..9F 80..BF
6651 case 0xED:
6652 {
6653 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!(next_byte_in_range({0x80, 0x9F, 0x80, 0xBF}))))
6654 {
6655 return token_type::parse_error;
6656 }
6657 break;
6658 }
6659
6660 // U+10000..U+3FFFF F0 90..BF 80..BF 80..BF
6661 case 0xF0:
6662 {
6663 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!(next_byte_in_range({0x90, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF}))))
6664 {
6665 return token_type::parse_error;
6666 }
6667 break;
6668 }
6669
6670 // U+40000..U+FFFFF F1..F3 80..BF 80..BF 80..BF
6671 case 0xF1:
6672 case 0xF2:
6673 case 0xF3:
6674 {
6675 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!(next_byte_in_range({0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF}))))
6676 {
6677 return token_type::parse_error;
6678 }
6679 break;
6680 }
6681
6682 // U+100000..U+10FFFF F4 80..8F 80..BF 80..BF
6683 case 0xF4:
6684 {
6685 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!(next_byte_in_range({0x80, 0x8F, 0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF}))))
6686 {
6687 return token_type::parse_error;
6688 }
6689 break;
6690 }
6691
6692 // remaining bytes (80..C1 and F5..FF) are ill-formed
6693 default:
6694 {
6695 error_message = "invalid string: ill-formed UTF-8 byte";
6696 return token_type::parse_error;
6697 }
6698 }
6699 }
6700 }
6701
6706 bool scan_comment()
6707 {
6708 switch (get())
6709 {
6710 // single-line comments skip input until a newline or EOF is read
6711 case '/':
6712 {
6713 while (true)
6714 {
6715 switch (get())
6716 {
6717 case '\n':
6718 case '\r':
6719 case std::char_traits<char_type>::eof():
6720 case '\0':
6721 return true;
6722
6723 default:
6724 break;
6725 }
6726 }
6727 }
6728
6729 // multi-line comments skip input until */ is read
6730 case '*':
6731 {
6732 while (true)
6733 {
6734 switch (get())
6735 {
6736 case std::char_traits<char_type>::eof():
6737 case '\0':
6738 {
6739 error_message = "invalid comment; missing closing '*/'";
6740 return false;
6741 }
6742
6743 case '*':
6744 {
6745 switch (get())
6746 {
6747 case '/':
6748 return true;
6749
6750 default:
6751 {
6752 unget();
6753 continue;
6754 }
6755 }
6756 }
6757
6758 default:
6759 continue;
6760 }
6761 }
6762 }
6763
6764 // unexpected character after reading '/'
6765 default:
6766 {
6767 error_message = "invalid comment; expecting '/' or '*' after '/'";
6768 return false;
6769 }
6770 }
6771 }
6772
6773 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(2)
6774 static void strtof(float& f, const char* str, char** endptr) noexcept
6775 {
6776 f = std::strtof(str, endptr);
6777 }
6778
6779 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(2)
6780 static void strtof(double& f, const char* str, char** endptr) noexcept
6781 {
6782 f = std::strtod(str, endptr);
6783 }
6784
6785 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(2)
6786 static void strtof(long double& f, const char* str, char** endptr) noexcept
6787 {
6788 f = std::strtold(str, endptr);
6789 }
6790
6831 token_type scan_number() // lgtm [cpp/use-of-goto]
6832 {
6833 // reset token_buffer to store the number's bytes
6834 reset();
6835
6836 // the type of the parsed number; initially set to unsigned; will be
6837 // changed if minus sign, decimal point or exponent is read
6838 token_type number_type = token_type::value_unsigned;
6839
6840 // state (init): we just found out we need to scan a number
6841 switch (current)
6842 {
6843 case '-':
6844 {
6845 add(current);
6846 goto scan_number_minus;
6847 }
6848
6849 case '0':
6850 {
6851 add(current);
6852 goto scan_number_zero;
6853 }
6854
6855 case '1':
6856 case '2':
6857 case '3':
6858 case '4':
6859 case '5':
6860 case '6':
6861 case '7':
6862 case '8':
6863 case '9':
6864 {
6865 add(current);
6866 goto scan_number_any1;
6867 }
6868
6869 // all other characters are rejected outside scan_number()
6870 default: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
6871 JSON_ASSERT(false); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
6872 }
6873
6874scan_number_minus:
6875 // state: we just parsed a leading minus sign
6876 number_type = token_type::value_integer;
6877 switch (get())
6878 {
6879 case '0':
6880 {
6881 add(current);
6882 goto scan_number_zero;
6883 }
6884
6885 case '1':
6886 case '2':
6887 case '3':
6888 case '4':
6889 case '5':
6890 case '6':
6891 case '7':
6892 case '8':
6893 case '9':
6894 {
6895 add(current);
6896 goto scan_number_any1;
6897 }
6898
6899 default:
6900 {
6901 error_message = "invalid number; expected digit after '-'";
6902 return token_type::parse_error;
6903 }
6904 }
6905
6906scan_number_zero:
6907 // state: we just parse a zero (maybe with a leading minus sign)
6908 switch (get())
6909 {
6910 case '.':
6911 {
6912 add(decimal_point_char);
6913 goto scan_number_decimal1;
6914 }
6915
6916 case 'e':
6917 case 'E':
6918 {
6919 add(current);
6920 goto scan_number_exponent;
6921 }
6922
6923 default:
6924 goto scan_number_done;
6925 }
6926
6927scan_number_any1:
6928 // state: we just parsed a number 0-9 (maybe with a leading minus sign)
6929 switch (get())
6930 {
6931 case '0':
6932 case '1':
6933 case '2':
6934 case '3':
6935 case '4':
6936 case '5':
6937 case '6':
6938 case '7':
6939 case '8':
6940 case '9':
6941 {
6942 add(current);
6943 goto scan_number_any1;
6944 }
6945
6946 case '.':
6947 {
6948 add(decimal_point_char);
6949 goto scan_number_decimal1;
6950 }
6951
6952 case 'e':
6953 case 'E':
6954 {
6955 add(current);
6956 goto scan_number_exponent;
6957 }
6958
6959 default:
6960 goto scan_number_done;
6961 }
6962
6963scan_number_decimal1:
6964 // state: we just parsed a decimal point
6965 number_type = token_type::value_float;
6966 switch (get())
6967 {
6968 case '0':
6969 case '1':
6970 case '2':
6971 case '3':
6972 case '4':
6973 case '5':
6974 case '6':
6975 case '7':
6976 case '8':
6977 case '9':
6978 {
6979 add(current);
6980 goto scan_number_decimal2;
6981 }
6982
6983 default:
6984 {
6985 error_message = "invalid number; expected digit after '.'";
6986 return token_type::parse_error;
6987 }
6988 }
6989
6990scan_number_decimal2:
6991 // we just parsed at least one number after a decimal point
6992 switch (get())
6993 {
6994 case '0':
6995 case '1':
6996 case '2':
6997 case '3':
6998 case '4':
6999 case '5':
7000 case '6':
7001 case '7':
7002 case '8':
7003 case '9':
7004 {
7005 add(current);
7006 goto scan_number_decimal2;
7007 }
7008
7009 case 'e':
7010 case 'E':
7011 {
7012 add(current);
7013 goto scan_number_exponent;
7014 }
7015
7016 default:
7017 goto scan_number_done;
7018 }
7019
7020scan_number_exponent:
7021 // we just parsed an exponent
7022 number_type = token_type::value_float;
7023 switch (get())
7024 {
7025 case '+':
7026 case '-':
7027 {
7028 add(current);
7029 goto scan_number_sign;
7030 }
7031
7032 case '0':
7033 case '1':
7034 case '2':
7035 case '3':
7036 case '4':
7037 case '5':
7038 case '6':
7039 case '7':
7040 case '8':
7041 case '9':
7042 {
7043 add(current);
7044 goto scan_number_any2;
7045 }
7046
7047 default:
7048 {
7049 error_message =
7050 "invalid number; expected '+', '-', or digit after exponent";
7051 return token_type::parse_error;
7052 }
7053 }
7054
7055scan_number_sign:
7056 // we just parsed an exponent sign
7057 switch (get())
7058 {
7059 case '0':
7060 case '1':
7061 case '2':
7062 case '3':
7063 case '4':
7064 case '5':
7065 case '6':
7066 case '7':
7067 case '8':
7068 case '9':
7069 {
7070 add(current);
7071 goto scan_number_any2;
7072 }
7073
7074 default:
7075 {
7076 error_message = "invalid number; expected digit after exponent sign";
7077 return token_type::parse_error;
7078 }
7079 }
7080
7081scan_number_any2:
7082 // we just parsed a number after the exponent or exponent sign
7083 switch (get())
7084 {
7085 case '0':
7086 case '1':
7087 case '2':
7088 case '3':
7089 case '4':
7090 case '5':
7091 case '6':
7092 case '7':
7093 case '8':
7094 case '9':
7095 {
7096 add(current);
7097 goto scan_number_any2;
7098 }
7099
7100 default:
7101 goto scan_number_done;
7102 }
7103
7104scan_number_done:
7105 // unget the character after the number (we only read it to know that
7106 // we are done scanning a number)
7107 unget();
7108
7109 char* endptr = nullptr;
7110 errno = 0;
7111
7112 // try to parse integers first and fall back to floats
7113 if (number_type == token_type::value_unsigned)
7114 {
7115 const auto x = std::strtoull(token_buffer.data(), &endptr, 10);
7116
7117 // we checked the number format before
7118 JSON_ASSERT(endptr == token_buffer.data() + token_buffer.size());
7119
7120 if (errno == 0)
7121 {
7122 value_unsigned = static_cast<number_unsigned_t>(x);
7123 if (value_unsigned == x)
7124 {
7125 return token_type::value_unsigned;
7126 }
7127 }
7128 }
7129 else if (number_type == token_type::value_integer)
7130 {
7131 const auto x = std::strtoll(token_buffer.data(), &endptr, 10);
7132
7133 // we checked the number format before
7134 JSON_ASSERT(endptr == token_buffer.data() + token_buffer.size());
7135
7136 if (errno == 0)
7137 {
7138 value_integer = static_cast<number_integer_t>(x);
7139 if (value_integer == x)
7140 {
7141 return token_type::value_integer;
7142 }
7143 }
7144 }
7145
7146 // this code is reached if we parse a floating-point number or if an
7147 // integer conversion above failed
7148 strtof(value_float, token_buffer.data(), &endptr);
7149
7150 // we checked the number format before
7151 JSON_ASSERT(endptr == token_buffer.data() + token_buffer.size());
7152
7153 return token_type::value_float;
7154 }
7155
7161 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(2)
7162 token_type scan_literal(const char_type* literal_text, const std::size_t length,
7163 token_type return_type)
7164 {
7165 JSON_ASSERT(std::char_traits<char_type>::to_char_type(current) == literal_text[0]);
7166 for (std::size_t i = 1; i < length; ++i)
7167 {
7168 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(std::char_traits<char_type>::to_char_type(get()) != literal_text[i]))
7169 {
7170 error_message = "invalid literal";
7171 return token_type::parse_error;
7172 }
7173 }
7174 return return_type;
7175 }
7176
7178 // input management
7180
7182 void reset() noexcept
7183 {
7184 token_buffer.clear();
7185 token_string.clear();
7186 token_string.push_back(std::char_traits<char_type>::to_char_type(current));
7187 }
7188
7189 /*
7190 @brief get next character from the input
7191
7192 This function provides the interface to the used input adapter. It does
7193 not throw in case the input reached EOF, but returns a
7194 `std::char_traits<char>::eof()` in that case. Stores the scanned characters
7195 for use in error messages.
7196
7197 @return character read from the input
7198 */
7199 char_int_type get()
7200 {
7201 ++position.chars_read_total;
7202 ++position.chars_read_current_line;
7203
7204 if (next_unget)
7205 {
7206 // just reset the next_unget variable and work with current
7207 next_unget = false;
7208 }
7209 else
7210 {
7211 current = ia.get_character();
7212 }
7213
7214 if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(current != std::char_traits<char_type>::eof()))
7215 {
7216 token_string.push_back(std::char_traits<char_type>::to_char_type(current));
7217 }
7218
7219 if (current == '\n')
7220 {
7221 ++position.lines_read;
7222 position.chars_read_current_line = 0;
7223 }
7224
7225 return current;
7226 }
7227
7236 void unget()
7237 {
7238 next_unget = true;
7239
7240 --position.chars_read_total;
7241
7242 // in case we "unget" a newline, we have to also decrement the lines_read
7243 if (position.chars_read_current_line == 0)
7244 {
7245 if (position.lines_read > 0)
7246 {
7247 --position.lines_read;
7248 }
7249 }
7250 else
7251 {
7252 --position.chars_read_current_line;
7253 }
7254
7255 if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(current != std::char_traits<char_type>::eof()))
7256 {
7257 JSON_ASSERT(!token_string.empty());
7258 token_string.pop_back();
7259 }
7260 }
7261
7263 void add(char_int_type c)
7264 {
7265 token_buffer.push_back(static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(c));
7266 }
7267
7268 public:
7270 // value getters
7272
7274 constexpr number_integer_t get_number_integer() const noexcept
7275 {
7276 return value_integer;
7277 }
7278
7280 constexpr number_unsigned_t get_number_unsigned() const noexcept
7281 {
7282 return value_unsigned;
7283 }
7284
7286 constexpr number_float_t get_number_float() const noexcept
7287 {
7288 return value_float;
7289 }
7290
7292 string_t& get_string()
7293 {
7294 return token_buffer;
7295 }
7296
7298 // diagnostics
7300
7302 constexpr position_t get_position() const noexcept
7303 {
7304 return position;
7305 }
7306
7310 std::string get_token_string() const
7311 {
7312 // escape control characters
7313 std::string result;
7314 for (const auto c : token_string)
7315 {
7316 if (static_cast<unsigned char>(c) <= '\x1F')
7317 {
7318 // escape control characters
7319 std::array<char, 9> cs{{}};
7320 #if (defined (_WIN32) || defined (_WIN64))
7321 (snprintf)(cs.data(), cs.size(), "<U+%.4X>", static_cast<unsigned char>(c));
7322 #else
7323 (std::snprintf)(cs.data(), cs.size(), "<U+%.4X>", static_cast<unsigned char>(c));
7324 #endif
7325 result += cs.data();
7326 }
7327 else
7328 {
7329 // add character as is
7330 result.push_back(static_cast<std::string::value_type>(c));
7331 }
7332 }
7333
7334 return result;
7335 }
7336
7338 JSON_HEDLEY_RETURNS_NON_NULL
7339 constexpr const char* get_error_message() const noexcept
7340 {
7341 return error_message;
7342 }
7343
7345 // actual scanner
7347
7352 bool skip_bom()
7353 {
7354 if (get() == 0xEF)
7355 {
7356 // check if we completely parse the BOM
7357 return get() == 0xBB && get() == 0xBF;
7358 }
7359
7360 // the first character is not the beginning of the BOM; unget it to
7361 // process is later
7362 unget();
7363 return true;
7364 }
7365
7366 void skip_whitespace()
7367 {
7368 do
7369 {
7370 get();
7371 }
7372 while (current == ' ' || current == '\t' || current == '\n' || current == '\r');
7373 }
7374
7375 token_type scan()
7376 {
7377 // initially, skip the BOM
7378 if (position.chars_read_total == 0 && !skip_bom())
7379 {
7380 error_message = "invalid BOM; must be 0xEF 0xBB 0xBF if given";
7381 return token_type::parse_error;
7382 }
7383
7384 // read next character and ignore whitespace
7385 skip_whitespace();
7386
7387 // ignore comments
7388 while (ignore_comments && current == '/')
7389 {
7390 if (!scan_comment())
7391 {
7392 return token_type::parse_error;
7393 }
7394
7395 // skip following whitespace
7396 skip_whitespace();
7397 }
7398
7399 switch (current)
7400 {
7401 // structural characters
7402 case '[':
7403 return token_type::begin_array;
7404 case ']':
7405 return token_type::end_array;
7406 case '{':
7407 return token_type::begin_object;
7408 case '}':
7409 return token_type::end_object;
7410 case ':':
7411 return token_type::name_separator;
7412 case ',':
7413 return token_type::value_separator;
7414
7415 // literals
7416 case 't':
7417 {
7418 std::array<char_type, 4> true_literal = {{'t', 'r', 'u', 'e'}};
7419 return scan_literal(true_literal.data(), true_literal.size(), token_type::literal_true);
7420 }
7421 case 'f':
7422 {
7423 std::array<char_type, 5> false_literal = {{'f', 'a', 'l', 's', 'e'}};
7424 return scan_literal(false_literal.data(), false_literal.size(), token_type::literal_false);
7425 }
7426 case 'n':
7427 {
7428 std::array<char_type, 4> null_literal = {{'n', 'u', 'l', 'l'}};
7429 return scan_literal(null_literal.data(), null_literal.size(), token_type::literal_null);
7430 }
7431
7432 // string
7433 case '\"':
7434 return scan_string();
7435
7436 // number
7437 case '-':
7438 case '0':
7439 case '1':
7440 case '2':
7441 case '3':
7442 case '4':
7443 case '5':
7444 case '6':
7445 case '7':
7446 case '8':
7447 case '9':
7448 return scan_number();
7449
7450 // end of input (the null byte is needed when parsing from
7451 // string literals)
7452 case '\0':
7453 case std::char_traits<char_type>::eof():
7454 return token_type::end_of_input;
7455
7456 // error
7457 default:
7458 error_message = "invalid literal";
7459 return token_type::parse_error;
7460 }
7461 }
7462
7463 private:
7465 InputAdapterType ia;
7466
7468 const bool ignore_comments = false;
7469
7471 char_int_type current = std::char_traits<char_type>::eof();
7472
7474 bool next_unget = false;
7475
7477 position_t position {};
7478
7480 std::vector<char_type> token_string {};
7481
7483 string_t token_buffer {};
7484
7486 const char* error_message = "";
7487
7488 // number values
7489 number_integer_t value_integer = 0;
7490 number_unsigned_t value_unsigned = 0;
7491 number_float_t value_float = 0;
7492
7494 const char_int_type decimal_point_char = '.';
7495 };
7496 } // namespace detail
7497} // namespace nlohmann

7517 template<typename T>
7518 using null_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().null());
7519
7520 template<typename T>
7521 using boolean_function_t =
7522 decltype(std::declval<T&>().boolean(std::declval<bool>()));
7523
7524 template<typename T, typename Integer>
7525 using number_integer_function_t =
7526 decltype(std::declval<T&>().number_integer(std::declval<Integer>()));
7527
7528 template<typename T, typename Unsigned>
7529 using number_unsigned_function_t =
7530 decltype(std::declval<T&>().number_unsigned(std::declval<Unsigned>()));
7531
7532 template<typename T, typename Float, typename String>
7533 using number_float_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().number_float(
7534 std::declval<Float>(), std::declval<const String&>()));
7535
7536 template<typename T, typename String>
7537 using string_function_t =
7538 decltype(std::declval<T&>().string(std::declval<String&>()));
7539
7540 template<typename T, typename Binary>
7541 using binary_function_t =
7542 decltype(std::declval<T&>().binary(std::declval<Binary&>()));
7543
7544 template<typename T>
7545 using start_object_function_t =
7546 decltype(std::declval<T&>().start_object(std::declval<std::size_t>()));
7547
7548 template<typename T, typename String>
7549 using key_function_t =
7550 decltype(std::declval<T&>().key(std::declval<String&>()));
7551
7552 template<typename T>
7553 using end_object_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().end_object());
7554
7555 template<typename T>
7556 using start_array_function_t =
7557 decltype(std::declval<T&>().start_array(std::declval<std::size_t>()));
7558
7559 template<typename T>
7560 using end_array_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().end_array());
7561
7562 template<typename T, typename Exception>
7563 using parse_error_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().parse_error(
7564 std::declval<std::size_t>(), std::declval<const std::string&>(),
7565 std::declval<const Exception&>()));
7566
7567 template<typename SAX, typename BasicJsonType>
7568 struct is_sax
7569 {
7570 private:
7571 static_assert(is_basic_json<BasicJsonType>::value,
7572 "BasicJsonType must be of type basic_json<...>");
7573
7574 using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
7575 using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
7576 using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
7577 using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
7578 using binary_t = typename BasicJsonType::binary_t;
7579 using exception_t = typename BasicJsonType::exception;
7580
7581 public:
7582 static constexpr bool value =
7583 is_detected_exact<bool, null_function_t, SAX>::value &&
7584 is_detected_exact<bool, boolean_function_t, SAX>::value &&
7585 is_detected_exact<bool, number_integer_function_t, SAX, number_integer_t>::value &&
7586 is_detected_exact<bool, number_unsigned_function_t, SAX, number_unsigned_t>::value &&
7587 is_detected_exact<bool, number_float_function_t, SAX, number_float_t, string_t>::value &&
7588 is_detected_exact<bool, string_function_t, SAX, string_t>::value &&
7589 is_detected_exact<bool, binary_function_t, SAX, binary_t>::value &&
7590 is_detected_exact<bool, start_object_function_t, SAX>::value &&
7591 is_detected_exact<bool, key_function_t, SAX, string_t>::value &&
7592 is_detected_exact<bool, end_object_function_t, SAX>::value &&
7593 is_detected_exact<bool, start_array_function_t, SAX>::value &&
7594 is_detected_exact<bool, end_array_function_t, SAX>::value &&
7595 is_detected_exact<bool, parse_error_function_t, SAX, exception_t>::value;
7596 };
7597
7598 template<typename SAX, typename BasicJsonType>
7599 struct is_sax_static_asserts
7600 {
7601 private:
7602 static_assert(is_basic_json<BasicJsonType>::value,
7603 "BasicJsonType must be of type basic_json<...>");
7604
7605 using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
7606 using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
7607 using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
7608 using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
7609 using binary_t = typename BasicJsonType::binary_t;
7610 using exception_t = typename BasicJsonType::exception;
7611
7612 public:
7613 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, null_function_t, SAX>::value,
7614 "Missing/invalid function: bool null()");
7615 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, boolean_function_t, SAX>::value,
7616 "Missing/invalid function: bool boolean(bool)");
7617 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, boolean_function_t, SAX>::value,
7618 "Missing/invalid function: bool boolean(bool)");
7619 static_assert(
7620 is_detected_exact<bool, number_integer_function_t, SAX,
7621 number_integer_t>::value,
7622 "Missing/invalid function: bool number_integer(number_integer_t)");
7623 static_assert(
7624 is_detected_exact<bool, number_unsigned_function_t, SAX,
7625 number_unsigned_t>::value,
7626 "Missing/invalid function: bool number_unsigned(number_unsigned_t)");
7627 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, number_float_function_t, SAX,
7628 number_float_t, string_t>::value,
7629 "Missing/invalid function: bool number_float(number_float_t, const string_t&)");
7630 static_assert(
7631 is_detected_exact<bool, string_function_t, SAX, string_t>::value,
7632 "Missing/invalid function: bool string(string_t&)");
7633 static_assert(
7634 is_detected_exact<bool, binary_function_t, SAX, binary_t>::value,
7635 "Missing/invalid function: bool binary(binary_t&)");
7636 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, start_object_function_t, SAX>::value,
7637 "Missing/invalid function: bool start_object(std::size_t)");
7638 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, key_function_t, SAX, string_t>::value,
7639 "Missing/invalid function: bool key(string_t&)");
7640 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, end_object_function_t, SAX>::value,
7641 "Missing/invalid function: bool end_object()");
7642 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, start_array_function_t, SAX>::value,
7643 "Missing/invalid function: bool start_array(std::size_t)");
7644 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, end_array_function_t, SAX>::value,
7645 "Missing/invalid function: bool end_array()");
7646 static_assert(
7647 is_detected_exact<bool, parse_error_function_t, SAX, exception_t>::value,
7648 "Missing/invalid function: bool parse_error(std::size_t, const "
7649 "std::string&, const exception&)");
7650 };
7651 } // namespace detail
7652} // namespace nlohmann

7663 enum class cbor_tag_handler_t
7664 {
7665 error,
7666 ignore
7667 };

7676 static inline bool little_endianess(int num = 1) noexcept
7677 {
7678 return *reinterpret_cast<char*>(&num) == 1;
7679 }

7683 // binary reader //
7685
7689 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename InputAdapterType, typename SAX = json_sax_dom_parser<BasicJsonType>>
7690 class binary_reader
7691 {
7692 using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
7693 using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
7694 using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
7695 using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
7696 using binary_t = typename BasicJsonType::binary_t;
7697 using json_sax_t = SAX;
7698 using char_type = typename InputAdapterType::char_type;
7699 using char_int_type = typename std::char_traits<char_type>::int_type;
7700
7701 public:
7707 explicit binary_reader(InputAdapterType&& adapter) : ia(std::move(adapter))
7708 {
7709 (void)detail::is_sax_static_asserts<SAX, BasicJsonType> {};
7710 }
7711
7712 // make class move-only
7713 binary_reader(const binary_reader&) = delete;
7714 binary_reader(binary_reader&&) = default;
7715 binary_reader& operator=(const binary_reader&) = delete;
7716 binary_reader& operator=(binary_reader&&) = default;
7717 ~binary_reader() = default;
7718
7727 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(3)
7728 bool sax_parse(const input_format_t format,
7729 json_sax_t* sax_,
7730 const bool strict = true,
7731 const cbor_tag_handler_t tag_handler = cbor_tag_handler_t::error)
7732 {
7733 sax = sax_;
7734 bool result = false;
7735
7736 switch (format)
7737 {
7738 case input_format_t::bson:
7739 result = parse_bson_internal();
7740 break;
7741
7742 case input_format_t::cbor:
7743 result = parse_cbor_internal(true, tag_handler);
7744 break;
7745
7746 case input_format_t::msgpack:
7747 result = parse_msgpack_internal();
7748 break;
7749
7750 case input_format_t::ubjson:
7751 result = parse_ubjson_internal();
7752 break;
7753
7754 default: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
7755 JSON_ASSERT(false); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
7756 }
7757
7758 // strict mode: next byte must be EOF
7759 if (result && strict)
7760 {
7761 if (format == input_format_t::ubjson)
7762 {
7763 get_ignore_noop();
7764 }
7765 else
7766 {
7767 get();
7768 }
7769
7770 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(current != std::char_traits<char_type>::eof()))
7771 {
7772 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, get_token_string(),
7773 parse_error::create(110, chars_read, exception_message(format, "expected end of input; last byte: 0x" + get_token_string(), "value")));
7774 }
7775 }
7776
7777 return result;
7778 }
7779
7780 private:
7782 // BSON //
7784
7789 bool parse_bson_internal()
7790 {
7791 std::int32_t document_size{};
7792 get_number<std::int32_t, true>(input_format_t::bson, document_size);
7793
7794 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->start_object(std::size_t(-1))))
7795 {
7796 return false;
7797 }
7798
7799 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!parse_bson_element_list(/*is_array*/false)))
7800 {
7801 return false;
7802 }
7803
7804 return sax->end_object();
7805 }
7806
7814 bool get_bson_cstr(string_t& result)
7815 {
7816 auto out = std::back_inserter(result);
7817 while (true)
7818 {
7819 get();
7820 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(input_format_t::bson, "cstring")))
7821 {
7822 return false;
7823 }
7824 if (current == 0x00)
7825 {
7826 return true;
7827 }
7828 *out++ = static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(current);
7829 }
7830 }
7831
7843 template<typename NumberType>
7844 bool get_bson_string(const NumberType len, string_t& result)
7845 {
7846 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(len < 1))
7847 {
7848 auto last_token = get_token_string();
7849 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(112, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::bson, "string length must be at least 1, is " + std::to_string(len), "string")));
7850 }
7851
7852 return get_string(input_format_t::bson, len - static_cast<NumberType>(1), result) && get() != std::char_traits<char_type>::eof();
7853 }
7854
7864 template<typename NumberType>
7865 bool get_bson_binary(const NumberType len, binary_t& result)
7866 {
7867 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(len < 0))
7868 {
7869 auto last_token = get_token_string();
7870 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(112, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::bson, "byte array length cannot be negative, is " + std::to_string(len), "binary")));
7871 }
7872
7873 // All BSON binary values have a subtype
7874 std::uint8_t subtype{};
7875 get_number<std::uint8_t>(input_format_t::bson, subtype);
7876 result.set_subtype(subtype);
7877
7878 return get_binary(input_format_t::bson, len, result);
7879 }
7880
7891 bool parse_bson_element_internal(const char_int_type element_type,
7892 const std::size_t element_type_parse_position)
7893 {
7894 switch (element_type)
7895 {
7896 case 0x01: // double
7897 {
7898 double number{};
7899 return get_number<double, true>(input_format_t::bson, number) && sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
7900 }
7901
7902 case 0x02: // string
7903 {
7904 std::int32_t len{};
7905 string_t value;
7906 return get_number<std::int32_t, true>(input_format_t::bson, len) && get_bson_string(len, value) && sax->string(value);
7907 }
7908
7909 case 0x03: // object
7910 {
7911 return parse_bson_internal();
7912 }
7913
7914 case 0x04: // array
7915 {
7916 return parse_bson_array();
7917 }
7918
7919 case 0x05: // binary
7920 {
7921 std::int32_t len{};
7922 binary_t value;
7923 return get_number<std::int32_t, true>(input_format_t::bson, len) && get_bson_binary(len, value) && sax->binary(value);
7924 }
7925
7926 case 0x08: // boolean
7927 {
7928 return sax->boolean(get() != 0);
7929 }
7930
7931 case 0x0A: // null
7932 {
7933 return sax->null();
7934 }
7935
7936 case 0x10: // int32
7937 {
7938 std::int32_t value{};
7939 return get_number<std::int32_t, true>(input_format_t::bson, value) && sax->number_integer(value);
7940 }
7941
7942 case 0x12: // int64
7943 {
7944 std::int64_t value{};
7945 return get_number<std::int64_t, true>(input_format_t::bson, value) && sax->number_integer(value);
7946 }
7947
7948 default: // anything else not supported (yet)
7949 {
7950 std::array<char, 3> cr{{}};
7951 (std::snprintf)(cr.data(), cr.size(), "%.2hhX", static_cast<unsigned char>(element_type));
7952 return sax->parse_error(element_type_parse_position, std::string(cr.data()), parse_error::create(114, element_type_parse_position, "Unsupported BSON record type 0x" + std::string(cr.data())));
7953 }
7954 }
7955 }
7956
7969 bool parse_bson_element_list(const bool is_array)
7970 {
7971 string_t key;
7972
7973 while (auto element_type = get())
7974 {
7975 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(input_format_t::bson, "element list")))
7976 {
7977 return false;
7978 }
7979
7980 const std::size_t element_type_parse_position = chars_read;
7981 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_bson_cstr(key)))
7982 {
7983 return false;
7984 }
7985
7986 if (!is_array && !sax->key(key))
7987 {
7988 return false;
7989 }
7990
7991 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!parse_bson_element_internal(element_type, element_type_parse_position)))
7992 {
7993 return false;
7994 }
7995
7996 // get_bson_cstr only appends
7997 key.clear();
7998 }
7999
8000 return true;
8001 }
8002
8007 bool parse_bson_array()
8008 {
8009 std::int32_t document_size{};
8010 get_number<std::int32_t, true>(input_format_t::bson, document_size);
8011
8012 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->start_array(std::size_t(-1))))
8013 {
8014 return false;
8015 }
8016
8017 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!parse_bson_element_list(/*is_array*/true)))
8018 {
8019 return false;
8020 }
8021
8022 return sax->end_array();
8023 }
8024
8026 // CBOR //
8028
8037 bool parse_cbor_internal(const bool get_char,
8038 const cbor_tag_handler_t tag_handler)
8039 {
8040 switch (get_char ? get() : current)
8041 {
8042 // EOF
8043 case std::char_traits<char_type>::eof():
8044 return unexpect_eof(input_format_t::cbor, "value");
8045
8046 // Integer 0x00..0x17 (0..23)
8047 case 0x00:
8048 case 0x01:
8049 case 0x02:
8050 case 0x03:
8051 case 0x04:
8052 case 0x05:
8053 case 0x06:
8054 case 0x07:
8055 case 0x08:
8056 case 0x09:
8057 case 0x0A:
8058 case 0x0B:
8059 case 0x0C:
8060 case 0x0D:
8061 case 0x0E:
8062 case 0x0F:
8063 case 0x10:
8064 case 0x11:
8065 case 0x12:
8066 case 0x13:
8067 case 0x14:
8068 case 0x15:
8069 case 0x16:
8070 case 0x17:
8071 return sax->number_unsigned(static_cast<number_unsigned_t>(current));
8072
8073 case 0x18: // Unsigned integer (one-byte uint8_t follows)
8074 {
8075 std::uint8_t number{};
8076 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) && sax->number_unsigned(number);
8077 }
8078
8079 case 0x19: // Unsigned integer (two-byte uint16_t follows)
8080 {
8081 std::uint16_t number{};
8082 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) && sax->number_unsigned(number);
8083 }
8084
8085 case 0x1A: // Unsigned integer (four-byte uint32_t follows)
8086 {
8087 std::uint32_t number{};
8088 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) && sax->number_unsigned(number);
8089 }
8090
8091 case 0x1B: // Unsigned integer (eight-byte uint64_t follows)
8092 {
8093 std::uint64_t number{};
8094 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) && sax->number_unsigned(number);
8095 }
8096
8097 // Negative integer -1-0x00..-1-0x17 (-1..-24)
8098 case 0x20:
8099 case 0x21:
8100 case 0x22:
8101 case 0x23:
8102 case 0x24:
8103 case 0x25:
8104 case 0x26:
8105 case 0x27:
8106 case 0x28:
8107 case 0x29:
8108 case 0x2A:
8109 case 0x2B:
8110 case 0x2C:
8111 case 0x2D:
8112 case 0x2E:
8113 case 0x2F:
8114 case 0x30:
8115 case 0x31:
8116 case 0x32:
8117 case 0x33:
8118 case 0x34:
8119 case 0x35:
8120 case 0x36:
8121 case 0x37:
8122 return sax->number_integer(static_cast<std::int8_t>(0x20 - 1 - current));
8123
8124 case 0x38: // Negative integer (one-byte uint8_t follows)
8125 {
8126 std::uint8_t number{};
8127 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) && sax->number_integer(static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - number);
8128 }
8129
8130 case 0x39: // Negative integer -1-n (two-byte uint16_t follows)
8131 {
8132 std::uint16_t number{};
8133 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) && sax->number_integer(static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - number);
8134 }
8135
8136 case 0x3A: // Negative integer -1-n (four-byte uint32_t follows)
8137 {
8138 std::uint32_t number{};
8139 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) && sax->number_integer(static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - number);
8140 }
8141
8142 case 0x3B: // Negative integer -1-n (eight-byte uint64_t follows)
8143 {
8144 std::uint64_t number{};
8145 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) && sax->number_integer(static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1)
8146 - static_cast<number_integer_t>(number));
8147 }
8148
8149 // Binary data (0x00..0x17 bytes follow)
8150 case 0x40:
8151 case 0x41:
8152 case 0x42:
8153 case 0x43:
8154 case 0x44:
8155 case 0x45:
8156 case 0x46:
8157 case 0x47:
8158 case 0x48:
8159 case 0x49:
8160 case 0x4A:
8161 case 0x4B:
8162 case 0x4C:
8163 case 0x4D:
8164 case 0x4E:
8165 case 0x4F:
8166 case 0x50:
8167 case 0x51:
8168 case 0x52:
8169 case 0x53:
8170 case 0x54:
8171 case 0x55:
8172 case 0x56:
8173 case 0x57:
8174 case 0x58: // Binary data (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
8175 case 0x59: // Binary data (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
8176 case 0x5A: // Binary data (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
8177 case 0x5B: // Binary data (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
8178 case 0x5F: // Binary data (indefinite length)
8179 {
8180 binary_t b;
8181 return get_cbor_binary(b) && sax->binary(b);
8182 }
8183
8184 // UTF-8 string (0x00..0x17 bytes follow)
8185 case 0x60:
8186 case 0x61:
8187 case 0x62:
8188 case 0x63:
8189 case 0x64:
8190 case 0x65:
8191 case 0x66:
8192 case 0x67:
8193 case 0x68:
8194 case 0x69:
8195 case 0x6A:
8196 case 0x6B:
8197 case 0x6C:
8198 case 0x6D:
8199 case 0x6E:
8200 case 0x6F:
8201 case 0x70:
8202 case 0x71:
8203 case 0x72:
8204 case 0x73:
8205 case 0x74:
8206 case 0x75:
8207 case 0x76:
8208 case 0x77:
8209 case 0x78: // UTF-8 string (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
8210 case 0x79: // UTF-8 string (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
8211 case 0x7A: // UTF-8 string (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
8212 case 0x7B: // UTF-8 string (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
8213 case 0x7F: // UTF-8 string (indefinite length)
8214 {
8215 string_t s;
8216 return get_cbor_string(s) && sax->string(s);
8217 }
8218
8219 // array (0x00..0x17 data items follow)
8220 case 0x80:
8221 case 0x81:
8222 case 0x82:
8223 case 0x83:
8224 case 0x84:
8225 case 0x85:
8226 case 0x86:
8227 case 0x87:
8228 case 0x88:
8229 case 0x89:
8230 case 0x8A:
8231 case 0x8B:
8232 case 0x8C:
8233 case 0x8D:
8234 case 0x8E:
8235 case 0x8F:
8236 case 0x90:
8237 case 0x91:
8238 case 0x92:
8239 case 0x93:
8240 case 0x94:
8241 case 0x95:
8242 case 0x96:
8243 case 0x97:
8244 return get_cbor_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(static_cast<unsigned int>(current) & 0x1Fu), tag_handler);
8245
8246 case 0x98: // array (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
8247 {
8248 std::uint8_t len{};
8249 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) && get_cbor_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(len), tag_handler);
8250 }
8251
8252 case 0x99: // array (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
8253 {
8254 std::uint16_t len{};
8255 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) && get_cbor_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(len), tag_handler);
8256 }
8257
8258 case 0x9A: // array (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
8259 {
8260 std::uint32_t len{};
8261 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) && get_cbor_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(len), tag_handler);
8262 }
8263
8264 case 0x9B: // array (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
8265 {
8266 std::uint64_t len{};
8267 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) && get_cbor_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(len), tag_handler);
8268 }
8269
8270 case 0x9F: // array (indefinite length)
8271 return get_cbor_array(std::size_t(-1), tag_handler);
8272
8273 // map (0x00..0x17 pairs of data items follow)
8274 case 0xA0:
8275 case 0xA1:
8276 case 0xA2:
8277 case 0xA3:
8278 case 0xA4:
8279 case 0xA5:
8280 case 0xA6:
8281 case 0xA7:
8282 case 0xA8:
8283 case 0xA9:
8284 case 0xAA:
8285 case 0xAB:
8286 case 0xAC:
8287 case 0xAD:
8288 case 0xAE:
8289 case 0xAF:
8290 case 0xB0:
8291 case 0xB1:
8292 case 0xB2:
8293 case 0xB3:
8294 case 0xB4:
8295 case 0xB5:
8296 case 0xB6:
8297 case 0xB7:
8298 return get_cbor_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(static_cast<unsigned int>(current) & 0x1Fu), tag_handler);
8299
8300 case 0xB8: // map (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
8301 {
8302 std::uint8_t len{};
8303 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) && get_cbor_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(len), tag_handler);
8304 }
8305
8306 case 0xB9: // map (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
8307 {
8308 std::uint16_t len{};
8309 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) && get_cbor_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(len), tag_handler);
8310 }
8311
8312 case 0xBA: // map (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
8313 {
8314 std::uint32_t len{};
8315 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) && get_cbor_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(len), tag_handler);
8316 }
8317
8318 case 0xBB: // map (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
8319 {
8320 std::uint64_t len{};
8321 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) && get_cbor_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(len), tag_handler);
8322 }
8323
8324 case 0xBF: // map (indefinite length)
8325 return get_cbor_object(std::size_t(-1), tag_handler);
8326
8327 case 0xC6: // tagged item
8328 case 0xC7:
8329 case 0xC8:
8330 case 0xC9:
8331 case 0xCA:
8332 case 0xCB:
8333 case 0xCC:
8334 case 0xCD:
8335 case 0xCE:
8336 case 0xCF:
8337 case 0xD0:
8338 case 0xD1:
8339 case 0xD2:
8340 case 0xD3:
8341 case 0xD4:
8342 case 0xD8: // tagged item (1 bytes follow)
8343 case 0xD9: // tagged item (2 bytes follow)
8344 case 0xDA: // tagged item (4 bytes follow)
8345 case 0xDB: // tagged item (8 bytes follow)
8346 {
8347 switch (tag_handler)
8348 {
8349 case cbor_tag_handler_t::error:
8350 {
8351 auto last_token = get_token_string();
8352 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(112, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::cbor, "invalid byte: 0x" + last_token, "value")));
8353 }
8354
8355 case cbor_tag_handler_t::ignore:
8356 {
8357 switch (current)
8358 {
8359 case 0xD8:
8360 {
8361 std::uint8_t len{};
8362 get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len);
8363 break;
8364 }
8365 case 0xD9:
8366 {
8367 std::uint16_t len{};
8368 get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len);
8369 break;
8370 }
8371 case 0xDA:
8372 {
8373 std::uint32_t len{};
8374 get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len);
8375 break;
8376 }
8377 case 0xDB:
8378 {
8379 std::uint64_t len{};
8380 get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len);
8381 break;
8382 }
8383 default:
8384 break;
8385 }
8386 return parse_cbor_internal(true, tag_handler);
8387 }
8388
8389 default: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
8390 JSON_ASSERT(false); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
8391 }
8392 }
8393
8394 case 0xF4: // false
8395 return sax->boolean(false);
8396
8397 case 0xF5: // true
8398 return sax->boolean(true);
8399
8400 case 0xF6: // null
8401 return sax->null();
8402
8403 case 0xF9: // Half-Precision Float (two-byte IEEE 754)
8404 {
8405 const auto byte1_raw = get();
8406 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(input_format_t::cbor, "number")))
8407 {
8408 return false;
8409 }
8410 const auto byte2_raw = get();
8411 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(input_format_t::cbor, "number")))
8412 {
8413 return false;
8414 }
8415
8416 const auto byte1 = static_cast<unsigned char>(byte1_raw);
8417 const auto byte2 = static_cast<unsigned char>(byte2_raw);
8418
8419 // code from RFC 7049, Appendix D, Figure 3:
8420 // As half-precision floating-point numbers were only added
8421 // to IEEE 754 in 2008, today's programming platforms often
8422 // still only have limited support for them. It is very
8423 // easy to include at least decoding support for them even
8424 // without such support. An example of a small decoder for
8425 // half-precision floating-point numbers in the C language
8426 // is shown in Fig. 3.
8427 const auto half = static_cast<unsigned int>((byte1 << 8u) + byte2);
8428 const double val = [&half]
8429 {
8430 const int exp = (half >> 10u) & 0x1Fu;
8431 const unsigned int mant = half & 0x3FFu;
8432 JSON_ASSERT(0 <= exp&& exp <= 32);
8433 JSON_ASSERT(mant <= 1024);
8434 switch (exp)
8435 {
8436 case 0:
8437 return std::ldexp(mant, -24);
8438 case 31:
8439 return (mant == 0)
8440 ? std::numeric_limits<double>::infinity()
8441 : std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
8442 default:
8443 return std::ldexp(mant + 1024, exp - 25);
8444 }
8445 }();
8446 return sax->number_float((half & 0x8000u) != 0
8447 ? static_cast<number_float_t>(-val)
8448 : static_cast<number_float_t>(val), "");
8449 }
8450
8451 case 0xFA: // Single-Precision Float (four-byte IEEE 754)
8452 {
8453 float number{};
8454 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) && sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
8455 }
8456
8457 case 0xFB: // Double-Precision Float (eight-byte IEEE 754)
8458 {
8459 double number{};
8460 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) && sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
8461 }
8462
8463 default: // anything else (0xFF is handled inside the other types)
8464 {
8465 auto last_token = get_token_string();
8466 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(112, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::cbor, "invalid byte: 0x" + last_token, "value")));
8467 }
8468 }
8469 }
8470
8482 bool get_cbor_string(string_t& result)
8483 {
8484 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(input_format_t::cbor, "string")))
8485 {
8486 return false;
8487 }
8488
8489 switch (current)
8490 {
8491 // UTF-8 string (0x00..0x17 bytes follow)
8492 case 0x60:
8493 case 0x61:
8494 case 0x62:
8495 case 0x63:
8496 case 0x64:
8497 case 0x65:
8498 case 0x66:
8499 case 0x67:
8500 case 0x68:
8501 case 0x69:
8502 case 0x6A:
8503 case 0x6B:
8504 case 0x6C:
8505 case 0x6D:
8506 case 0x6E:
8507 case 0x6F:
8508 case 0x70:
8509 case 0x71:
8510 case 0x72:
8511 case 0x73:
8512 case 0x74:
8513 case 0x75:
8514 case 0x76:
8515 case 0x77:
8516 {
8517 return get_string(input_format_t::cbor, static_cast<unsigned int>(current) & 0x1Fu, result);
8518 }
8519
8520 case 0x78: // UTF-8 string (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
8521 {
8522 std::uint8_t len{};
8523 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) && get_string(input_format_t::cbor, len, result);
8524 }
8525
8526 case 0x79: // UTF-8 string (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
8527 {
8528 std::uint16_t len{};
8529 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) && get_string(input_format_t::cbor, len, result);
8530 }
8531
8532 case 0x7A: // UTF-8 string (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
8533 {
8534 std::uint32_t len{};
8535 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) && get_string(input_format_t::cbor, len, result);
8536 }
8537
8538 case 0x7B: // UTF-8 string (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
8539 {
8540 std::uint64_t len{};
8541 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) && get_string(input_format_t::cbor, len, result);
8542 }
8543
8544 case 0x7F: // UTF-8 string (indefinite length)
8545 {
8546 while (get() != 0xFF)
8547 {
8548 string_t chunk;
8549 if (!get_cbor_string(chunk))
8550 {
8551 return false;
8552 }
8553 result.append(chunk);
8554 }
8555 return true;
8556 }
8557
8558 default:
8559 {
8560 auto last_token = get_token_string();
8561 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(113, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::cbor, "expected length specification (0x60-0x7B) or indefinite string type (0x7F); last byte: 0x" + last_token, "string")));
8562 }
8563 }
8564 }
8565
8577 bool get_cbor_binary(binary_t& result)
8578 {
8579 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(input_format_t::cbor, "binary")))
8580 {
8581 return false;
8582 }
8583
8584 switch (current)
8585 {
8586 // Binary data (0x00..0x17 bytes follow)
8587 case 0x40:
8588 case 0x41:
8589 case 0x42:
8590 case 0x43:
8591 case 0x44:
8592 case 0x45:
8593 case 0x46:
8594 case 0x47:
8595 case 0x48:
8596 case 0x49:
8597 case 0x4A:
8598 case 0x4B:
8599 case 0x4C:
8600 case 0x4D:
8601 case 0x4E:
8602 case 0x4F:
8603 case 0x50:
8604 case 0x51:
8605 case 0x52:
8606 case 0x53:
8607 case 0x54:
8608 case 0x55:
8609 case 0x56:
8610 case 0x57:
8611 {
8612 return get_binary(input_format_t::cbor, static_cast<unsigned int>(current) & 0x1Fu, result);
8613 }
8614
8615 case 0x58: // Binary data (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
8616 {
8617 std::uint8_t len{};
8618 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) &&
8619 get_binary(input_format_t::cbor, len, result);
8620 }
8621
8622 case 0x59: // Binary data (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
8623 {
8624 std::uint16_t len{};
8625 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) &&
8626 get_binary(input_format_t::cbor, len, result);
8627 }
8628
8629 case 0x5A: // Binary data (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
8630 {
8631 std::uint32_t len{};
8632 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) &&
8633 get_binary(input_format_t::cbor, len, result);
8634 }
8635
8636 case 0x5B: // Binary data (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
8637 {
8638 std::uint64_t len{};
8639 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) &&
8640 get_binary(input_format_t::cbor, len, result);
8641 }
8642
8643 case 0x5F: // Binary data (indefinite length)
8644 {
8645 while (get() != 0xFF)
8646 {
8647 binary_t chunk;
8648 if (!get_cbor_binary(chunk))
8649 {
8650 return false;
8651 }
8652 result.insert(result.end(), chunk.begin(), chunk.end());
8653 }
8654 return true;
8655 }
8656
8657 default:
8658 {
8659 auto last_token = get_token_string();
8660 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(113, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::cbor, "expected length specification (0x40-0x5B) or indefinite binary array type (0x5F); last byte: 0x" + last_token, "binary")));
8661 }
8662 }
8663 }
8664
8671 bool get_cbor_array(const std::size_t len,
8672 const cbor_tag_handler_t tag_handler)
8673 {
8674 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->start_array(len)))
8675 {
8676 return false;
8677 }
8678
8679 if (len != std::size_t(-1))
8680 {
8681 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
8682 {
8683 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!parse_cbor_internal(true, tag_handler)))
8684 {
8685 return false;
8686 }
8687 }
8688 }
8689 else
8690 {
8691 while (get() != 0xFF)
8692 {
8693 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!parse_cbor_internal(false, tag_handler)))
8694 {
8695 return false;
8696 }
8697 }
8698 }
8699
8700 return sax->end_array();
8701 }
8702
8709 bool get_cbor_object(const std::size_t len,
8710 const cbor_tag_handler_t tag_handler)
8711 {
8712 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->start_object(len)))
8713 {
8714 return false;
8715 }
8716
8717 string_t key;
8718 if (len != std::size_t(-1))
8719 {
8720 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
8721 {
8722 get();
8723 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_cbor_string(key) || !sax->key(key)))
8724 {
8725 return false;
8726 }
8727
8728 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!parse_cbor_internal(true, tag_handler)))
8729 {
8730 return false;
8731 }
8732 key.clear();
8733 }
8734 }
8735 else
8736 {
8737 while (get() != 0xFF)
8738 {
8739 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_cbor_string(key) || !sax->key(key)))
8740 {
8741 return false;
8742 }
8743
8744 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!parse_cbor_internal(true, tag_handler)))
8745 {
8746 return false;
8747 }
8748 key.clear();
8749 }
8750 }
8751
8752 return sax->end_object();
8753 }
8754

9033 }

9036 {

9039 }
9040
9041 case 0xD0: // int 8
9042 {

9045 }
9046
9047 case 0xD1: // int 16
9048 {
9049 std::int16_t number{};
9050 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, number) && sax->number_integer(number);
9051 }
9052
9053 case 0xD2: // int 32
9054 {

9058

9063 }

9081 }

9084 {

9087 }

9090 case 0xE0:

9123
9124 default: // anything else

9127 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(112, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::msgpack, "invalid byte: 0x" + last_token, "value")));
9128 }
9129 }

9131
9142 bool get_msgpack_string(string_t& result)
9143 {
9144 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(input_format_t::msgpack, "string")))
9145 {
9146 return false;
9147 }
9148
9149 switch (current)
9150 {
9151 // fixstr
9152 case 0xA0:
9153 case 0xA1:
9154 case 0xA2:
9155 case 0xA3:
9156 case 0xA4:
9157 case 0xA5:
9158 case 0xA6:
9159 case 0xA7:
9160 case 0xA8:
9161 case 0xA9:
9162 case 0xAA:
9163 case 0xAB:
9164 case 0xAC:
9165 case 0xAD:
9166 case 0xAE:
9167 case 0xAF:
9168 case 0xB0:
9169 case 0xB1:
9170 case 0xB2:
9171 case 0xB3:
9172 case 0xB4:
9173 case 0xB5:
9174 case 0xB6:
9175 case 0xB7:
9176 case 0xB8:
9177 case 0xB9:
9178 case 0xBA:
9179 case 0xBB:
9180 case 0xBC:
9181 case 0xBD:
9182 case 0xBE:
9183 case 0xBF:
9184 {
9185 return get_string(input_format_t::msgpack, static_cast<unsigned int>(current) & 0x1Fu, result);
9186 }
9187
9188 case 0xD9: // str 8
9189 {
9190 std::uint8_t len{};
9191 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, len) && get_string(input_format_t::msgpack, len, result);
9192 }
9193
9194 case 0xDA: // str 16
9195 {
9196 std::uint16_t len{};
9197 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, len) && get_string(input_format_t::msgpack, len, result);
9198 }
9199
9200 case 0xDB: // str 32
9201 {
9202 std::uint32_t len{};
9203 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, len) && get_string(input_format_t::msgpack, len, result);
9204 }
9205
9206 default:
9207 {
9208 auto last_token = get_token_string();
9209 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(113, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::msgpack, "expected length specification (0xA0-0xBF, 0xD9-0xDB); last byte: 0x" + last_token, "string")));
9210 }
9211 }
9212 }
9213
9224 bool get_msgpack_binary(binary_t& result)
9225 {
9226 // helper function to set the subtype
9227 auto assign_and_return_true = [&result](std::int8_t subtype)
9228 {
9229 result.set_subtype(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(subtype));
9230 return true;
9231 };
9232
9233 switch (current)
9234 {
9235 case 0xC4: // bin 8
9236 {
9237 std::uint8_t len{};
9238 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, len) &&
9239 get_binary(input_format_t::msgpack, len, result);
9240 }
9241
9242 case 0xC5: // bin 16
9243 {
9244 std::uint16_t len{};
9245 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, len) &&
9246 get_binary(input_format_t::msgpack, len, result);
9247 }
9248
9249 case 0xC6: // bin 32
9250 {
9251 std::uint32_t len{};
9252 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, len) &&
9253 get_binary(input_format_t::msgpack, len, result);
9254 }
9255
9256 case 0xC7: // ext 8
9257 {
9258 std::uint8_t len{};
9259 std::int8_t subtype{};
9260 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, len) &&
9261 get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, subtype) &&
9262 get_binary(input_format_t::msgpack, len, result) &&
9263 assign_and_return_true(subtype);
9264 }
9265
9266 case 0xC8: // ext 16
9267 {
9268 std::uint16_t len{};
9269 std::int8_t subtype{};
9270 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, len) &&
9271 get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, subtype) &&
9272 get_binary(input_format_t::msgpack, len, result) &&
9273 assign_and_return_true(subtype);
9274 }
9275
9276 case 0xC9: // ext 32
9277 {
9278 std::uint32_t len{};
9279 std::int8_t subtype{};
9280 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, len) &&
9281 get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, subtype) &&
9282 get_binary(input_format_t::msgpack, len, result) &&
9283 assign_and_return_true(subtype);
9284 }
9285
9286 case 0xD4: // fixext 1
9287 {
9288 std::int8_t subtype{};
9289 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, subtype) &&
9290 get_binary(input_format_t::msgpack, 1, result) &&
9291 assign_and_return_true(subtype);
9292 }
9293
9294 case 0xD5: // fixext 2
9295 {
9296 std::int8_t subtype{};
9297 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, subtype) &&
9298 get_binary(input_format_t::msgpack, 2, result) &&
9299 assign_and_return_true(subtype);
9300 }
9301
9302 case 0xD6: // fixext 4
9303 {
9304 std::int8_t subtype{};
9305 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, subtype) &&
9306 get_binary(input_format_t::msgpack, 4, result) &&
9307 assign_and_return_true(subtype);
9308 }
9309
9310 case 0xD7: // fixext 8
9311 {
9312 std::int8_t subtype{};
9313 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, subtype) &&
9314 get_binary(input_format_t::msgpack, 8, result) &&
9315 assign_and_return_true(subtype);
9316 }
9317
9318 case 0xD8: // fixext 16
9319 {
9320 std::int8_t subtype{};
9321 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, subtype) &&
9322 get_binary(input_format_t::msgpack, 16, result) &&
9323 assign_and_return_true(subtype);
9324 }
9325
9326 default: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
9327 return false; // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
9328 }
9329 }
9330
9335 bool get_msgpack_array(const std::size_t len)
9336 {
9337 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->start_array(len)))
9338 {
9339 return false;
9340 }
9341
9342 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
9343 {
9344 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!parse_msgpack_internal()))
9345 {
9346 return false;
9347 }
9348 }
9349
9350 return sax->end_array();
9351 }
9352
9357 bool get_msgpack_object(const std::size_t len)
9358 {
9359 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->start_object(len)))
9360 {
9361 return false;
9362 }
9363
9364 string_t key;
9365 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
9366 {
9367 get();
9368 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_msgpack_string(key) || !sax->key(key)))
9369 {
9370 return false;
9371 }
9372
9373 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!parse_msgpack_internal()))
9374 {
9375 return false;
9376 }
9377 key.clear();
9378 }
9379
9380 return sax->end_object();
9381 }
9382
9384 // UBJSON //
9386
9394 bool parse_ubjson_internal(const bool get_char = true)
9395 {
9396 return get_ubjson_value(get_char ? get_ignore_noop() : current);
9397 }
9398
9413 bool get_ubjson_string(string_t& result, const bool get_char = true)
9414 {
9415 if (get_char)
9416 {
9417 get(); // TODO(niels): may we ignore N here?
9418 }
9419
9420 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(input_format_t::ubjson, "value")))
9421 {
9422 return false;
9423 }
9424
9425 switch (current)
9426 {
9427 case 'U':
9428 {
9429 std::uint8_t len{};
9430 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, len) && get_string(input_format_t::ubjson, len, result);
9431 }
9432
9433 case 'i':
9434 {
9435 std::int8_t len{};
9436 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, len) && get_string(input_format_t::ubjson, len, result);
9437 }
9438
9439 case 'I':
9440 {
9441 std::int16_t len{};
9442 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, len) && get_string(input_format_t::ubjson, len, result);
9443 }
9444
9445 case 'l':
9446 {
9447 std::int32_t len{};
9448 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, len) && get_string(input_format_t::ubjson, len, result);
9449 }
9450
9451 case 'L':
9452 {
9453 std::int64_t len{};
9454 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, len) && get_string(input_format_t::ubjson, len, result);
9455 }
9456
9457 default:
9458 auto last_token = get_token_string();
9459 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(113, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::ubjson, "expected length type specification (U, i, I, l, L); last byte: 0x" + last_token, "string")));
9460 }
9461 }
9462
9467 bool get_ubjson_size_value(std::size_t& result)
9468 {
9469 switch (get_ignore_noop())
9470 {
9471 case 'U':
9472 {
9473 std::uint8_t number{};
9474 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number)))
9475 {
9476 return false;
9477 }
9478 result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
9479 return true;
9480 }
9481
9482 case 'i':
9483 {
9484 std::int8_t number{};
9485 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number)))
9486 {
9487 return false;
9488 }
9489 result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
9490 return true;
9491 }
9492
9493 case 'I':
9494 {
9495 std::int16_t number{};
9496 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number)))
9497 {
9498 return false;
9499 }
9500 result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
9501 return true;
9502 }
9503
9504 case 'l':
9505 {
9506 std::int32_t number{};
9507 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number)))
9508 {
9509 return false;
9510 }
9511 result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
9512 return true;
9513 }
9514
9515 case 'L':
9516 {
9517 std::int64_t number{};
9518 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number)))
9519 {
9520 return false;
9521 }
9522 result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
9523 return true;
9524 }
9525
9526 default:
9527 {
9528 auto last_token = get_token_string();
9529 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(113, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::ubjson, "expected length type specification (U, i, I, l, L) after '#'; last byte: 0x" + last_token, "size")));
9530 }
9531 }
9532 }
9533
9544 bool get_ubjson_size_type(std::pair<std::size_t, char_int_type>& result)
9545 {
9546 result.first = string_t::npos; // size
9547 result.second = 0; // type
9548
9549 get_ignore_noop();
9550
9551 if (current == '$')
9552 {
9553 result.second = get(); // must not ignore 'N', because 'N' maybe the type
9554 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(input_format_t::ubjson, "type")))
9555 {
9556 return false;
9557 }
9558
9559 get_ignore_noop();
9560 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(current != '#'))
9561 {
9562 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(input_format_t::ubjson, "value")))
9563 {
9564 return false;
9565 }
9566 auto last_token = get_token_string();
9567 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(112, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::ubjson, "expected '#' after type information; last byte: 0x" + last_token, "size")));
9568 }
9569
9570 return get_ubjson_size_value(result.first);
9571 }
9572
9573 if (current == '#')
9574 {
9575 return get_ubjson_size_value(result.first);
9576 }
9577
9578 return true;
9579 }
9580
9585 bool get_ubjson_value(const char_int_type prefix)
9586 {
9587 switch (prefix)
9588 {
9589 case std::char_traits<char_type>::eof(): // EOF
9590 return unexpect_eof(input_format_t::ubjson, "value");
9591
9592 case 'T': // true
9593 return sax->boolean(true);
9594 case 'F': // false
9595 return sax->boolean(false);
9596
9597 case 'Z': // null
9598 return sax->null();
9599
9600 case 'U':
9601 {
9602 std::uint8_t number{};
9603 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number) && sax->number_unsigned(number);
9604 }
9605
9606 case 'i':
9607 {
9608 std::int8_t number{};
9609 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number) && sax->number_integer(number);
9610 }
9611
9612 case 'I':
9613 {
9614 std::int16_t number{};
9615 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number) && sax->number_integer(number);
9616 }
9617
9618 case 'l':
9619 {
9620 std::int32_t number{};
9621 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number) && sax->number_integer(number);
9622 }
9623
9624 case 'L':
9625 {
9626 std::int64_t number{};
9627 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number) && sax->number_integer(number);
9628 }
9629
9630 case 'd':
9631 {
9632 float number{};
9633 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number) && sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
9634 }
9635
9636 case 'D':
9637 {
9638 double number{};
9639 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number) && sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
9640 }
9641
9642 case 'H':
9643 {
9644 return get_ubjson_high_precision_number();
9645 }
9646
9647 case 'C': // char
9648 {
9649 get();
9650 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(input_format_t::ubjson, "char")))
9651 {
9652 return false;
9653 }
9654 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(current > 127))
9655 {
9656 auto last_token = get_token_string();
9657 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(113, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::ubjson, "byte after 'C' must be in range 0x00..0x7F; last byte: 0x" + last_token, "char")));
9658 }
9659 string_t s(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(current));
9660 return sax->string(s);
9661 }
9662
9663 case 'S': // string
9664 {
9665 string_t s;
9666 return get_ubjson_string(s) && sax->string(s);
9667 }
9668
9669 case '[': // array
9670 return get_ubjson_array();
9671
9672 case '{': // object
9673 return get_ubjson_object();
9674
9675 default: // anything else
9676 {
9677 auto last_token = get_token_string();
9678 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(112, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::ubjson, "invalid byte: 0x" + last_token, "value")));
9679 }
9680 }
9681 }
9682
9686 bool get_ubjson_array()
9687 {
9688 std::pair<std::size_t, char_int_type> size_and_type;
9689 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_ubjson_size_type(size_and_type)))
9690 {
9691 return false;
9692 }
9693
9694 if (size_and_type.first != string_t::npos)
9695 {
9696 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->start_array(size_and_type.first)))
9697 {
9698 return false;
9699 }
9700
9701 if (size_and_type.second != 0)
9702 {
9703 if (size_and_type.second != 'N')
9704 {
9705 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < size_and_type.first; ++i)
9706 {
9707 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_ubjson_value(size_and_type.second)))
9708 {
9709 return false;
9710 }
9711 }
9712 }
9713 }
9714 else
9715 {
9716 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < size_and_type.first; ++i)
9717 {
9718 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!parse_ubjson_internal()))
9719 {
9720 return false;
9721 }
9722 }
9723 }
9724 }
9725 else
9726 {
9727 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->start_array(std::size_t(-1))))
9728 {
9729 return false;
9730 }
9731
9732 while (current != ']')
9733 {
9734 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!parse_ubjson_internal(false)))
9735 {
9736 return false;
9737 }
9738 get_ignore_noop();
9739 }
9740 }
9741
9742 return sax->end_array();
9743 }
9744
9748 bool get_ubjson_object()
9749 {
9750 std::pair<std::size_t, char_int_type> size_and_type;
9751 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_ubjson_size_type(size_and_type)))
9752 {
9753 return false;
9754 }
9755
9756 string_t key;
9757 if (size_and_type.first != string_t::npos)
9758 {
9759 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->start_object(size_and_type.first)))
9760 {
9761 return false;
9762 }
9763
9764 if (size_and_type.second != 0)
9765 {
9766 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < size_and_type.first; ++i)
9767 {
9768 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_ubjson_string(key) || !sax->key(key)))
9769 {
9770 return false;
9771 }
9772 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_ubjson_value(size_and_type.second)))
9773 {
9774 return false;
9775 }
9776 key.clear();
9777 }
9778 }
9779 else
9780 {
9781 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < size_and_type.first; ++i)
9782 {
9783 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_ubjson_string(key) || !sax->key(key)))
9784 {
9785 return false;
9786 }
9787 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!parse_ubjson_internal()))
9788 {
9789 return false;
9790 }
9791 key.clear();
9792 }
9793 }
9794 }
9795 else
9796 {
9797 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->start_object(std::size_t(-1))))
9798 {
9799 return false;
9800 }
9801
9802 while (current != '}')
9803 {
9804 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_ubjson_string(key, false) || !sax->key(key)))
9805 {
9806 return false;
9807 }
9808 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!parse_ubjson_internal()))
9809 {
9810 return false;
9811 }
9812 get_ignore_noop();
9813 key.clear();
9814 }
9815 }
9816
9817 return sax->end_object();
9818 }
9819
9820 // Note, no reader for UBJSON binary types is implemented because they do
9821 // not exist
9822
9823 bool get_ubjson_high_precision_number()
9824 {
9825 // get size of following number string
9826 std::size_t size{};
9827 auto res = get_ubjson_size_value(size);
9828 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!res))
9829 {
9830 return res;
9831 }
9832
9833 // get number string
9834 std::vector<char> number_vector;
9835 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < size; ++i)
9836 {
9837 get();
9838 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(input_format_t::ubjson, "number")))
9839 {
9840 return false;
9841 }
9842 number_vector.push_back(static_cast<char>(current));
9843 }
9844
9845 // parse number string
9846 auto number_ia = detail::input_adapter(std::forward<decltype(number_vector)>(number_vector));
9847 auto number_lexer = detail::lexer<BasicJsonType, decltype(number_ia)>(std::move(number_ia), false);
9848 const auto result_number = number_lexer.scan();
9849 const auto number_string = number_lexer.get_token_string();
9850 const auto result_remainder = number_lexer.scan();
9851
9852 using token_type = typename detail::lexer_base<BasicJsonType>::token_type;
9853
9854 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(result_remainder != token_type::end_of_input))
9855 {
9856 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, number_string, parse_error::create(115, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::ubjson, "invalid number text: " + number_lexer.get_token_string(), "high-precision number")));
9857 }
9858
9859 switch (result_number)
9860 {
9861 case token_type::value_integer:
9862 return sax->number_integer(number_lexer.get_number_integer());
9863 case token_type::value_unsigned:
9864 return sax->number_unsigned(number_lexer.get_number_unsigned());
9865 case token_type::value_float:
9866 return sax->number_float(number_lexer.get_number_float(), std::move(number_string));
9867 default:
9868 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, number_string, parse_error::create(115, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::ubjson, "invalid number text: " + number_lexer.get_token_string(), "high-precision number")));
9869 }
9870 }
9871
9873 // Utility functions //
9875
9885 char_int_type get()
9886 {
9887 ++chars_read;
9888 return current = ia.get_character();
9889 }
9890
9894 char_int_type get_ignore_noop()
9895 {
9896 do
9897 {
9898 get();
9899 }
9900 while (current == 'N');
9901
9902 return current;
9903 }
9904
9905 /*
9906 @brief read a number from the input
9907
9908 @tparam NumberType the type of the number
9909 @param[in] format the current format (for diagnostics)
9910 @param[out] result number of type @a NumberType
9911
9912 @return whether conversion completed
9913
9914 @note This function needs to respect the system's endianess, because
9915 bytes in CBOR, MessagePack, and UBJSON are stored in network order
9916 (big endian) and therefore need reordering on little endian systems.
9917 */
9918 template<typename NumberType, bool InputIsLittleEndian = false>
9919 bool get_number(const input_format_t format, NumberType& result)
9920 {
9921 // step 1: read input into array with system's byte order
9922 std::array<std::uint8_t, sizeof(NumberType)> vec;
9923 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < sizeof(NumberType); ++i)
9924 {
9925 get();
9926 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(format, "number")))
9927 {
9928 return false;
9929 }
9930
9931 // reverse byte order prior to conversion if necessary
9932 if (is_little_endian != InputIsLittleEndian)
9933 {
9934 vec[sizeof(NumberType) - i - 1] = static_cast<std::uint8_t>(current);
9935 }
9936 else
9937 {
9938 vec[i] = static_cast<std::uint8_t>(current); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
9939 }
9940 }
9941
9942 // step 2: convert array into number of type T and return
9943 std::memcpy(&result, vec.data(), sizeof(NumberType));
9944 return true;
9945 }
9946
9961 template<typename NumberType>
9962 bool get_string(const input_format_t format,
9963 const NumberType len,
9964 string_t& result)
9965 {
9966 bool success = true;
9967 for (NumberType i = 0; i < len; i++)
9968 {
9969 get();
9970 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(format, "string")))
9971 {
9972 success = false;
9973 break;
9974 }
9975 result.push_back(static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(current));
9976 };
9977 return success;
9978 }
9979
9994 template<typename NumberType>
9995 bool get_binary(const input_format_t format,
9996 const NumberType len,
9997 binary_t& result)
9998 {
9999 bool success = true;
10000 for (NumberType i = 0; i < len; i++)
10001 {
10002 get();
10003 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(format, "binary")))
10004 {
10005 success = false;
10006 break;
10007 }
10008 result.push_back(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(current));
10009 }
10010 return success;
10011 }
10012
10018 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(3)
10019 bool unexpect_eof(const input_format_t format, const char* context) const
10020 {
10021 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(current == std::char_traits<char_type>::eof()))
10022 {
10023 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, "<end of file>",
10024 parse_error::create(110, chars_read, exception_message(format, "unexpected end of input", context)));
10025 }
10026 return true;
10027 }
10028
10032 std::string get_token_string() const
10033 {
10034 std::array<char, 3> cr{{}};
10035 (std::snprintf)(cr.data(), cr.size(), "%.2hhX", static_cast<unsigned char>(current));
10036 return std::string{cr.data()};
10037 }
10038
10045 std::string exception_message(const input_format_t format,
10046 const std::string& detail,
10047 const std::string& context) const
10048 {
10049 std::string error_msg = "syntax error while parsing ";
10050
10051 switch (format)
10052 {
10053 case input_format_t::cbor:
10054 error_msg += "CBOR";
10055 break;
10056
10057 case input_format_t::msgpack:
10058 error_msg += "MessagePack";
10059 break;
10060
10061 case input_format_t::ubjson:
10062 error_msg += "UBJSON";
10063 break;
10064
10065 case input_format_t::bson:
10066 error_msg += "BSON";
10067 break;
10068
10069 default: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
10070 JSON_ASSERT(false); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
10071 }
10072
10073 return error_msg + " " + context + ": " + detail;
10074 }
10075
10076 private:
10078 InputAdapterType ia;
10079
10081 char_int_type current = std::char_traits<char_type>::eof();
10082
10084 std::size_t chars_read = 0;
10085
10087 const bool is_little_endian = little_endianess();
10088
10090 json_sax_t* sax = nullptr;
10091 };
