10129 // parser //
10131
10132 enum class parse_event_t : uint8_t
10133 {
10135 object_start,
10137 object_end,
10139 array_start,
10141 array_end,
10143 key,
10145 value
10146 };
10147
10148 template<typename BasicJsonType>
10149 using parser_callback_t =
10150 std::function<bool(int depth, parse_event_t event, BasicJsonType& parsed)>;
10151
10157 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename InputAdapterType>
10158 class parser
10159 {
10160 using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
10161 using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
10162 using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
10163 using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
10164 using lexer_t = lexer<BasicJsonType, InputAdapterType>;
10165 using token_type = typename lexer_t::token_type;
10166
10167 public:
10169 explicit parser(InputAdapterType&& adapter,
10170 const parser_callback_t<BasicJsonType> cb = nullptr,
10171 const bool allow_exceptions_ = true,
10172 const bool skip_comments = false)
10173 : callback(cb)
10174 , m_lexer(std::move(adapter), skip_comments)
10175 , allow_exceptions(allow_exceptions_)
10176 {
10177 // read first token
10178 get_token();
10179 }
10180
10191 void parse(const bool strict, BasicJsonType& result)
10192 {
10193 if (callback)
10194 {
10195 json_sax_dom_callback_parser<BasicJsonType> sdp(result, callback, allow_exceptions);
10196 sax_parse_internal(&sdp);
10197 result.assert_invariant();
10198
10199 // in strict mode, input must be completely read
10200 if (strict && (get_token() != token_type::end_of_input))
10201 {
10202 sdp.parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
10203 m_lexer.get_token_string(),
10204 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
10205 exception_message(token_type::end_of_input, "value")));
10206 }
10207
10208 // in case of an error, return discarded value
10209 if (sdp.is_errored())
10210 {
10211 result = value_t::discarded;
10212 return;
10213 }
10214
10215 // set top-level value to null if it was discarded by the callback
10216 // function
10217 if (result.is_discarded())
10218 {
10219 result = nullptr;
10220 }
10221 }
10222 else
10223 {
10224 json_sax_dom_parser<BasicJsonType> sdp(result, allow_exceptions);
10225 sax_parse_internal(&sdp);
10226 result.assert_invariant();
10227
10228 // in strict mode, input must be completely read
10229 if (strict && (get_token() != token_type::end_of_input))
10230 {
10231 sdp.parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
10232 m_lexer.get_token_string(),
10233 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
10234 exception_message(token_type::end_of_input, "value")));
10235 }
10236
10237 // in case of an error, return discarded value
10238 if (sdp.is_errored())
10239 {
10240 result = value_t::discarded;
10241 return;
10242 }
10243 }
10244 }
10245
10252 bool accept(const bool strict = true)
10253 {
10254 json_sax_acceptor<BasicJsonType> sax_acceptor;
10255 return sax_parse(&sax_acceptor, strict);
10256 }
10257
10258 template<typename SAX>
10259 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(2)
10260 bool sax_parse(SAX* sax, const bool strict = true)
10261 {
10262 (void)detail::is_sax_static_asserts<SAX, BasicJsonType> {};
10263 const bool result = sax_parse_internal(sax);
10264
10265 // strict mode: next byte must be EOF
10266 if (result && strict && (get_token() != token_type::end_of_input))
10267 {
10268 return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
10269 m_lexer.get_token_string(),
10270 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
10271 exception_message(token_type::end_of_input, "value")));
10272 }
10273
10274 return result;
10275 }
10276
10277 private:
10278 template<typename SAX>
10279 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(2)
10280 bool sax_parse_internal(SAX* sax)
10281 {
10282 // stack to remember the hierarchy of structured values we are parsing
10283 // true = array; false = object
10284 std::vector<bool> states;
10285 // value to avoid a goto (see comment where set to true)
10286 bool skip_to_state_evaluation = false;
10287
10288 while (true)
10289 {
10290 if (!skip_to_state_evaluation)
10291 {
10292 // invariant: get_token() was called before each iteration
10293 switch (last_token)
10294 {
10295 case token_type::begin_object:
10296 {
10297 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->start_object(std::size_t(-1))))
10298 {
10299 return false;
10300 }
10301
10302 // closing } -> we are done
10303 if (get_token() == token_type::end_object)
10304 {
10305 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->end_object()))
10306 {
10307 return false;
10308 }
10309 break;
10310 }
10311
10312 // parse key
10313 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(last_token != token_type::value_string))
10314 {
10315 return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
10316 m_lexer.get_token_string(),
10317 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
10318 exception_message(token_type::value_string, "object key")));
10319 }
10320 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->key(m_lexer.get_string())))
10321 {
10322 return false;
10323 }
10324
10325 // parse separator (:)
10326 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(get_token() != token_type::name_separator))
10327 {
10328 return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
10329 m_lexer.get_token_string(),
10330 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
10331 exception_message(token_type::name_separator, "object separator")));
10332 }
10333
10334 // remember we are now inside an object
10335 states.push_back(false);
10336
10337 // parse values
10338 get_token();
10339 continue;
10340 }
10341
10342 case token_type::begin_array:
10343 {
10344 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->start_array(std::size_t(-1))))
10345 {
10346 return false;
10347 }
10348
10349 // closing ] -> we are done
10350 if (get_token() == token_type::end_array)
10351 {
10352 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->end_array()))
10353 {
10354 return false;
10355 }
10356 break;
10357 }
10358
10359 // remember we are now inside an array
10360 states.push_back(true);
10361
10362 // parse values (no need to call get_token)
10363 continue;
10364 }
10365
10366 case token_type::value_float:
10367 {
10368 const auto res = m_lexer.get_number_float();
10369
10370 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!std::isfinite(res)))
10371 {
10372 return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
10373 m_lexer.get_token_string(),
10374 out_of_range::create(406, "number overflow parsing '" + m_lexer.get_token_string() + "'"));
10375 }
10376
10377 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->number_float(res, m_lexer.get_string())))
10378 {
10379 return false;
10380 }
10381
10382 break;
10383 }
10384
10385 case token_type::literal_false:
10386 {
10387 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->boolean(false)))
10388 {
10389 return false;
10390 }
10391 break;
10392 }
10393
10394 case token_type::literal_null:
10395 {
10396 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->null()))
10397 {
10398 return false;
10399 }
10400 break;
10401 }
10402
10403 case token_type::literal_true:
10404 {
10405 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->boolean(true)))
10406 {
10407 return false;
10408 }
10409 break;
10410 }
10411
10412 case token_type::value_integer:
10413 {
10414 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->number_integer(m_lexer.get_number_integer())))
10415 {
10416 return false;
10417 }
10418 break;
10419 }
10420
10421 case token_type::value_string:
10422 {
10423 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->string(m_lexer.get_string())))
10424 {
10425 return false;
10426 }
10427 break;
10428 }
10429
10430 case token_type::value_unsigned:
10431 {
10432 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->number_unsigned(m_lexer.get_number_unsigned())))
10433 {
10434 return false;
10435 }
10436 break;
10437 }
10438
10439 case token_type::parse_error:
10440 {
10441 // using "uninitialized" to avoid "expected" message
10442 return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
10443 m_lexer.get_token_string(),
10444 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
10445 exception_message(token_type::uninitialized, "value")));
10446 }
10447
10448 default: // the last token was unexpected
10449 {
10450 return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
10451 m_lexer.get_token_string(),
10452 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
10453 exception_message(token_type::literal_or_value, "value")));
10454 }
10455 }
10456 }
10457 else
10458 {
10459 skip_to_state_evaluation = false;
10460 }
10461
10462 // we reached this line after we successfully parsed a value
10463 if (states.empty())
10464 {
10465 // empty stack: we reached the end of the hierarchy: done
10466 return true;
10467 }
10468
10469 if (states.back()) // array
10470 {
10471 // comma -> next value
10472 if (get_token() == token_type::value_separator)
10473 {
10474 // parse a new value
10475 get_token();
10476 continue;
10477 }
10478
10479 // closing ]
10480 if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(last_token == token_type::end_array))
10481 {
10482 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->end_array()))
10483 {
10484 return false;
10485 }
10486
10487 // We are done with this array. Before we can parse a
10488 // new value, we need to evaluate the new state first.
10489 // By setting skip_to_state_evaluation to false, we
10490 // are effectively jumping to the beginning of this if.
10491 JSON_ASSERT(!states.empty());
10492 states.pop_back();
10493 skip_to_state_evaluation = true;
10494 continue;
10495 }
10496
10497 return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
10498 m_lexer.get_token_string(),
10499 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
10500 exception_message(token_type::end_array, "array")));
10501 }
10502 else // object
10503 {
10504 // comma -> next value
10505 if (get_token() == token_type::value_separator)
10506 {
10507 // parse key
10508 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(get_token() != token_type::value_string))
10509 {
10510 return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
10511 m_lexer.get_token_string(),
10512 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
10513 exception_message(token_type::value_string, "object key")));
10514 }
10515
10516 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->key(m_lexer.get_string())))
10517 {
10518 return false;
10519 }
10520
10521 // parse separator (:)
10522 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(get_token() != token_type::name_separator))
10523 {
10524 return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
10525 m_lexer.get_token_string(),
10526 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
10527 exception_message(token_type::name_separator, "object separator")));
10528 }
10529
10530 // parse values
10531 get_token();
10532 continue;
10533 }
10534
10535 // closing }
10536 if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(last_token == token_type::end_object))
10537 {
10538 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->end_object()))
10539 {
10540 return false;
10541 }
10542
10543 // We are done with this object. Before we can parse a
10544 // new value, we need to evaluate the new state first.
10545 // By setting skip_to_state_evaluation to false, we
10546 // are effectively jumping to the beginning of this if.
10547 JSON_ASSERT(!states.empty());
10548 states.pop_back();
10549 skip_to_state_evaluation = true;
10550 continue;
10551 }
10552
10553 return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
10554 m_lexer.get_token_string(),
10555 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
10556 exception_message(token_type::end_object, "object")));
10557 }
10558 }
10559 }
10560
10562 token_type get_token()
10563 {
10564 return last_token = m_lexer.scan();
10565 }
10566
10567 std::string exception_message(const token_type expected, const std::string& context)
10568 {
10569 std::string error_msg = "syntax error ";
10570
10571 if (!context.empty())
10572 {
10573 error_msg += "while parsing " + context + " ";
10574 }
10575
10576 error_msg += "- ";
10577
10578 if (last_token == token_type::parse_error)
10579 {
10580 error_msg += std::string(m_lexer.get_error_message()) + "; last read: '" +
10581 m_lexer.get_token_string() + "'";
10582 }
10583 else
10584 {
10585 error_msg += "unexpected " + std::string(lexer_t::token_type_name(last_token));
10586 }
10587
10588 if (expected != token_type::uninitialized)
10589 {
10590 error_msg += "; expected " + std::string(lexer_t::token_type_name(expected));
10591 }
10592
10593 return error_msg;
10594 }
10595
10596 private:
10598 const parser_callback_t<BasicJsonType> callback = nullptr;
10600 token_type last_token = token_type::uninitialized;
10602 lexer_t m_lexer;
10604 const bool allow_exceptions = true;
10605 };
10606 } // namespace detail
10607} // namespace nlohmann
10608
10609// #include <nlohmann/detail/iterators/internal_iterator.hpp>
10610
10611
10612// #include <nlohmann/detail/iterators/primitive_iterator.hpp>
10613
10614
10615#include <cstddef> // ptrdiff_t
10616#include <limits> // numeric_limits
10617
10618namespace nlohmann
10619{
10620 namespace detail
10621 {
10622 /*
10623@brief an iterator for primitive JSON types
10624
10625This class models an iterator for primitive JSON types (boolean, number,
10626string). It's only purpose is to allow the iterator/const_iterator classes
10627to "iterate" over primitive values. Internally, the iterator is modeled by
10628a `difference_type` variable. Value begin_value (`0`) models the begin,
10629end_value (`1`) models past the end.
10630*/
10631 class primitive_iterator_t
10632 {
10633 private:
10634 using difference_type = std::ptrdiff_t;
10635 static constexpr difference_type begin_value = 0;
10636 static constexpr difference_type end_value = begin_value + 1;
10637
10639 difference_type m_it = (std::numeric_limits<std::ptrdiff_t>::min)();
10640
10641 public:
10642 constexpr difference_type get_value() const noexcept
10643 {
10644 return m_it;
10645 }
10646
10648 void set_begin() noexcept
10649 {
10650 m_it = begin_value;
10651 }
10652
10654 void set_end() noexcept
10655 {
10656 m_it = end_value;
10657 }
10658
10660 constexpr bool is_begin() const noexcept
10661 {
10662 return m_it == begin_value;
10663 }
10664
10666 constexpr bool is_end() const noexcept
10667 {
10668 return m_it == end_value;
10669 }
10670
10671 friend constexpr bool operator==(primitive_iterator_t lhs, primitive_iterator_t rhs) noexcept
10672 {
10673 return lhs.m_it == rhs.m_it;
10674 }
10675
10676 friend constexpr bool operator<(primitive_iterator_t lhs, primitive_iterator_t rhs) noexcept
10677 {
10678 return lhs.m_it < rhs.m_it;
10679 }
10680
10681 primitive_iterator_t operator+(difference_type n) noexcept
10682 {
10683 auto result = *this;
10684 result += n;
10685 return result;
10686 }
10687
10688 friend constexpr difference_type operator-(primitive_iterator_t lhs, primitive_iterator_t rhs) noexcept
10689 {
10690 return lhs.m_it - rhs.m_it;
10691 }
10692
10693 primitive_iterator_t& operator++() noexcept
10694 {
10695 ++m_it;
10696 return *this;
10697 }
10698
10699 primitive_iterator_t const operator++(int) noexcept
10700 {
10701 auto result = *this;
10702 ++m_it;
10703 return result;
10704 }
10705
10706 primitive_iterator_t& operator--() noexcept
10707 {
10708 --m_it;
10709 return *this;
10710 }
10711
10712 primitive_iterator_t const operator--(int) noexcept
10713 {
10714 auto result = *this;
10715 --m_it;
10716 return result;
10717 }
10718
10719 primitive_iterator_t& operator+=(difference_type n) noexcept
10720 {
10721 m_it += n;
10722 return *this;
10723 }
10724
10725 primitive_iterator_t& operator-=(difference_type n) noexcept
10726 {
10727 m_it -= n;
10728 return *this;
10729 }
10730 };
10731 } // namespace detail
10732} // namespace nlohmann
10733
10734
10735namespace nlohmann
10736{
10737 namespace detail
10738 {
10745 template<typename BasicJsonType> struct internal_iterator
10746 {
10748 typename BasicJsonType::object_t::iterator object_iterator {};
10750 typename BasicJsonType::array_t::iterator array_iterator {};
10752 primitive_iterator_t primitive_iterator {};
10753 };
10754 } // namespace detail
10755} // namespace nlohmann

10757// #include <nlohmann/detail/iterators/iter_impl.hpp>
10758
10759
10760#include <iterator> // iterator, random_access_iterator_tag, bidirectional_iterator_tag, advance, next
10761#include <type_traits> // conditional, is_const, remove_const
10762
10763// #include <nlohmann/detail/exceptions.hpp>
10764
10765// #include <nlohmann/detail/iterators/internal_iterator.hpp>
10766
10767// #include <nlohmann/detail/iterators/primitive_iterator.hpp>
10768
10769// #include <nlohmann/detail/macro_scope.hpp>
10770
10771// #include <nlohmann/detail/meta/cpp_future.hpp>
10772
10773// #include <nlohmann/detail/meta/type_traits.hpp>
10774
10775// #include <nlohmann/detail/value_t.hpp>
10776
10777
10778namespace nlohmann
10779{
10780 namespace detail
10781 {
10782 // forward declare, to be able to friend it later on
10783 template<typename IteratorType> class iteration_proxy;
10784 template<typename IteratorType> class iteration_proxy_value;
10785
10802 template<typename BasicJsonType>
10803 class iter_impl
10804 {
10806 friend iter_impl<typename std::conditional<std::is_const<BasicJsonType>::value, typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type, const BasicJsonType>::type>;
10807 friend BasicJsonType;
10808 friend iteration_proxy<iter_impl>;
10809 friend iteration_proxy_value<iter_impl>;
10810
10811 using object_t = typename BasicJsonType::object_t;
10812 using array_t = typename BasicJsonType::array_t;
10813 // make sure BasicJsonType is basic_json or const basic_json
10814 static_assert(is_basic_json<typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type>::value,
10815 "iter_impl only accepts (const) basic_json");
10816
10817 public:
10818
10824 using iterator_category = std::bidirectional_iterator_tag;
10825
10827 using value_type = typename BasicJsonType::value_type;
10829 using difference_type = typename BasicJsonType::difference_type;
10831 using pointer = typename std::conditional<std::is_const<BasicJsonType>::value,
10832 typename BasicJsonType::const_pointer,
10833 typename BasicJsonType::pointer>::type;
10835 using reference =
10836 typename std::conditional<std::is_const<BasicJsonType>::value,
10837 typename BasicJsonType::const_reference,
10838 typename BasicJsonType::reference>::type;
10839
10841 iter_impl() = default;
10842
10849 explicit iter_impl(pointer object) noexcept : m_object(object)
10850 {
10851 JSON_ASSERT(m_object != nullptr);
10852
10853 switch (m_object->m_type)
10854 {
10855 case value_t::object:
10856 {
10857 m_it.object_iterator = typename object_t::iterator();
10858 break;
10859 }
10860
10861 case value_t::array:
10862 {
10863 m_it.array_iterator = typename array_t::iterator();
10864 break;
10865 }
10866
10867 default:
10868 {
10869 m_it.primitive_iterator = primitive_iterator_t();
10870 break;
10871 }
10872 }
10873 }
10874
10891 iter_impl(const iter_impl<const BasicJsonType>& other) noexcept
10892 : m_object(other.m_object), m_it(other.m_it)
10893 {}
10894
10901 iter_impl& operator=(const iter_impl<const BasicJsonType>& other) noexcept
10902 {
10903 m_object = other.m_object;
10904 m_it = other.m_it;
10905 return *this;
10906 }
10907
10913 iter_impl(const iter_impl<typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type>& other) noexcept
10914 : m_object(other.m_object), m_it(other.m_it)
10915 {}
10916
10923 iter_impl& operator=(const iter_impl<typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type>& other) noexcept
10924 {
10925 m_object = other.m_object;
10926 m_it = other.m_it;
10927 return *this;
10928 }
10929
10930 private:
10935 void set_begin() noexcept
10936 {
10937 JSON_ASSERT(m_object != nullptr);
10938
10939 switch (m_object->m_type)
10940 {
10941 case value_t::object:
10942 {
10943 m_it.object_iterator = m_object->m_value.object->begin();
10944 break;
10945 }
10946
10947 case value_t::array:
10948 {
10949 m_it.array_iterator = m_object->m_value.array->begin();
10950 break;
10951 }
10952
10953 case value_t::null:
10954 {
10955 // set to end so begin()==end() is true: null is empty
10956 m_it.primitive_iterator.set_end();
10957 break;
10958 }
10959
10960 default:
10961 {
10962 m_it.primitive_iterator.set_begin();
10963 break;
10964 }
10965 }
10966 }
10967
10972 void set_end() noexcept
10973 {
10974 JSON_ASSERT(m_object != nullptr);
10975
10976 switch (m_object->m_type)
10977 {
10978 case value_t::object:
10979 {
10980 m_it.object_iterator = m_object->m_value.object->end();
10981 break;
10982 }
10983
10984 case value_t::array:
10985 {
10986 m_it.array_iterator = m_object->m_value.array->end();
10987 break;
10988 }
10989
10990 default:
10991 {
10992 m_it.primitive_iterator.set_end();
10993 break;
10994 }
10995 }
10996 }
10997
10998 public:
11003 reference operator*() const
11004 {
11005 JSON_ASSERT(m_object != nullptr);
11006
11007 switch (m_object->m_type)
11008 {
11009 case value_t::object:
11010 {
11011 JSON_ASSERT(m_it.object_iterator != m_object->m_value.object->end());
11012 return m_it.object_iterator->second;
11013 }
11014
11015 case value_t::array:
11016 {
11017 JSON_ASSERT(m_it.array_iterator != m_object->m_value.array->end());
11018 return *m_it.array_iterator;
11019 }
11020
11021 case value_t::null:
11022 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
11023
11024 default:
11025 {
11026 if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(m_it.primitive_iterator.is_begin()))
11027 {
11028 return *m_object;
11029 }
11030
11031 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
11032 }
11033 }
11034 }
11035
11040 pointer operator->() const
11041 {
11042 JSON_ASSERT(m_object != nullptr);
11043
11044 switch (m_object->m_type)
11045 {
11046 case value_t::object:
11047 {
11048 JSON_ASSERT(m_it.object_iterator != m_object->m_value.object->end());
11049 return &(m_it.object_iterator->second);
11050 }
11051
11052 case value_t::array:
11053 {
11054 JSON_ASSERT(m_it.array_iterator != m_object->m_value.array->end());
11055 return &*m_it.array_iterator;
11056 }
11057
11058 default:
11059 {
11060 if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(m_it.primitive_iterator.is_begin()))
11061 {
11062 return m_object;
11063 }
11064
11065 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
11066 }
11067 }
11068 }
11069
11074 iter_impl const operator++(int)
11075 {
11076 auto result = *this;
11077 ++(*this);
11078 return result;
11079 }
11080
11085 iter_impl& operator++()
11086 {
11087 JSON_ASSERT(m_object != nullptr);
11088
11089 switch (m_object->m_type)
11090 {
11091 case value_t::object:
11092 {
11093 std::advance(m_it.object_iterator, 1);
11094 break;
11095 }
11096
11097 case value_t::array:
11098 {
11099 std::advance(m_it.array_iterator, 1);
11100 break;
11101 }
11102
11103 default:
11104 {
11105 ++m_it.primitive_iterator;
11106 break;
11107 }
11108 }
11109
11110 return *this;
11111 }
11112
11117 iter_impl const operator--(int)
11118 {
11119 auto result = *this;
11120 --(*this);
11121 return result;
11122 }
11123
11128 iter_impl& operator--()
11129 {
11130 JSON_ASSERT(m_object != nullptr);
11131
11132 switch (m_object->m_type)
11133 {
11134 case value_t::object:
11135 {
11136 std::advance(m_it.object_iterator, -1);
11137 break;
11138 }
11139
11140 case value_t::array:
11141 {
11142 std::advance(m_it.array_iterator, -1);
11143 break;
11144 }
11145
11146 default:
11147 {
11148 --m_it.primitive_iterator;
11149 break;
11150 }
11151 }
11152
11153 return *this;
11154 }
11155
11160 bool operator==(const iter_impl& other) const
11161 {
11162 // if objects are not the same, the comparison is undefined
11163 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(m_object != other.m_object))
11164 {
11165 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(212, "cannot compare iterators of different containers"));
11166 }
11167
11168 JSON_ASSERT(m_object != nullptr);
11169
11170 switch (m_object->m_type)
11171 {
11172 case value_t::object:
11173 return (m_it.object_iterator == other.m_it.object_iterator);
11174
11175 case value_t::array:
11176 return (m_it.array_iterator == other.m_it.array_iterator);
11177
11178 default:
11179 return (m_it.primitive_iterator == other.m_it.primitive_iterator);
11180 }
11181 }
11182
11187 bool operator!=(const iter_impl& other) const
11188 {
11189 return !operator==(other);
11190 }
11191
11196 bool operator<(const iter_impl& other) const
11197 {
11198 // if objects are not the same, the comparison is undefined
11199 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(m_object != other.m_object))
11200 {
11201 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(212, "cannot compare iterators of different containers"));
11202 }
11203
11204 JSON_ASSERT(m_object != nullptr);
11205
11206 switch (m_object->m_type)
11207 {
11208 case value_t::object:
11209 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(213, "cannot compare order of object iterators"));
11210
11211 case value_t::array:
11212 return (m_it.array_iterator < other.m_it.array_iterator);
11213
11214 default:
11215 return (m_it.primitive_iterator < other.m_it.primitive_iterator);
11216 }
11217 }
11218
11223 bool operator<=(const iter_impl& other) const
11224 {
11225 return !other.operator < (*this);
11226 }
11227
11232 bool operator>(const iter_impl& other) const
11233 {
11234 return !operator<=(other);
11235 }
11236
11241 bool operator>=(const iter_impl& other) const
11242 {
11243 return !operator<(other);
11244 }
11245
11250 iter_impl& operator+=(difference_type i)
11251 {
11252 JSON_ASSERT(m_object != nullptr);
11253
11254 switch (m_object->m_type)
11255 {
11256 case value_t::object:
11257 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(209, "cannot use offsets with object iterators"));
11258
11259 case value_t::array:
11260 {
11261 std::advance(m_it.array_iterator, i);
11262 break;
11263 }
11264
11265 default:
11266 {
11267 m_it.primitive_iterator += i;
11268 break;
11269 }
11270 }
11271
11272 return *this;
11273 }
11274
11279 iter_impl& operator-=(difference_type i)
11280 {
11281 return operator+=(-i);
11282 }
11283
11288 iter_impl operator+(difference_type i) const
11289 {
11290 auto result = *this;
11291 result += i;
11292 return result;
11293 }
11294
11299 friend iter_impl operator+(difference_type i, const iter_impl& it)
11300 {
11301 auto result = it;
11302 result += i;
11303 return result;
11304 }
11305
11310 iter_impl operator-(difference_type i) const
11311 {
11312 auto result = *this;
11313 result -= i;
11314 return result;
11315 }
11316
11321 difference_type operator-(const iter_impl& other) const
11322 {
11323 JSON_ASSERT(m_object != nullptr);
11324
11325 switch (m_object->m_type)
11326 {
11327 case value_t::object:
11328 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(209, "cannot use offsets with object iterators"));
11329
11330 case value_t::array:
11331 return m_it.array_iterator - other.m_it.array_iterator;
11332
11333 default:
11334 return m_it.primitive_iterator - other.m_it.primitive_iterator;
11335 }
11336 }
11337
11342 reference operator[](difference_type n) const
11343 {
11344 JSON_ASSERT(m_object != nullptr);
11345
11346 switch (m_object->m_type)
11347 {
11348 case value_t::object:
11349 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(208, "cannot use operator[] for object iterators"));
11350
11351 case value_t::array:
11352 return *std::next(m_it.array_iterator, n);
11353
11354 case value_t::null:
11355 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
11356
11357 default:
11358 {
11359 if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(m_it.primitive_iterator.get_value() == -n))
11360 {
11361 return *m_object;
11362 }
11363
11364 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
11365 }
11366 }
11367 }
11368
11373 const typename object_t::key_type& key() const
11374 {
11375 JSON_ASSERT(m_object != nullptr);
11376
11377 if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(m_object->is_object()))
11378 {
11379 return m_it.object_iterator->first;
11380 }
11381
11382 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(207, "cannot use key() for non-object iterators"));
11383 }
11384
11389 reference value() const
11390 {
11391 return operator*();
11392 }
11393
11394 private:
11396 pointer m_object = nullptr;
11398 internal_iterator<typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type> m_it {};
11399 };
11400 } // namespace detail
11401} // namespace nlohmann

11438 template<typename Base>
11439 class json_reverse_iterator : public std::reverse_iterator<Base>
11440 {
11441 public:
11442 using difference_type = std::ptrdiff_t;
11444 using base_iterator = std::reverse_iterator<Base>;
11446 using reference = typename Base::reference;
11447
11449 explicit json_reverse_iterator(const typename base_iterator::iterator_type& it) noexcept
11450 : base_iterator(it) {}
11451
11453 explicit json_reverse_iterator(const base_iterator& it) noexcept : base_iterator(it) {}
11454
11456 json_reverse_iterator const operator++(int)
11457 {
11458 return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator>(base_iterator::operator++(1));
11459 }
11460
11462 json_reverse_iterator& operator++()
11463 {
11464 return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator&>(base_iterator::operator++());
11465 }
11466

11469 {
11470 return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator>(base_iterator::operator--(1));
11471 }
11472

11475 {
11476 return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator&>(base_iterator::operator--());
11477 }
11478

11481 {
11482 return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator&>(base_iterator::operator+=(i));
11483 }

11487 {
11488 return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator>(base_iterator::operator+(i));
11489 }

11493 {
11494 return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator>(base_iterator::operator-(i));
11495 }

11499 {
11500 return base_iterator(*this) - base_iterator(other);
11501 }
11502

11505 {
11506 return *(this->operator+(n));
11507 }

11511 {

11514 }

11518 {

11578 : reference_tokens(split(s))

11596 {

11598 std::string{},
11599 [](const std::string & a, const std::string & b)
11600 {
11601 return a + "/" + escape(b);
11602 });

11852
11853 private:
11864 static typename BasicJsonType::size_type array_index(const std::string& s)
11865 {
11866 using size_type = typename BasicJsonType::size_type;
11867
11868 // error condition (cf. RFC 6901, Sect. 4)
11869 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(s.size() > 1 && s[0] == '0'))
11870 {
11871 JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(106, 0,
11872 "array index '" + s +
11873 "' must not begin with '0'"));
11874 }
11875
11876 // error condition (cf. RFC 6901, Sect. 4)
11877 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(s.size() > 1 && !(s[0] >= '1' && s[0] <= '9')))
11878 {
11879 JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(109, 0, "array index '" + s + "' is not a number"));
11880 }
11881
11882 std::size_t processed_chars = 0;
11883 unsigned long long res = 0;
11884 JSON_TRY
11885 {
11886 res = std::stoull(s, &processed_chars);
11887 }
11888 JSON_CATCH(std::out_of_range&)
11889 {
11890 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(404, "unresolved reference token '" + s + "'"));
11891 }
11892
11893 // check if the string was completely read
11894 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(processed_chars != s.size()))
11895 {
11896 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(404, "unresolved reference token '" + s + "'"));
11897 }
11898
11899 // only triggered on special platforms (like 32bit), see also
11900 // https://github.com/nlohmann/json/pull/2203
11901 if (res >= static_cast<unsigned long long>((std::numeric_limits<size_type>::max)()))
11902 {
11903 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(410, "array index " + s + " exceeds size_type")); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
11904 }
11905
11906 return static_cast<size_type>(res);
11907 }
11908
11909 json_pointer top() const
11910 {
11911 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(empty()))
11912 {
11913 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(405, "JSON pointer has no parent"));
11914 }
11915
11916 json_pointer result = *this;
11917 result.reference_tokens = {reference_tokens[0]};
11918 return result;
11919 }
11920
11929 BasicJsonType& get_and_create(BasicJsonType& j) const
11930 {
11931 auto result = &j;
11932
11933 // in case no reference tokens exist, return a reference to the JSON value
11934 // j which will be overwritten by a primitive value
11935 for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
11936 {
11937 switch (result->type())
11938 {
11939 case detail::value_t::null:
11940 {
11941 if (reference_token == "0")
11942 {
11943 // start a new array if reference token is 0
11944 result = &result->operator[](0);
11945 }
11946 else
11947 {
11948 // start a new object otherwise
11949 result = &result->operator[](reference_token);
11950 }
11951 break;
11952 }
11953
11954 case detail::value_t::object:
11955 {
11956 // create an entry in the object
11957 result = &result->operator[](reference_token);
11958 break;
11959 }
11960
11961 case detail::value_t::array:
11962 {
11963 // create an entry in the array
11964 result = &result->operator[](array_index(reference_token));
11965 break;
11966 }
11967
11968 /*
11969 The following code is only reached if there exists a reference
11970 token _and_ the current value is primitive. In this case, we have
11971 an error situation, because primitive values may only occur as
11972 single value; that is, with an empty list of reference tokens.
11973 */
11974 default:
11975 JSON_THROW(detail::type_error::create(313, "invalid value to unflatten"));
11976 }
11977 }
11978
11979 return *result;
11980 }
11981
12001 BasicJsonType& get_unchecked(BasicJsonType* ptr) const
12002 {
12003 for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
12004 {
12005 // convert null values to arrays or objects before continuing
12006 if (ptr->is_null())
12007 {
12008 // check if reference token is a number
12009 const bool nums =
12010 std::all_of(reference_token.begin(), reference_token.end(),
12011 [](const unsigned char x)
12012 {
12013 return std::isdigit(x);
12014 });
12015
12016 // change value to array for numbers or "-" or to object otherwise
12017 *ptr = (nums || reference_token == "-")
12018 ? detail::value_t::array
12019 : detail::value_t::object;
12020 }
12021
12022 switch (ptr->type())
12023 {
12024 case detail::value_t::object:
12025 {
12026 // use unchecked object access
12027 ptr = &ptr->operator[](reference_token);
12028 break;
12029 }
12030
12031 case detail::value_t::array:
12032 {
12033 if (reference_token == "-")
12034 {
12035 // explicitly treat "-" as index beyond the end
12036 ptr = &ptr->operator[](ptr->m_value.array->size());
12037 }
12038 else
12039 {
12040 // convert array index to number; unchecked access
12041 ptr = &ptr->operator[](array_index(reference_token));
12042 }
12043 break;
12044 }
12045
12046 default:
12047 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(404, "unresolved reference token '" + reference_token + "'"));
12048 }
12049 }
12050
12051 return *ptr;
12052 }
12053
12060 BasicJsonType& get_checked(BasicJsonType* ptr) const
12061 {
12062 for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
12063 {
12064 switch (ptr->type())
12065 {
12066 case detail::value_t::object:
12067 {
12068 // note: at performs range check
12069 ptr = &ptr->at(reference_token);
12070 break;
12071 }
12072
12073 case detail::value_t::array:
12074 {
12075 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(reference_token == "-"))
12076 {
12077 // "-" always fails the range check
12078 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(402,
12079 "array index '-' (" + std::to_string(ptr->m_value.array->size()) +
12080 ") is out of range"));
12081 }
12082
12083 // note: at performs range check
12084 ptr = &ptr->at(array_index(reference_token));
12085 break;
12086 }
12087
12088 default:
12089 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(404, "unresolved reference token '" + reference_token + "'"));
12090 }
12091 }
12092
12093 return *ptr;
12094 }
12095
12109 const BasicJsonType& get_unchecked(const BasicJsonType* ptr) const
12110 {
12111 for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
12112 {
12113 switch (ptr->type())
12114 {
12115 case detail::value_t::object:
12116 {
12117 // use unchecked object access
12118 ptr = &ptr->operator[](reference_token);
12119 break;
12120 }
12121
12122 case detail::value_t::array:
12123 {
12124 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(reference_token == "-"))
12125 {
12126 // "-" cannot be used for const access
12127 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(402,
12128 "array index '-' (" + std::to_string(ptr->m_value.array->size()) +
12129 ") is out of range"));
12130 }
12131
12132 // use unchecked array access
12133 ptr = &ptr->operator[](array_index(reference_token));
12134 break;
12135 }
12136
12137 default:
12138 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(404, "unresolved reference token '" + reference_token + "'"));
12139 }
12140 }
12141
12142 return *ptr;
12143 }
12144
12151 const BasicJsonType& get_checked(const BasicJsonType* ptr) const
12152 {
12153 for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
12154 {
12155 switch (ptr->type())
12156 {
12157 case detail::value_t::object:
12158 {
12159 // note: at performs range check
12160 ptr = &ptr->at(reference_token);
12161 break;
12162 }
12163
12164 case detail::value_t::array:
12165 {
12166 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(reference_token == "-"))
12167 {
12168 // "-" always fails the range check
12169 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(402,
12170 "array index '-' (" + std::to_string(ptr->m_value.array->size()) +
12171 ") is out of range"));
12172 }
12173
12174 // note: at performs range check
12175 ptr = &ptr->at(array_index(reference_token));
12176 break;
12177 }
12178
12179 default:
12180 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(404, "unresolved reference token '" + reference_token + "'"));
12181 }
12182 }
12183
12184 return *ptr;
12185 }
12186
12191 bool contains(const BasicJsonType* ptr) const
12192 {
12193 for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
12194 {
12195 switch (ptr->type())
12196 {
12197 case detail::value_t::object:
12198 {
12199 if (!ptr->contains(reference_token))
12200 {
12201 // we did not find the key in the object
12202 return false;
12203 }
12204
12205 ptr = &ptr->operator[](reference_token);
12206 break;
12207 }
12208
12209 case detail::value_t::array:
12210 {
12211 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(reference_token == "-"))
12212 {
12213 // "-" always fails the range check
12214 return false;
12215 }
12216 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(reference_token.size() == 1 && !("0" <= reference_token && reference_token <= "9")))
12217 {
12218 // invalid char
12219 return false;
12220 }
12221 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(reference_token.size() > 1))
12222 {
12223 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!('1' <= reference_token[0] && reference_token[0] <= '9')))
12224 {
12225 // first char should be between '1' and '9'
12226 return false;
12227 }
12228 for (std::size_t i = 1; i < reference_token.size(); i++)
12229 {
12230 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!('0' <= reference_token[i] && reference_token[i] <= '9')))
12231 {
12232 // other char should be between '0' and '9'
12233 return false;
12234 }
12235 }
12236 }
12237
12238 const auto idx = array_index(reference_token);
12239 if (idx >= ptr->size())
12240 {
12241 // index out of range
12242 return false;
12243 }
12244
12245 ptr = &ptr->operator[](idx);
12246 break;
12247 }
12248
12249 default:
12250 {
12251 // we do not expect primitive values if there is still a
12252 // reference token to process
12253 return false;
12254 }
12255 }
12256 }
12257
12258 // no reference token left means we found a primitive value
12259 return true;
12260 }
12261
12271 static std::vector<std::string> split(const std::string& reference_string)
12272 {
12273 std::vector<std::string> result;
12274
12275 // special case: empty reference string -> no reference tokens
12276 if (reference_string.empty())
12277 {
12278 return result;
12279 }
12280
12281 // check if nonempty reference string begins with slash
12282 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(reference_string[0] != '/'))
12283 {
12284 JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(107, 1,
12285 "JSON pointer must be empty or begin with '/' - was: '" +
12286 reference_string + "'"));
12287 }
12288
12289 // extract the reference tokens:
12290 // - slash: position of the last read slash (or end of string)
12291 // - start: position after the previous slash
12292 for (
12293 // search for the first slash after the first character
12294 std::size_t slash = reference_string.find_first_of('/', 1),
12295 // set the beginning of the first reference token
12296 start = 1;
12297 // we can stop if start == 0 (if slash == std::string::npos)
12298 start != 0;
12299 // set the beginning of the next reference token
12300 // (will eventually be 0 if slash == std::string::npos)
12301 start = (slash == std::string::npos) ? 0 : slash + 1,
12302 // find next slash
12303 slash = reference_string.find_first_of('/', start))
12304 {
12305 // use the text between the beginning of the reference token
12306 // (start) and the last slash (slash).
12307 auto reference_token = reference_string.substr(start, slash - start);
12308
12309 // check reference tokens are properly escaped
12310 for (std::size_t pos = reference_token.find_first_of('~');
12311 pos != std::string::npos;
12312 pos = reference_token.find_first_of('~', pos + 1))
12313 {
12314 JSON_ASSERT(reference_token[pos] == '~');
12315
12316 // ~ must be followed by 0 or 1
12317 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(pos == reference_token.size() - 1 ||
12318 (reference_token[pos + 1] != '0' &&
12319 reference_token[pos + 1] != '1')))
12320 {
12321 JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(108, 0, "escape character '~' must be followed with '0' or '1'"));
12322 }
12323 }
12324
12325 // finally, store the reference token
12326 unescape(reference_token);
12327 result.push_back(reference_token);
12328 }
12329
12330 return result;
12331 }
12332
12346 static void replace_substring(std::string& s, const std::string& f,
12347 const std::string& t)
12348 {
12349 JSON_ASSERT(!f.empty());
12350 for (auto pos = s.find(f); // find first occurrence of f
12351 pos != std::string::npos; // make sure f was found
12352 s.replace(pos, f.size(), t), // replace with t, and
12353 pos = s.find(f, pos + t.size())) // find next occurrence of f
12354 {}
12355 }
12356
12358 static std::string escape(std::string s)
12359 {
12360 replace_substring(s, "~", "~0");
12361 replace_substring(s, "/", "~1");
12362 return s;
12363 }
12364
12366 static void unescape(std::string& s)
12367 {
12368 replace_substring(s, "~1", "/");
12369 replace_substring(s, "~0", "~");
12370 }
12371
12379 static void flatten(const std::string& reference_string,
12380 const BasicJsonType& value,
12381 BasicJsonType& result)
12382 {
12383 switch (value.type())
12384 {
12385 case detail::value_t::array:
12386 {
12387 if (value.m_value.array->empty())
12388 {
12389 // flatten empty array as null
12390 result[reference_string] = nullptr;
12391 }
12392 else
12393 {
12394 // iterate array and use index as reference string
12395 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < value.m_value.array->size(); ++i)
12396 {
12397 flatten(reference_string + "/" + std::to_string(i),
12398 value.m_value.array->operator[](i), result);
12399 }
12400 }
12401 break;
12402 }
12403
12404 case detail::value_t::object:
12405 {
12406 if (value.m_value.object->empty())
12407 {
12408 // flatten empty object as null
12409 result[reference_string] = nullptr;
12410 }
12411 else
12412 {
12413 // iterate object and use keys as reference string
12414 for (const auto& element : *value.m_value.object)
12415 {
12416 flatten(reference_string + "/" + escape(element.first), element.second, result);
12417 }
12418 }
12419 break;
12420 }
12421
12422 default:
12423 {
12424 // add primitive value with its reference string
12425 result[reference_string] = value;
12426 break;
12427 }
12428 }
12429 }
12430
12441 static BasicJsonType
12442 unflatten(const BasicJsonType& value)
12443 {
12444 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!value.is_object()))
12445 {
12446 JSON_THROW(detail::type_error::create(314, "only objects can be unflattened"));
12447 }
12448
12449 BasicJsonType result;
12450
12451 // iterate the JSON object values
12452 for (const auto& element : *value.m_value.object)
12453 {
12454 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!element.second.is_primitive()))
12455 {
12456 JSON_THROW(detail::type_error::create(315, "values in object must be primitive"));
12457 }
12458
12459 // assign value to reference pointed to by JSON pointer; Note that if
12460 // the JSON pointer is "" (i.e., points to the whole value), function
12461 // get_and_create returns a reference to result itself. An assignment
12462 // will then create a primitive value.
12463 json_pointer(element.first).get_and_create(result) = element.second;
12464 }
12465
12466 return result;
12467 }
12468
12480 friend bool operator==(json_pointer const& lhs,
12481 json_pointer const& rhs) noexcept
12482 {
12483 return lhs.reference_tokens == rhs.reference_tokens;
12484 }
12485
12497 friend bool operator!=(json_pointer const& lhs,
12498 json_pointer const& rhs) noexcept
12499 {
12500 return !(lhs == rhs);
12501 }
12502
12504 std::vector<std::string> reference_tokens;
12505 };
12506} // namespace nlohmann
12507
12508// #include <nlohmann/detail/json_ref.hpp>
12509
12510
12511#include <initializer_list>
12512#include <utility>
12513
12514// #include <nlohmann/detail/meta/type_traits.hpp>
12515
12516
12517namespace nlohmann
12518{
12519 namespace detail
12520 {
12521 template<typename BasicJsonType>
12522 class json_ref
12523 {
12524 public:
12525 using value_type = BasicJsonType;
12526
12527 json_ref(value_type&& value)
12528 : owned_value(std::move(value))
12529 , value_ref(&owned_value)
12530 , is_rvalue(true)
12531 {}
12532
12533 json_ref(const value_type& value)
12534 : value_ref(const_cast<value_type*>(&value))
12535 , is_rvalue(false)
12536 {}
12537
12538 json_ref(std::initializer_list<json_ref> init)
12539 : owned_value(init)
12540 , value_ref(&owned_value)
12541 , is_rvalue(true)
12542 {}
12543
12544 template <
12545 class... Args,
12546 enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<value_type, Args...>::value, int> = 0 >
12547 json_ref(Args && ... args)
12548 : owned_value(std::forward<Args>(args)...)
12549 , value_ref(&owned_value)
12550 , is_rvalue(true)
12551 {}
12552
12553 // class should be movable only
12554 json_ref(json_ref&&) = default;
12555 json_ref(const json_ref&) = delete;
12556 json_ref& operator=(const json_ref&) = delete;
12557 json_ref& operator=(json_ref&&) = delete;
12558 ~json_ref() = default;
12559
12560 value_type moved_or_copied() const
12561 {
12562 if (is_rvalue)
12563 {
12564 return std::move(*value_ref);
12565 }
12566 return *value_ref;
12567 }
12568
12569 value_type const& operator*() const
12570 {
12571 return *static_cast<value_type const*>(value_ref);
12572 }
12573
12574 value_type const* operator->() const
12575 {
12576 return static_cast<value_type const*>(value_ref);
12577 }
12578
12579 private:
12580 mutable value_type owned_value = nullptr;
12581 value_type* value_ref = nullptr;
12582 const bool is_rvalue = true;
12583 };
12584 } // namespace detail
12585} // namespace nlohmann
