12627 template<typename CharType> struct output_adapter_protocol
12628 {
12629 virtual void write_character(CharType c) = 0;
12630 virtual void write_characters(const CharType* s, std::size_t length) = 0;
12631 virtual ~output_adapter_protocol() = default;
12632 };
12633
12635 template<typename CharType>
12636 using output_adapter_t = std::shared_ptr<output_adapter_protocol<CharType>>;
12637
12639 template<typename CharType>
12640 class output_vector_adapter : public output_adapter_protocol<CharType>
12641 {
12642 public:
12643 explicit output_vector_adapter(std::vector<CharType>& vec) noexcept
12644 : v(vec)
12645 {}
12646
12647 void write_character(CharType c) override
12648 {
12649 v.push_back(c);
12650 }
12651
12652 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(2)
12653 void write_characters(const CharType* s, std::size_t length) override
12654 {
12655 std::copy(s, s + length, std::back_inserter(v));
12656 }
12657
12658 private:
12659 std::vector<CharType>& v;
12660 };
12661
12663 template<typename CharType>
12664 class output_stream_adapter : public output_adapter_protocol<CharType>
12665 {
12666 public:
12667 explicit output_stream_adapter(std::basic_ostream<CharType>& s) noexcept
12668 : stream(s)
12669 {}
12670
12671 void write_character(CharType c) override
12672 {
12673 stream.put(c);
12674 }
12675
12676 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(2)
12677 void write_characters(const CharType* s, std::size_t length) override
12678 {
12679 stream.write(s, static_cast<std::streamsize>(length));
12680 }
12681
12682 private:
12683 std::basic_ostream<CharType>& stream;
12684 };
12685
12687 template<typename CharType, typename StringType = std::basic_string<CharType>>
12688 class output_string_adapter : public output_adapter_protocol<CharType>
12689 {
12690 public:
12691 explicit output_string_adapter(StringType& s) noexcept
12692 : str(s)
12693 {}
12694
12695 void write_character(CharType c) override
12696 {
12697 str.push_back(c);
12698 }
12699
12700 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(2)
12701 void write_characters(const CharType* s, std::size_t length) override
12702 {
12703 str.append(s, length);
12704 }
12705
12706 private:
12707 StringType& str;
12708 };
12709
12710 template<typename CharType, typename StringType = std::basic_string<CharType>>
12711 class output_adapter
12712 {
12713 public:
12714 output_adapter(std::vector<CharType>& vec)
12715 : oa(std::make_shared<output_vector_adapter<CharType>>(vec)) {}
12716
12717 output_adapter(std::basic_ostream<CharType>& s)
12718 : oa(std::make_shared<output_stream_adapter<CharType>>(s)) {}
12719
12720 output_adapter(StringType& s)
12721 : oa(std::make_shared<output_string_adapter<CharType, StringType>>(s)) {}
12722
12723 operator output_adapter_t<CharType>()
12724 {
12725 return oa;
12726 }
12727
12728 private:
12729 output_adapter_t<CharType> oa = nullptr;
12730 };
12731 } // namespace detail
12732} // namespace nlohmann
12733
12734
12735namespace nlohmann
12736{
12737 namespace detail
12738 {
12740 // binary writer //
12742
12746 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename CharType>
12747 class binary_writer
12748 {
12749 using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
12750 using binary_t = typename BasicJsonType::binary_t;
12751 using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
12752
12753 public:
12759 explicit binary_writer(output_adapter_t<CharType> adapter) : oa(adapter)
12760 {
12761 JSON_ASSERT(oa);
12762 }
12763
12768 void write_bson(const BasicJsonType& j)
12769 {
12770 switch (j.type())
12771 {
12772 case value_t::object:
12773 {
12774 write_bson_object(*j.m_value.object);
12775 break;
12776 }
12777
12778 default:
12779 {
12780 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(317, "to serialize to BSON, top-level type must be object, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
12781 }
12782 }
12783 }
12784
12788 void write_cbor(const BasicJsonType& j)
12789 {
12790 switch (j.type())
12791 {
12792 case value_t::null:
12793 {
12794 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xF6));
12795 break;
12796 }
12797
12798 case value_t::boolean:
12799 {
12800 oa->write_character(j.m_value.boolean
12801 ? to_char_type(0xF5)
12802 : to_char_type(0xF4));
12803 break;
12804 }
12805
12806 case value_t::number_integer:
12807 {
12808 if (j.m_value.number_integer >= 0)
12809 {
12810 // CBOR does not differentiate between positive signed
12811 // integers and unsigned integers. Therefore, we used the
12812 // code from the value_t::number_unsigned case here.
12813 if (j.m_value.number_integer <= 0x17)
12814 {
12815 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
12816 }
12817 else if (j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
12818 {
12819 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x18));
12820 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
12821 }
12822 else if (j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
12823 {
12824 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x19));
12825 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
12826 }
12827 else if (j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
12828 {
12829 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x1A));
12830 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
12831 }
12832 else
12833 {
12834 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x1B));
12835 write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
12836 }
12837 }
12838 else
12839 {
12840 // The conversions below encode the sign in the first
12841 // byte, and the value is converted to a positive number.
12842 const auto positive_number = -1 - j.m_value.number_integer;
12843 if (j.m_value.number_integer >= -24)
12844 {
12845 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0x20 + positive_number));
12846 }
12847 else if (positive_number <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
12848 {
12849 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x38));
12850 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(positive_number));
12851 }
12852 else if (positive_number <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
12853 {
12854 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x39));
12855 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(positive_number));
12856 }
12857 else if (positive_number <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
12858 {
12859 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x3A));
12860 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(positive_number));
12861 }
12862 else
12863 {
12864 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x3B));
12865 write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(positive_number));
12866 }
12867 }
12868 break;
12869 }
12870
12871 case value_t::number_unsigned:
12872 {
12873 if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= 0x17)
12874 {
12875 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
12876 }
12877 else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
12878 {
12879 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x18));
12880 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
12881 }
12882 else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
12883 {
12884 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x19));
12885 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
12886 }
12887 else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
12888 {
12889 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x1A));
12890 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
12891 }
12892 else
12893 {
12894 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x1B));
12895 write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
12896 }
12897 break;
12898 }
12899
12900 case value_t::number_float:
12901 {
12902 if (std::isnan(j.m_value.number_float))
12903 {
12904 // NaN is 0xf97e00 in CBOR
12905 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xF9));
12906 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x7E));
12907 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x00));
12908 }
12909 else if (std::isinf(j.m_value.number_float))
12910 {
12911 // Infinity is 0xf97c00, -Infinity is 0xf9fc00
12912 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xf9));
12913 oa->write_character(j.m_value.number_float > 0 ? to_char_type(0x7C) : to_char_type(0xFC));
12914 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x00));
12915 }
12916 else
12917 {
12918 write_compact_float(j.m_value.number_float, detail::input_format_t::cbor);
12919 }
12920 break;
12921 }
12922
12923 case value_t::string:
12924 {
12925 // step 1: write control byte and the string length
12926 const auto N = j.m_value.string->size();
12927 if (N <= 0x17)
12928 {
12929 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0x60 + N));
12930 }
12931 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
12932 {
12933 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x78));
12934 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(N));
12935 }
12936 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
12937 {
12938 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x79));
12939 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
12940 }
12941 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
12942 {
12943 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x7A));
12944 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
12945 }
12946 // LCOV_EXCL_START
12947 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint64_t>::max)())
12948 {
12949 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x7B));
12950 write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(N));
12951 }
12952 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
12953
12954 // step 2: write the string
12955 oa->write_characters(
12956 reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(j.m_value.string->c_str()),
12957 j.m_value.string->size());
12958 break;
12959 }
12960
12961 case value_t::array:
12962 {
12963 // step 1: write control byte and the array size
12964 const auto N = j.m_value.array->size();
12965 if (N <= 0x17)
12966 {
12967 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0x80 + N));
12968 }
12969 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
12970 {
12971 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x98));
12972 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(N));
12973 }
12974 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
12975 {
12976 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x99));
12977 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
12978 }
12979 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
12980 {
12981 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x9A));
12982 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
12983 }
12984 // LCOV_EXCL_START
12985 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint64_t>::max)())
12986 {
12987 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x9B));
12988 write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(N));
12989 }
12990 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
12991
12992 // step 2: write each element
12993 for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.array)
12994 {
12995 write_cbor(el);
12996 }
12997 break;
12998 }
12999
13000 case value_t::binary:
13001 {
13002 if (j.m_value.binary->has_subtype())
13003 {
13004 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0xd8));
13005 write_number(j.m_value.binary->subtype());
13006 }
13007
13008 // step 1: write control byte and the binary array size
13009 const auto N = j.m_value.binary->size();
13010 if (N <= 0x17)
13011 {
13012 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0x40 + N));
13013 }
13014 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
13015 {
13016 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x58));
13017 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(N));
13018 }
13019 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
13020 {
13021 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x59));
13022 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
13023 }
13024 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
13025 {
13026 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x5A));
13027 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
13028 }
13029 // LCOV_EXCL_START
13030 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint64_t>::max)())
13031 {
13032 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x5B));
13033 write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(N));
13034 }
13035 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
13036
13037 // step 2: write each element
13038 oa->write_characters(
13039 reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(j.m_value.binary->data()),
13040 N);
13041
13042 break;
13043 }
13044
13045 case value_t::object:
13046 {
13047 // step 1: write control byte and the object size
13048 const auto N = j.m_value.object->size();
13049 if (N <= 0x17)
13050 {
13051 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0xA0 + N));
13052 }
13053 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
13054 {
13055 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xB8));
13056 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(N));
13057 }
13058 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
13059 {
13060 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xB9));
13061 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
13062 }
13063 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
13064 {
13065 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xBA));
13066 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
13067 }
13068 // LCOV_EXCL_START
13069 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint64_t>::max)())
13070 {
13071 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xBB));
13072 write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(N));
13073 }
13074 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
13075
13076 // step 2: write each element
13077 for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.object)
13078 {
13079 write_cbor(el.first);
13080 write_cbor(el.second);
13081 }
13082 break;
13083 }
13084
13085 default:
13086 break;
13087 }
13088 }
13089
13093 void write_msgpack(const BasicJsonType& j)
13094 {
13095 switch (j.type())
13096 {
13097 case value_t::null: // nil
13098 {
13099 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xC0));
13100 break;
13101 }
13102
13103 case value_t::boolean: // true and false
13104 {
13105 oa->write_character(j.m_value.boolean
13106 ? to_char_type(0xC3)
13107 : to_char_type(0xC2));
13108 break;
13109 }
13110
13111 case value_t::number_integer:
13112 {
13113 if (j.m_value.number_integer >= 0)
13114 {
13115 // MessagePack does not differentiate between positive
13116 // signed integers and unsigned integers. Therefore, we used
13117 // the code from the value_t::number_unsigned case here.
13118 if (j.m_value.number_unsigned < 128)
13119 {
13120 // positive fixnum
13121 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
13122 }
13123 else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
13124 {
13125 // uint 8
13126 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCC));
13127 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
13128 }
13129 else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
13130 {
13131 // uint 16
13132 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCD));
13133 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
13134 }
13135 else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
13136 {
13137 // uint 32
13138 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCE));
13139 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
13140 }
13141 else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint64_t>::max)())
13142 {
13143 // uint 64
13144 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCF));
13145 write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
13146 }
13147 }
13148 else
13149 {
13150 if (j.m_value.number_integer >= -32)
13151 {
13152 // negative fixnum
13153 write_number(static_cast<std::int8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
13154 }
13155 else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<std::int8_t>::min)() &&
13156 j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int8_t>::max)())
13157 {
13158 // int 8
13159 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xD0));
13160 write_number(static_cast<std::int8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
13161 }
13162 else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<std::int16_t>::min)() &&
13163 j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int16_t>::max)())
13164 {
13165 // int 16
13166 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xD1));
13167 write_number(static_cast<std::int16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
13168 }
13169 else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::min)() &&
13170 j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)())
13171 {
13172 // int 32
13173 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xD2));
13174 write_number(static_cast<std::int32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
13175 }
13176 else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<std::int64_t>::min)() &&
13177 j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int64_t>::max)())
13178 {
13179 // int 64
13180 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xD3));
13181 write_number(static_cast<std::int64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
13182 }
13183 }
13184 break;
13185 }
13186
13187 case value_t::number_unsigned:
13188 {
13189 if (j.m_value.number_unsigned < 128)
13190 {
13191 // positive fixnum
13192 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
13193 }
13194 else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
13195 {
13196 // uint 8
13197 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCC));
13198 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
13199 }
13200 else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
13201 {
13202 // uint 16
13203 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCD));
13204 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
13205 }
13206 else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
13207 {
13208 // uint 32
13209 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCE));
13210 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
13211 }
13212 else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint64_t>::max)())
13213 {
13214 // uint 64
13215 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCF));
13216 write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
13217 }
13218 break;
13219 }
13220
13221 case value_t::number_float:
13222 {
13223 write_compact_float(j.m_value.number_float, detail::input_format_t::msgpack);
13224 break;
13225 }
13226
13227 case value_t::string:
13228 {
13229 // step 1: write control byte and the string length
13230 const auto N = j.m_value.string->size();
13231 if (N <= 31)
13232 {
13233 // fixstr
13234 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0xA0 | N));
13235 }
13236 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
13237 {
13238 // str 8
13239 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xD9));
13240 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(N));
13241 }
13242 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
13243 {
13244 // str 16
13245 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xDA));
13246 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
13247 }
13248 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
13249 {
13250 // str 32
13251 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xDB));
13252 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
13253 }
13254
13255 // step 2: write the string
13256 oa->write_characters(
13257 reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(j.m_value.string->c_str()),
13258 j.m_value.string->size());
13259 break;
13260 }
13261
13262 case value_t::array:
13263 {
13264 // step 1: write control byte and the array size
13265 const auto N = j.m_value.array->size();
13266 if (N <= 15)
13267 {
13268 // fixarray
13269 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0x90 | N));
13270 }
13271 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
13272 {
13273 // array 16
13274 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xDC));
13275 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
13276 }
13277 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
13278 {
13279 // array 32
13280 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xDD));
13281 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
13282 }
13283
13284 // step 2: write each element
13285 for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.array)
13286 {
13287 write_msgpack(el);
13288 }
13289 break;
13290 }
13291
13292 case value_t::binary:
13293 {
13294 // step 0: determine if the binary type has a set subtype to
13295 // determine whether or not to use the ext or fixext types
13296 const bool use_ext = j.m_value.binary->has_subtype();
13297
13298 // step 1: write control byte and the byte string length
13299 const auto N = j.m_value.binary->size();
13300 if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
13301 {
13302 std::uint8_t output_type{};
13303 bool fixed = true;
13304 if (use_ext)
13305 {
13306 switch (N)
13307 {
13308 case 1:
13309 output_type = 0xD4; // fixext 1
13310 break;
13311 case 2:
13312 output_type = 0xD5; // fixext 2
13313 break;
13314 case 4:
13315 output_type = 0xD6; // fixext 4
13316 break;
13317 case 8:
13318 output_type = 0xD7; // fixext 8
13319 break;
13320 case 16:
13321 output_type = 0xD8; // fixext 16
13322 break;
13323 default:
13324 output_type = 0xC7; // ext 8
13325 fixed = false;
13326 break;
13327 }
13328
13329 }
13330 else
13331 {
13332 output_type = 0xC4; // bin 8
13333 fixed = false;
13334 }
13335
13336 oa->write_character(to_char_type(output_type));
13337 if (!fixed)
13338 {
13339 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(N));
13340 }
13341 }
13342 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
13343 {
13344 std::uint8_t output_type = use_ext
13345 ? 0xC8 // ext 16
13346 : 0xC5; // bin 16
13347
13348 oa->write_character(to_char_type(output_type));
13349 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
13350 }
13351 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
13352 {
13353 std::uint8_t output_type = use_ext
13354 ? 0xC9 // ext 32
13355 : 0xC6; // bin 32
13356
13357 oa->write_character(to_char_type(output_type));
13358 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
13359 }
13360
13361 // step 1.5: if this is an ext type, write the subtype
13362 if (use_ext)
13363 {
13364 write_number(static_cast<std::int8_t>(j.m_value.binary->subtype()));
13365 }
13366
13367 // step 2: write the byte string
13368 oa->write_characters(
13369 reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(j.m_value.binary->data()),
13370 N);
13371
13372 break;
13373 }
13374
13375 case value_t::object:
13376 {
13377 // step 1: write control byte and the object size
13378 const auto N = j.m_value.object->size();
13379 if (N <= 15)
13380 {
13381 // fixmap
13382 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0x80 | (N & 0xF)));
13383 }
13384 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
13385 {
13386 // map 16
13387 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xDE));
13388 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
13389 }
13390 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
13391 {
13392 // map 32
13393 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xDF));
13394 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
13395 }
13396
13397 // step 2: write each element
13398 for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.object)
13399 {
13400 write_msgpack(el.first);
13401 write_msgpack(el.second);
13402 }
13403 break;
13404 }
13405
13406 default:
13407 break;
13408 }
13409 }
13410
13417 void write_ubjson(const BasicJsonType& j, const bool use_count,
13418 const bool use_type, const bool add_prefix = true)
13419 {
13420 switch (j.type())
13421 {
13422 case value_t::null:
13423 {
13424 if (add_prefix)
13425 {
13426 oa->write_character(to_char_type('Z'));
13427 }
13428 break;
13429 }
13430
13431 case value_t::boolean:
13432 {
13433 if (add_prefix)
13434 {
13435 oa->write_character(j.m_value.boolean
13436 ? to_char_type('T')
13437 : to_char_type('F'));
13438 }
13439 break;
13440 }
13441
13442 case value_t::number_integer:
13443 {
13444 write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.number_integer, add_prefix);
13445 break;
13446 }
13447
13448 case value_t::number_unsigned:
13449 {
13450 write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.number_unsigned, add_prefix);
13451 break;
13452 }
13453
13454 case value_t::number_float:
13455 {
13456 write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.number_float, add_prefix);
13457 break;
13458 }
13459
13460 case value_t::string:
13461 {
13462 if (add_prefix)
13463 {
13464 oa->write_character(to_char_type('S'));
13465 }
13466 write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.string->size(), true);
13467 oa->write_characters(
13468 reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(j.m_value.string->c_str()),
13469 j.m_value.string->size());
13470 break;
13471 }
13472
13473 case value_t::array:
13474 {
13475 if (add_prefix)
13476 {
13477 oa->write_character(to_char_type('['));
13478 }
13479
13480 bool prefix_required = true;
13481 if (use_type && !j.m_value.array->empty())
13482 {
13483 JSON_ASSERT(use_count);
13484 const CharType first_prefix = ubjson_prefix(j.front());
13485 const bool same_prefix = std::all_of(j.begin() + 1, j.end(),
13486 [this, first_prefix](const BasicJsonType & v)
13487 {
13488 return ubjson_prefix(v) == first_prefix;
13489 });
13490
13491 if (same_prefix)
13492 {
13493 prefix_required = false;
13494 oa->write_character(to_char_type('$'));
13495 oa->write_character(first_prefix);
13496 }
13497 }
13498
13499 if (use_count)
13500 {
13501 oa->write_character(to_char_type('#'));
13502 write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.array->size(), true);
13503 }
13504
13505 for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.array)
13506 {
13507 write_ubjson(el, use_count, use_type, prefix_required);
13508 }
13509
13510 if (!use_count)
13511 {
13512 oa->write_character(to_char_type(']'));
13513 }
13514
13515 break;
13516 }
13517
13518 case value_t::binary:
13519 {
13520 if (add_prefix)
13521 {
13522 oa->write_character(to_char_type('['));
13523 }
13524
13525 if (use_type && !j.m_value.binary->empty())
13526 {
13527 JSON_ASSERT(use_count);
13528 oa->write_character(to_char_type('$'));
13529 oa->write_character('U');
13530 }
13531
13532 if (use_count)
13533 {
13534 oa->write_character(to_char_type('#'));
13535 write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.binary->size(), true);
13536 }
13537
13538 if (use_type)
13539 {
13540 oa->write_characters(
13541 reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(j.m_value.binary->data()),
13542 j.m_value.binary->size());
13543 }
13544 else
13545 {
13546 for (size_t i = 0; i < j.m_value.binary->size(); ++i)
13547 {
13548 oa->write_character(to_char_type('U'));
13549 oa->write_character(j.m_value.binary->data()[i]);
13550 }
13551 }
13552
13553 if (!use_count)
13554 {
13555 oa->write_character(to_char_type(']'));
13556 }
13557
13558 break;
13559 }
13560
13561 case value_t::object:
13562 {
13563 if (add_prefix)
13564 {
13565 oa->write_character(to_char_type('{'));
13566 }
13567
13568 bool prefix_required = true;
13569 if (use_type && !j.m_value.object->empty())
13570 {
13571 JSON_ASSERT(use_count);
13572 const CharType first_prefix = ubjson_prefix(j.front());
13573 const bool same_prefix = std::all_of(j.begin(), j.end(),
13574 [this, first_prefix](const BasicJsonType & v)
13575 {
13576 return ubjson_prefix(v) == first_prefix;
13577 });
13578
13579 if (same_prefix)
13580 {
13581 prefix_required = false;
13582 oa->write_character(to_char_type('$'));
13583 oa->write_character(first_prefix);
13584 }
13585 }
13586
13587 if (use_count)
13588 {
13589 oa->write_character(to_char_type('#'));
13590 write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.object->size(), true);
13591 }
13592
13593 for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.object)
13594 {
13595 write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(el.first.size(), true);
13596 oa->write_characters(
13597 reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(el.first.c_str()),
13598 el.first.size());
13599 write_ubjson(el.second, use_count, use_type, prefix_required);
13600 }
13601
13602 if (!use_count)
13603 {
13604 oa->write_character(to_char_type('}'));
13605 }
13606
13607 break;
13608 }
13609
13610 default:
13611 break;
13612 }
13613 }
13614
13615 private:
13617 // BSON //
13619
13624 static std::size_t calc_bson_entry_header_size(const string_t& name)
13625 {
13626 const auto it = name.find(static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(0));
13627 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(it != BasicJsonType::string_t::npos))
13628 {
13629 JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(409,
13630 "BSON key cannot contain code point U+0000 (at byte " + std::to_string(it) + ")"));
13631 }
13632
13633 return /*id*/ 1ul + name.size() + /*zero-terminator*/1u;
13634 }
13635
13639 void write_bson_entry_header(const string_t& name,
13640 const std::uint8_t element_type)
13641 {
13642 oa->write_character(to_char_type(element_type)); // boolean
13643 oa->write_characters(
13644 reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(name.c_str()),
13645 name.size() + 1u);
13646 }
13647
13651 void write_bson_boolean(const string_t& name,
13652 const bool value)
13653 {
13654 write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x08);
13655 oa->write_character(value ? to_char_type(0x01) : to_char_type(0x00));
13656 }
13657
13661 void write_bson_double(const string_t& name,
13662 const double value)
13663 {
13664 write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x01);
13665 write_number<double, true>(value);
13666 }
13667
13671 static std::size_t calc_bson_string_size(const string_t& value)
13672 {
13673 return sizeof(std::int32_t) + value.size() + 1ul;
13674 }
13675
13679 void write_bson_string(const string_t& name,
13680 const string_t& value)
13681 {
13682 write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x02);
13683
13684 write_number<std::int32_t, true>(static_cast<std::int32_t>(value.size() + 1ul));
13685 oa->write_characters(
13686 reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(value.c_str()),
13687 value.size() + 1);
13688 }
13689
13693 void write_bson_null(const string_t& name)
13694 {
13695 write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x0A);
13696 }
13697
13701 static std::size_t calc_bson_integer_size(const std::int64_t value)
13702 {
13703 return (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::min)() <= value && value <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)()
13704 ? sizeof(std::int32_t)
13705 : sizeof(std::int64_t);
13706 }
13707
13711 void write_bson_integer(const string_t& name,
13712 const std::int64_t value)
13713 {
13714 if ((std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::min)() <= value && value <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)())
13715 {
13716 write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x10); // int32
13717 write_number<std::int32_t, true>(static_cast<std::int32_t>(value));
13718 }
13719 else
13720 {
13721 write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x12); // int64
13722 write_number<std::int64_t, true>(static_cast<std::int64_t>(value));
13723 }
13724 }
13725
13729 static constexpr std::size_t calc_bson_unsigned_size(const std::uint64_t value) noexcept
13730 {
13731 return (value <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)()))
13732 ? sizeof(std::int32_t)
13733 : sizeof(std::int64_t);
13734 }
13735
13739 void write_bson_unsigned(const string_t& name,
13740 const std::uint64_t value)
13741 {
13742 if (value <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)()))
13743 {
13744 write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x10 /* int32 */);
13745 write_number<std::int32_t, true>(static_cast<std::int32_t>(value));
13746 }
13747 else if (value <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int64_t>::max)()))
13748 {
13749 write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x12 /* int64 */);
13750 write_number<std::int64_t, true>(static_cast<std::int64_t>(value));
13751 }
13752 else
13753 {
13754 JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(407, "integer number " + std::to_string(value) + " cannot be represented by BSON as it does not fit int64"));
13755 }
13756 }
13757
13761 void write_bson_object_entry(const string_t& name,
13762 const typename BasicJsonType::object_t& value)
13763 {
13764 write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x03); // object
13765 write_bson_object(value);
13766 }
13767
13771 static std::size_t calc_bson_array_size(const typename BasicJsonType::array_t& value)
13772 {
13773 std::size_t array_index = 0ul;
13774
13775 const std::size_t embedded_document_size = std::accumulate(std::begin(value), std::end(value), std::size_t(0), [&array_index](std::size_t result, const typename BasicJsonType::array_t::value_type & el)
13776 {
13777 return result + calc_bson_element_size(std::to_string(array_index++), el);
13778 });
13779
13780 return sizeof(std::int32_t) + embedded_document_size + 1ul;
13781 }
13782
13786 static std::size_t calc_bson_binary_size(const typename BasicJsonType::binary_t& value)
13787 {
13788 return sizeof(std::int32_t) + value.size() + 1ul;
13789 }
13790
13794 void write_bson_array(const string_t& name,
13795 const typename BasicJsonType::array_t& value)
13796 {
13797 write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x04); // array
13798 write_number<std::int32_t, true>(static_cast<std::int32_t>(calc_bson_array_size(value)));
13799
13800 std::size_t array_index = 0ul;
13801
13802 for (const auto& el : value)
13803 {
13804 write_bson_element(std::to_string(array_index++), el);
13805 }
13806
13807 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x00));
13808 }
13809
13813 void write_bson_binary(const string_t& name,
13814 const binary_t& value)
13815 {
13816 write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x05);
13817
13818 write_number<std::int32_t, true>(static_cast<std::int32_t>(value.size()));
13819 write_number(value.has_subtype() ? value.subtype() : std::uint8_t(0x00));
13820
13821 oa->write_characters(reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(value.data()), value.size());
13822 }
13823
13828 static std::size_t calc_bson_element_size(const string_t& name,
13829 const BasicJsonType& j)
13830 {
13831 const auto header_size = calc_bson_entry_header_size(name);
13832 switch (j.type())
13833 {
13834 case value_t::object:
13835 return header_size + calc_bson_object_size(*j.m_value.object);
13836
13837 case value_t::array:
13838 return header_size + calc_bson_array_size(*j.m_value.array);
13839
13840 case value_t::binary:
13841 return header_size + calc_bson_binary_size(*j.m_value.binary);
13842
13843 case value_t::boolean:
13844 return header_size + 1ul;
13845
13846 case value_t::number_float:
13847 return header_size + 8ul;
13848
13849 case value_t::number_integer:
13850 return header_size + calc_bson_integer_size(j.m_value.number_integer);
13851
13852 case value_t::number_unsigned:
13853 return header_size + calc_bson_unsigned_size(j.m_value.number_unsigned);
13854
13855 case value_t::string:
13856 return header_size + calc_bson_string_size(*j.m_value.string);
13857
13858 case value_t::null:
13859 return header_size + 0ul;
13860
13861 // LCOV_EXCL_START
13862 default:
13863 JSON_ASSERT(false);
13864 return 0ul;
13865 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
13866 }
13867 }
13868
13876 void write_bson_element(const string_t& name,
13877 const BasicJsonType& j)
13878 {
13879 switch (j.type())
13880 {
13881 case value_t::object:
13882 return write_bson_object_entry(name, *j.m_value.object);
13883
13884 case value_t::array:
13885 return write_bson_array(name, *j.m_value.array);
13886
13887 case value_t::binary:
13888 return write_bson_binary(name, *j.m_value.binary);
13889
13890 case value_t::boolean:
13891 return write_bson_boolean(name, j.m_value.boolean);
13892
13893 case value_t::number_float:
13894 return write_bson_double(name, j.m_value.number_float);
13895
13896 case value_t::number_integer:
13897 return write_bson_integer(name, j.m_value.number_integer);
13898
13899 case value_t::number_unsigned:
13900 return write_bson_unsigned(name, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
13901
13902 case value_t::string:
13903 return write_bson_string(name, *j.m_value.string);
13904
13905 case value_t::null:
13906 return write_bson_null(name);
13907
13908 // LCOV_EXCL_START
13909 default:
13910 JSON_ASSERT(false);
13911 return;
13912 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
13913 }
13914 }
13915
13922 static std::size_t calc_bson_object_size(const typename BasicJsonType::object_t& value)
13923 {
13924 std::size_t document_size = std::accumulate(value.begin(), value.end(), std::size_t(0),
13925 [](size_t result, const typename BasicJsonType::object_t::value_type & el)
13926 {
13927 return result += calc_bson_element_size(el.first, el.second);
13928 });
13929
13930 return sizeof(std::int32_t) + document_size + 1ul;
13931 }
13932
13937 void write_bson_object(const typename BasicJsonType::object_t& value)
13938 {
13939 write_number<std::int32_t, true>(static_cast<std::int32_t>(calc_bson_object_size(value)));
13940
13941 for (const auto& el : value)
13942 {
13943 write_bson_element(el.first, el.second);
13944 }
13945
13946 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x00));
13947 }
13948

13952
13953 static constexpr CharType get_cbor_float_prefix(float /*unused*/)
13954 {
13955 return to_char_type(0xFA); // Single-Precision Float
13956 }
13957
13958 static constexpr CharType get_cbor_float_prefix(double /*unused*/)
13959 {
13960 return to_char_type(0xFB); // Double-Precision Float
13961 }

13967 static constexpr CharType get_msgpack_float_prefix(float /*unused*/)
13968 {
13969 return to_char_type(0xCA); // float 32
13970 }
13971
13972 static constexpr CharType get_msgpack_float_prefix(double /*unused*/)
13973 {
13974 return to_char_type(0xCB); // float 64
13975 }

13978 // UBJSON //
13980
13981 // UBJSON: write number (floating point)
13982 template<typename NumberType, typename std::enable_if<
13983 std::is_floating_point<NumberType>::value, int>::type = 0>
13984 void write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(const NumberType n,
13985 const bool add_prefix)
13986 {
13987 if (add_prefix)
13988 {
13989 oa->write_character(get_ubjson_float_prefix(n));
13990 }
13991 write_number(n);
13992 }
13993
13994 // UBJSON: write number (unsigned integer)
13995 template<typename NumberType, typename std::enable_if<
13996 std::is_unsigned<NumberType>::value, int>::type = 0>
13997 void write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(const NumberType n,
13998 const bool add_prefix)
13999 {
14000 if (n <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int8_t>::max)()))
14001 {
14002 if (add_prefix)
14003 {
14004 oa->write_character(to_char_type('i')); // int8
14005 }
14006 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(n));
14007 }
14008 else if (n <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
14009 {
14010 if (add_prefix)
14011 {
14012 oa->write_character(to_char_type('U')); // uint8
14013 }
14014 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(n));
14015 }
14016 else if (n <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int16_t>::max)()))
14017 {
14018 if (add_prefix)
14019 {
14020 oa->write_character(to_char_type('I')); // int16
14021 }
14022 write_number(static_cast<std::int16_t>(n));
14023 }
14024 else if (n <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)()))
14025 {
14026 if (add_prefix)
14027 {
14028 oa->write_character(to_char_type('l')); // int32
14029 }
14030 write_number(static_cast<std::int32_t>(n));
14031 }
14032 else if (n <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int64_t>::max)()))
14033 {
14034 if (add_prefix)
14035 {
14036 oa->write_character(to_char_type('L')); // int64
14037 }
14038 write_number(static_cast<std::int64_t>(n));
14039 }
14040 else
14041 {
14042 if (add_prefix)
14043 {
14044 oa->write_character(to_char_type('H')); // high-precision number
14045 }
14046
14047 const auto number = BasicJsonType(n).dump();
14048 write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(number.size(), true);
14049 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < number.size(); ++i)
14050 {
14051 oa->write_character(to_char_type(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(number[i])));
14052 }
14053 }
14054 }
14055
14056 // UBJSON: write number (signed integer)
14057 template < typename NumberType, typename std::enable_if <
14058 std::is_signed<NumberType>::value&&
14059 !std::is_floating_point<NumberType>::value, int >::type = 0 >
14060 void write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(const NumberType n,
14061 const bool add_prefix)
14062 {
14063 if ((std::numeric_limits<std::int8_t>::min)() <= n && n <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int8_t>::max)())
14064 {
14065 if (add_prefix)
14066 {
14067 oa->write_character(to_char_type('i')); // int8
14068 }
14069 write_number(static_cast<std::int8_t>(n));
14070 }
14071 else if (static_cast<std::int64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::min)()) <= n && n <= static_cast<std::int64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)()))
14072 {
14073 if (add_prefix)
14074 {
14075 oa->write_character(to_char_type('U')); // uint8
14076 }
14077 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(n));
14078 }
14079 else if ((std::numeric_limits<std::int16_t>::min)() <= n && n <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int16_t>::max)())
14080 {
14081 if (add_prefix)
14082 {
14083 oa->write_character(to_char_type('I')); // int16
14084 }
14085 write_number(static_cast<std::int16_t>(n));
14086 }
14087 else if ((std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::min)() <= n && n <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)())
14088 {
14089 if (add_prefix)
14090 {
14091 oa->write_character(to_char_type('l')); // int32
14092 }
14093 write_number(static_cast<std::int32_t>(n));
14094 }
14095 else if ((std::numeric_limits<std::int64_t>::min)() <= n && n <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int64_t>::max)())
14096 {
14097 if (add_prefix)
14098 {
14099 oa->write_character(to_char_type('L')); // int64
14100 }
14101 write_number(static_cast<std::int64_t>(n));
14102 }
14103 // LCOV_EXCL_START
14104 else
14105 {
14106 if (add_prefix)
14107 {
14108 oa->write_character(to_char_type('H')); // high-precision number
14109 }
14110
14111 const auto number = BasicJsonType(n).dump();
14112 write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(number.size(), true);
14113 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < number.size(); ++i)
14114 {
14115 oa->write_character(to_char_type(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(number[i])));
14116 }
14117 }
14118 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
14119 }
14120
14124 CharType ubjson_prefix(const BasicJsonType& j) const noexcept
14125 {
14126 switch (j.type())
14127 {
14128 case value_t::null:
14129 return 'Z';
14130
14131 case value_t::boolean:
14132 return j.m_value.boolean ? 'T' : 'F';
14133
14134 case value_t::number_integer:
14135 {
14136 if ((std::numeric_limits<std::int8_t>::min)() <= j.m_value.number_integer && j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int8_t>::max)())
14137 {
14138 return 'i';
14139 }
14140 if ((std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::min)() <= j.m_value.number_integer && j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
14141 {
14142 return 'U';
14143 }
14144 if ((std::numeric_limits<std::int16_t>::min)() <= j.m_value.number_integer && j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int16_t>::max)())
14145 {
14146 return 'I';
14147 }
14148 if ((std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::min)() <= j.m_value.number_integer && j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)())
14149 {
14150 return 'l';
14151 }
14152 if ((std::numeric_limits<std::int64_t>::min)() <= j.m_value.number_integer && j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int64_t>::max)())
14153 {
14154 return 'L';
14155 }
14156 // anything else is treated as high-precision number
14157 return 'H'; // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
14158 }
14159
14160 case value_t::number_unsigned:
14161 {
14162 if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int8_t>::max)()))
14163 {
14164 return 'i';
14165 }
14166 if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)()))
14167 {
14168 return 'U';
14169 }
14170 if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int16_t>::max)()))
14171 {
14172 return 'I';
14173 }
14174 if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)()))
14175 {
14176 return 'l';
14177 }
14178 if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int64_t>::max)()))
14179 {
14180 return 'L';
14181 }
14182 // anything else is treated as high-precision number
14183 return 'H'; // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
14184 }
14185
14186 case value_t::number_float:
14187 return get_ubjson_float_prefix(j.m_value.number_float);
14188
14189 case value_t::string:
14190 return 'S';
14191
14192 case value_t::array: // fallthrough
14193 case value_t::binary:
14194 return '[';
14195
14196 case value_t::object:
14197 return '{';
14198
14199 default: // discarded values
14200 return 'N';
14201 }
14202 }
14203
14204 static constexpr CharType get_ubjson_float_prefix(float /*unused*/)
14205 {
14206 return 'd'; // float 32
14207 }
14208
14209 static constexpr CharType get_ubjson_float_prefix(double /*unused*/)
14210 {
14211 return 'D'; // float 64
14212 }
14213
14215 // Utility functions //
14217
14218 /*
14219 @brief write a number to output input
14220 @param[in] n number of type @a NumberType
14221 @tparam NumberType the type of the number
14222 @tparam OutputIsLittleEndian Set to true if output data is
14223 required to be little endian
14224
14225 @note This function needs to respect the system's endianess, because bytes
14226 in CBOR, MessagePack, and UBJSON are stored in network order (big
14227 endian) and therefore need reordering on little endian systems.
14228 */
14229 template<typename NumberType, bool OutputIsLittleEndian = false>
14230 void write_number(const NumberType n)
14231 {
14232 // step 1: write number to array of length NumberType
14233 std::array<CharType, sizeof(NumberType)> vec;
14234 std::memcpy(vec.data(), &n, sizeof(NumberType));
14235
14236 // step 2: write array to output (with possible reordering)
14237 if (is_little_endian != OutputIsLittleEndian)
14238 {
14239 // reverse byte order prior to conversion if necessary
14240 std::reverse(vec.begin(), vec.end());
14241 }
14242
14243 oa->write_characters(vec.data(), sizeof(NumberType));
14244 }
14245
14246 void write_compact_float(const number_float_t n, detail::input_format_t format)
14247 {
14248 if (static_cast<double>(n) >= static_cast<double>(std::numeric_limits<float>::lowest()) &&
14249 static_cast<double>(n) <= static_cast<double>((std::numeric_limits<float>::max)()) &&
14250 static_cast<double>(static_cast<float>(n)) == static_cast<double>(n))
14251 {
14252 oa->write_character(format == detail::input_format_t::cbor
14253 ? get_cbor_float_prefix(static_cast<float>(n))
14254 : get_msgpack_float_prefix(static_cast<float>(n)));
14255 write_number(static_cast<float>(n));
14256 }
14257 else
14258 {
14259 oa->write_character(format == detail::input_format_t::cbor
14260 ? get_cbor_float_prefix(n)
14261 : get_msgpack_float_prefix(n));
14262 write_number(n);
14263 }
14264 }
14265
14266 public:
14267 // The following to_char_type functions are implement the conversion
14268 // between uint8_t and CharType. In case CharType is not unsigned,
14269 // such a conversion is required to allow values greater than 128.
14270 // See <https://github.com/nlohmann/json/issues/1286> for a discussion.
14271 template < typename C = CharType,
14272 enable_if_t < std::is_signed<C>::value && std::is_signed<char>::value > * = nullptr >
14273 static constexpr CharType to_char_type(std::uint8_t x) noexcept
14274 {
14275 return *reinterpret_cast<char*>(&x);
14276 }
14277
14278 template < typename C = CharType,
14279 enable_if_t < std::is_signed<C>::value && std::is_unsigned<char>::value > * = nullptr >
14280 static CharType to_char_type(std::uint8_t x) noexcept
14281 {
14282 static_assert(sizeof(std::uint8_t) == sizeof(CharType), "size of CharType must be equal to std::uint8_t");
14283 static_assert(std::is_trivial<CharType>::value, "CharType must be trivial");
14284 CharType result;
14285 std::memcpy(&result, &x, sizeof(x));
14286 return result;
14287 }
14288
14289 template<typename C = CharType,
14290 enable_if_t<std::is_unsigned<C>::value>* = nullptr>
14291 static constexpr CharType to_char_type(std::uint8_t x) noexcept
14292 {
14293 return x;
14294 }
14295
14296 template < typename InputCharType, typename C = CharType,
14297 enable_if_t <
14298 std::is_signed<C>::value &&
14299 std::is_signed<char>::value &&
14300 std::is_same<char, typename std::remove_cv<InputCharType>::type>::value
14301 > * = nullptr >
14302 static constexpr CharType to_char_type(InputCharType x) noexcept
14303 {
14304 return x;
14305 }
14306
14307 private:
14309 const bool is_little_endian = little_endianess();
14310
14312 output_adapter_t<CharType> oa = nullptr;
14313 };
14314 } // namespace detail
14315} // namespace nlohmann

14371 namespace dtoa_impl

14373
14374 template<typename Target, typename Source>
14375 Target reinterpret_bits(const Source source)
14376 {
14377 static_assert(sizeof(Target) == sizeof(Source), "size mismatch");
14378
14379 Target target;
14380 std::memcpy(&target, &source, sizeof(Source));
14381 return target;
14382 }
14383
14384 struct diyfp // f * 2^e
14385 {
14386 static constexpr int kPrecision = 64; // = q
14387
14388 std::uint64_t f = 0;
14389 int e = 0;
14390
14391 constexpr diyfp(std::uint64_t f_, int e_) noexcept : f(f_), e(e_) {}
14392
14397 static diyfp sub(const diyfp& x, const diyfp& y) noexcept
14398 {
14399 JSON_ASSERT(x.e == y.e);
14400 JSON_ASSERT(x.f >= y.f);
14401
14402 return {x.f - y.f, x.e};
14403 }
14404
14409 static diyfp mul(const diyfp& x, const diyfp& y) noexcept
14410 {
14411 static_assert(kPrecision == 64, "internal error");
14412
14413 // Computes:
14414 // f = round((x.f * y.f) / 2^q)
14415 // e = x.e + y.e + q
14416
14417 // Emulate the 64-bit * 64-bit multiplication:
14418 //
14419 // p = u * v
14420 // = (u_lo + 2^32 u_hi) (v_lo + 2^32 v_hi)
14421 // = (u_lo v_lo ) + 2^32 ((u_lo v_hi ) + (u_hi v_lo )) + 2^64 (u_hi v_hi )
14422 // = (p0 ) + 2^32 ((p1 ) + (p2 )) + 2^64 (p3 )
14423 // = (p0_lo + 2^32 p0_hi) + 2^32 ((p1_lo + 2^32 p1_hi) + (p2_lo + 2^32 p2_hi)) + 2^64 (p3 )
14424 // = (p0_lo ) + 2^32 (p0_hi + p1_lo + p2_lo ) + 2^64 (p1_hi + p2_hi + p3)
14425 // = (p0_lo ) + 2^32 (Q ) + 2^64 (H )
14426 // = (p0_lo ) + 2^32 (Q_lo + 2^32 Q_hi ) + 2^64 (H )
14427 //
14428 // (Since Q might be larger than 2^32 - 1)
14429 //
14430 // = (p0_lo + 2^32 Q_lo) + 2^64 (Q_hi + H)
14431 //
14432 // (Q_hi + H does not overflow a 64-bit int)
14433 //
14434 // = p_lo + 2^64 p_hi
14435
14436 const std::uint64_t u_lo = x.f & 0xFFFFFFFFu;
14437 const std::uint64_t u_hi = x.f >> 32u;
14438 const std::uint64_t v_lo = y.f & 0xFFFFFFFFu;
14439 const std::uint64_t v_hi = y.f >> 32u;
14440
14441 const std::uint64_t p0 = u_lo * v_lo;
14442 const std::uint64_t p1 = u_lo * v_hi;
14443 const std::uint64_t p2 = u_hi * v_lo;
14444 const std::uint64_t p3 = u_hi * v_hi;
14445
14446 const std::uint64_t p0_hi = p0 >> 32u;
14447 const std::uint64_t p1_lo = p1 & 0xFFFFFFFFu;
14448 const std::uint64_t p1_hi = p1 >> 32u;
14449 const std::uint64_t p2_lo = p2 & 0xFFFFFFFFu;
14450 const std::uint64_t p2_hi = p2 >> 32u;
14451
14452 std::uint64_t Q = p0_hi + p1_lo + p2_lo;
14453
14454 // The full product might now be computed as
14455 //
14456 // p_hi = p3 + p2_hi + p1_hi + (Q >> 32)
14457 // p_lo = p0_lo + (Q << 32)
14458 //
14459 // But in this particular case here, the full p_lo is not required.
14460 // Effectively we only need to add the highest bit in p_lo to p_hi (and
14461 // Q_hi + 1 does not overflow).
14462
14463 Q += std::uint64_t{1} << (64u - 32u - 1u); // round, ties up
14464
14465 const std::uint64_t h = p3 + p2_hi + p1_hi + (Q >> 32u);
14466
14467 return {h, x.e + y.e + 64};
14468 }
14469
14474 static diyfp normalize(diyfp x) noexcept
14475 {
14476 JSON_ASSERT(x.f != 0);
14477
14478 while ((x.f >> 63u) == 0)
14479 {
14480 x.f <<= 1u;
14481 x.e--;
14482 }
14483
14484 return x;
14485 }
14486
14491 static diyfp normalize_to(const diyfp& x, const int target_exponent) noexcept
14492 {
14493 const int delta = x.e - target_exponent;
14494
14495 JSON_ASSERT(delta >= 0);
14496 JSON_ASSERT(((x.f << delta) >> delta) == x.f);
14497
14498 return {x.f << delta, target_exponent};
14499 }
14500 };
14501
14502 struct boundaries
14503 {
14504 diyfp w;
14505 diyfp minus;
14506 diyfp plus;
14507 };
14508
14515 template<typename FloatType>
14516 boundaries compute_boundaries(FloatType value)
14517 {
14518 JSON_ASSERT(std::isfinite(value));
14519 JSON_ASSERT(value > 0);
14520
14521 // Convert the IEEE representation into a diyfp.
14522 //
14523 // If v is denormal:
14524 // value = 0.F * 2^(1 - bias) = ( F) * 2^(1 - bias - (p-1))
14525 // If v is normalized:
14526 // value = 1.F * 2^(E - bias) = (2^(p-1) + F) * 2^(E - bias - (p-1))
14527
14528 static_assert(std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::is_iec559,
14529 "internal error: dtoa_short requires an IEEE-754 floating-point implementation");
14530
14531 constexpr int kPrecision = std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::digits; // = p (includes the hidden bit)
14532 constexpr int kBias = std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::max_exponent - 1 + (kPrecision - 1);
14533 constexpr int kMinExp = 1 - kBias;
14534 constexpr std::uint64_t kHiddenBit = std::uint64_t{1} << (kPrecision - 1); // = 2^(p-1)
14535
14536 using bits_type = typename std::conditional<kPrecision == 24, std::uint32_t, std::uint64_t >::type;
14537
14538 const std::uint64_t bits = reinterpret_bits<bits_type>(value);
14539 const std::uint64_t E = bits >> (kPrecision - 1);
14540 const std::uint64_t F = bits & (kHiddenBit - 1);
14541
14542 const bool is_denormal = E == 0;
14543 const diyfp v = is_denormal
14544 ? diyfp(F, kMinExp)
14545 : diyfp(F + kHiddenBit, static_cast<int>(E) - kBias);
14546
14547 // Compute the boundaries m- and m+ of the floating-point value
14548 // v = f * 2^e.
14549 //
14550 // Determine v- and v+, the floating-point predecessor and successor if v,
14551 // respectively.
14552 //
14553 // v- = v - 2^e if f != 2^(p-1) or e == e_min (A)
14554 // = v - 2^(e-1) if f == 2^(p-1) and e > e_min (B)
14555 //
14556 // v+ = v + 2^e
14557 //
14558 // Let m- = (v- + v) / 2 and m+ = (v + v+) / 2. All real numbers _strictly_
14559 // between m- and m+ round to v, regardless of how the input rounding
14560 // algorithm breaks ties.
14561 //
14562 // ---+-------------+-------------+-------------+-------------+--- (A)
14563 // v- m- v m+ v+
14564 //
14565 // -----------------+------+------+-------------+-------------+--- (B)
14566 // v- m- v m+ v+
14567
14568 const bool lower_boundary_is_closer = F == 0 && E > 1;
14569 const diyfp m_plus = diyfp(2 * v.f + 1, v.e - 1);
14570 const diyfp m_minus = lower_boundary_is_closer
14571 ? diyfp(4 * v.f - 1, v.e - 2) // (B)
14572 : diyfp(2 * v.f - 1, v.e - 1); // (A)
14573
14574 // Determine the normalized w+ = m+.
14575 const diyfp w_plus = diyfp::normalize(m_plus);
14576
14577 // Determine w- = m- such that e_(w-) = e_(w+).
14578 const diyfp w_minus = diyfp::normalize_to(m_minus, w_plus.e);
14579
14580 return {diyfp::normalize(v), w_minus, w_plus};
14581 }
14582
14583 // Given normalized diyfp w, Grisu needs to find a (normalized) cached
14584 // power-of-ten c, such that the exponent of the product c * w = f * 2^e lies
14585 // within a certain range [alpha, gamma] (Definition 3.2 from [1])
14586 //
14587 // alpha <= e = e_c + e_w + q <= gamma
14588 //
14589 // or
14590 //
14591 // f_c * f_w * 2^alpha <= f_c 2^(e_c) * f_w 2^(e_w) * 2^q
14592 // <= f_c * f_w * 2^gamma
14593 //
14594 // Since c and w are normalized, i.e. 2^(q-1) <= f < 2^q, this implies
14595 //
14596 // 2^(q-1) * 2^(q-1) * 2^alpha <= c * w * 2^q < 2^q * 2^q * 2^gamma
14597 //
14598 // or
14599 //
14600 // 2^(q - 2 + alpha) <= c * w < 2^(q + gamma)
14601 //
14602 // The choice of (alpha,gamma) determines the size of the table and the form of
14603 // the digit generation procedure. Using (alpha,gamma)=(-60,-32) works out well
14604 // in practice:
14605 //
14606 // The idea is to cut the number c * w = f * 2^e into two parts, which can be
14607 // processed independently: An integral part p1, and a fractional part p2:
14608 //
14609 // f * 2^e = ( (f div 2^-e) * 2^-e + (f mod 2^-e) ) * 2^e
14610 // = (f div 2^-e) + (f mod 2^-e) * 2^e
14611 // = p1 + p2 * 2^e
14612 //
14613 // The conversion of p1 into decimal form requires a series of divisions and
14614 // modulos by (a power of) 10. These operations are faster for 32-bit than for
14615 // 64-bit integers, so p1 should ideally fit into a 32-bit integer. This can be
14616 // achieved by choosing
14617 //
14618 // -e >= 32 or e <= -32 := gamma
14619 //
14620 // In order to convert the fractional part
14621 //
14622 // p2 * 2^e = p2 / 2^-e = d[-1] / 10^1 + d[-2] / 10^2 + ...
14623 //
14624 // into decimal form, the fraction is repeatedly multiplied by 10 and the digits
14625 // d[-i] are extracted in order:
14626 //
14627 // (10 * p2) div 2^-e = d[-1]
14628 // (10 * p2) mod 2^-e = d[-2] / 10^1 + ...
14629 //
14630 // The multiplication by 10 must not overflow. It is sufficient to choose
14631 //
14632 // 10 * p2 < 16 * p2 = 2^4 * p2 <= 2^64.
14633 //
14634 // Since p2 = f mod 2^-e < 2^-e,
14635 //
14636 // -e <= 60 or e >= -60 := alpha
14637
14638 constexpr int kAlpha = -60;
14639 constexpr int kGamma = -32;
14640
14641 struct cached_power // c = f * 2^e ~= 10^k
14642 {
14643 std::uint64_t f;
14644 int e;
14645 int k;
14646 };
14647
14655 inline cached_power get_cached_power_for_binary_exponent(int e)
14656 {
14657 // Now
14658 //
14659 // alpha <= e_c + e + q <= gamma (1)
14660 // ==> f_c * 2^alpha <= c * 2^e * 2^q
14661 //
14662 // and since the c's are normalized, 2^(q-1) <= f_c,
14663 //
14664 // ==> 2^(q - 1 + alpha) <= c * 2^(e + q)
14665 // ==> 2^(alpha - e - 1) <= c
14666 //
14667 // If c were an exact power of ten, i.e. c = 10^k, one may determine k as
14668 //
14669 // k = ceil( log_10( 2^(alpha - e - 1) ) )
14670 // = ceil( (alpha - e - 1) * log_10(2) )
14671 //
14672 // From the paper:
14673 // "In theory the result of the procedure could be wrong since c is rounded,
14674 // and the computation itself is approximated [...]. In practice, however,
14675 // this simple function is sufficient."
14676 //
14677 // For IEEE double precision floating-point numbers converted into
14678 // normalized diyfp's w = f * 2^e, with q = 64,
14679 //
14680 // e >= -1022 (min IEEE exponent)
14681 // -52 (p - 1)
14682 // -52 (p - 1, possibly normalize denormal IEEE numbers)
14683 // -11 (normalize the diyfp)
14684 // = -1137
14685 //
14686 // and
14687 //
14688 // e <= +1023 (max IEEE exponent)
14689 // -52 (p - 1)
14690 // -11 (normalize the diyfp)
14691 // = 960
14692 //
14693 // This binary exponent range [-1137,960] results in a decimal exponent
14694 // range [-307,324]. One does not need to store a cached power for each
14695 // k in this range. For each such k it suffices to find a cached power
14696 // such that the exponent of the product lies in [alpha,gamma].
14697 // This implies that the difference of the decimal exponents of adjacent
14698 // table entries must be less than or equal to
14699 //
14700 // floor( (gamma - alpha) * log_10(2) ) = 8.
14701 //
14702 // (A smaller distance gamma-alpha would require a larger table.)
14703
14704 // NB:
14705 // Actually this function returns c, such that -60 <= e_c + e + 64 <= -34.
14706
14707 constexpr int kCachedPowersMinDecExp = -300;
14708 constexpr int kCachedPowersDecStep = 8;
14709

14789 { 0x8E679C2F5E44FF8F, 960, 308 },
14790 { 0xD433179D9C8CB841, 986, 316 },

14794
14795 // This computation gives exactly the same results for k as
14796 // k = ceil((kAlpha - e - 1) * 0.30102999566398114)
14797 // for |e| <= 1500, but doesn't require floating-point operations.
14798 // NB: log_10(2) ~= 78913 / 2^18
14799 JSON_ASSERT(e >= -1500);
14800 JSON_ASSERT(e <= 1500);
14801 const int f = kAlpha - e - 1;
14802 const int k = (f * 78913) / (1 << 18) + static_cast<int>(f > 0);
14803
14804 const int index = (-kCachedPowersMinDecExp + k + (kCachedPowersDecStep - 1)) / kCachedPowersDecStep;
14805 JSON_ASSERT(index >= 0);
14806 JSON_ASSERT(static_cast<std::size_t>(index) < kCachedPowers.size());
14807
14808 const cached_power cached = kCachedPowers[static_cast<std::size_t>(index)];
14809 JSON_ASSERT(kAlpha <= cached.e + e + 64);
14810 JSON_ASSERT(kGamma >= cached.e + e + 64);
14811
14812 return cached;
14813 }
14814
14819 inline int find_largest_pow10(const std::uint32_t n, std::uint32_t& pow10)
14820 {
14821 // LCOV_EXCL_START
14822 if (n >= 1000000000)
14823 {
14824 pow10 = 1000000000;
14825 return 10;
14826 }
14827 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
14828 else if (n >= 100000000)
14829 {
14830 pow10 = 100000000;
14831 return 9;
14832 }
14833 else if (n >= 10000000)
14834 {
14835 pow10 = 10000000;
14836 return 8;
14837 }
14838 else if (n >= 1000000)
14839 {
14840 pow10 = 1000000;
14841 return 7;
14842 }
14843 else if (n >= 100000)
14844 {
14845 pow10 = 100000;
14846 return 6;
14847 }
14848 else if (n >= 10000)
14849 {
14850 pow10 = 10000;
14851 return 5;
14852 }
14853 else if (n >= 1000)
14854 {
14855 pow10 = 1000;
14856 return 4;
14857 }
14858 else if (n >= 100)
14859 {
14860 pow10 = 100;
14861 return 3;
14862 }
14863 else if (n >= 10)
14864 {
14865 pow10 = 10;
14866 return 2;
14867 }
14868 else
14869 {
14870 pow10 = 1;
14871 return 1;
14872 }
14873 }
14874
14875 inline void grisu2_round(char* buf, int len, std::uint64_t dist, std::uint64_t delta,
14876 std::uint64_t rest, std::uint64_t ten_k)
14877 {
14878 JSON_ASSERT(len >= 1);
14879 JSON_ASSERT(dist <= delta);
14880 JSON_ASSERT(rest <= delta);
14881 JSON_ASSERT(ten_k > 0);
14882
14883 // <--------------------------- delta ---->
14884 // <---- dist --------->
14885 // --------------[------------------+-------------------]--------------
14886 // M- w M+
14887 //
14888 // ten_k
14889 // <------>
14890 // <---- rest ---->
14891 // --------------[------------------+----+--------------]--------------
14892 // w V
14893 // = buf * 10^k
14894 //
14895 // ten_k represents a unit-in-the-last-place in the decimal representation
14896 // stored in buf.
14897 // Decrement buf by ten_k while this takes buf closer to w.
14898
14899 // The tests are written in this order to avoid overflow in unsigned
14900 // integer arithmetic.
14901
14902 while (rest < dist
14903 && delta - rest >= ten_k
14904 && (rest + ten_k < dist || dist - rest > rest + ten_k - dist))
14905 {
14906 JSON_ASSERT(buf[len - 1] != '0');
14907 buf[len - 1]--;
14908 rest += ten_k;
14909 }
14910 }
14911
14916 inline void grisu2_digit_gen(char* buffer, int& length, int& decimal_exponent,
14917 diyfp M_minus, diyfp w, diyfp M_plus)
14918 {
14919 static_assert(kAlpha >= -60, "internal error");
14920 static_assert(kGamma <= -32, "internal error");
14921
14922 // Generates the digits (and the exponent) of a decimal floating-point
14923 // number V = buffer * 10^decimal_exponent in the range [M-, M+]. The diyfp's
14924 // w, M- and M+ share the same exponent e, which satisfies alpha <= e <= gamma.
14925 //
14926 // <--------------------------- delta ---->
14927 // <---- dist --------->
14928 // --------------[------------------+-------------------]--------------
14929 // M- w M+
14930 //
14931 // Grisu2 generates the digits of M+ from left to right and stops as soon as
14932 // V is in [M-,M+].
14933
14934 JSON_ASSERT(M_plus.e >= kAlpha);
14935 JSON_ASSERT(M_plus.e <= kGamma);
14936
14937 std::uint64_t delta = diyfp::sub(M_plus, M_minus).f; // (significand of (M+ - M-), implicit exponent is e)
14938 std::uint64_t dist = diyfp::sub(M_plus, w ).f; // (significand of (M+ - w ), implicit exponent is e)
14939
14940 // Split M+ = f * 2^e into two parts p1 and p2 (note: e < 0):
14941 //
14942 // M+ = f * 2^e
14943 // = ((f div 2^-e) * 2^-e + (f mod 2^-e)) * 2^e
14944 // = ((p1 ) * 2^-e + (p2 )) * 2^e
14945 // = p1 + p2 * 2^e
14946
14947 const diyfp one(std::uint64_t{1} << -M_plus.e, M_plus.e);
14948
14949 auto p1 = static_cast<std::uint32_t>(M_plus.f >> -one.e); // p1 = f div 2^-e (Since -e >= 32, p1 fits into a 32-bit int.)
14950 std::uint64_t p2 = M_plus.f & (one.f - 1); // p2 = f mod 2^-e
14951
14952 // 1)
14953 //
14954 // Generate the digits of the integral part p1 = d[n-1]...d[1]d[0]
14955
14956 JSON_ASSERT(p1 > 0);
14957
14958 std::uint32_t pow10;
14959 const int k = find_largest_pow10(p1, pow10);
14960
14961 // 10^(k-1) <= p1 < 10^k, pow10 = 10^(k-1)
14962 //
14963 // p1 = (p1 div 10^(k-1)) * 10^(k-1) + (p1 mod 10^(k-1))
14964 // = (d[k-1] ) * 10^(k-1) + (p1 mod 10^(k-1))
14965 //
14966 // M+ = p1 + p2 * 2^e
14967 // = d[k-1] * 10^(k-1) + (p1 mod 10^(k-1)) + p2 * 2^e
14968 // = d[k-1] * 10^(k-1) + ((p1 mod 10^(k-1)) * 2^-e + p2) * 2^e
14969 // = d[k-1] * 10^(k-1) + ( rest) * 2^e
14970 //
14971 // Now generate the digits d[n] of p1 from left to right (n = k-1,...,0)
14972 //
14973 // p1 = d[k-1]...d[n] * 10^n + d[n-1]...d[0]
14974 //
14975 // but stop as soon as
14976 //
14977 // rest * 2^e = (d[n-1]...d[0] * 2^-e + p2) * 2^e <= delta * 2^e
14978
14979 int n = k;
14980 while (n > 0)
14981 {
14982 // Invariants:
14983 // M+ = buffer * 10^n + (p1 + p2 * 2^e) (buffer = 0 for n = k)
14984 // pow10 = 10^(n-1) <= p1 < 10^n
14985 //
14986 const std::uint32_t d = p1 / pow10; // d = p1 div 10^(n-1)
14987 const std::uint32_t r = p1 % pow10; // r = p1 mod 10^(n-1)
14988 //
14989 // M+ = buffer * 10^n + (d * 10^(n-1) + r) + p2 * 2^e
14990 // = (buffer * 10 + d) * 10^(n-1) + (r + p2 * 2^e)
14991 //
14992 JSON_ASSERT(d <= 9);
14993 buffer[length++] = static_cast<char>('0' + d); // buffer := buffer * 10 + d
14994 //
14995 // M+ = buffer * 10^(n-1) + (r + p2 * 2^e)
14996 //
14997 p1 = r;
14998 n--;
14999 //
15000 // M+ = buffer * 10^n + (p1 + p2 * 2^e)
15001 // pow10 = 10^n
15002 //
15003
15004 // Now check if enough digits have been generated.
15005 // Compute
15006 //
15007 // p1 + p2 * 2^e = (p1 * 2^-e + p2) * 2^e = rest * 2^e
15008 //
15009 // Note:
15010 // Since rest and delta share the same exponent e, it suffices to
15011 // compare the significands.
15012 const std::uint64_t rest = (std::uint64_t{p1} << -one.e) + p2;
15013 if (rest <= delta)
15014 {
15015 // V = buffer * 10^n, with M- <= V <= M+.
15016
15017 decimal_exponent += n;
15018
15019 // We may now just stop. But instead look if the buffer could be
15020 // decremented to bring V closer to w.
15021 //
15022 // pow10 = 10^n is now 1 ulp in the decimal representation V.
15023 // The rounding procedure works with diyfp's with an implicit
15024 // exponent of e.
15025 //
15026 // 10^n = (10^n * 2^-e) * 2^e = ulp * 2^e
15027 //
15028 const std::uint64_t ten_n = std::uint64_t{pow10} << -one.e;
15029 grisu2_round(buffer, length, dist, delta, rest, ten_n);
15030
15031 return;
15032 }
15033
15034 pow10 /= 10;
15035 //
15036 // pow10 = 10^(n-1) <= p1 < 10^n
15037 // Invariants restored.
15038 }
15039
15040 // 2)
15041 //
15042 // The digits of the integral part have been generated:
15043 //
15044 // M+ = d[k-1]...d[1]d[0] + p2 * 2^e
15045 // = buffer + p2 * 2^e
15046 //
15047 // Now generate the digits of the fractional part p2 * 2^e.
15048 //
15049 // Note:
15050 // No decimal point is generated: the exponent is adjusted instead.
15051 //
15052 // p2 actually represents the fraction
15053 //
15054 // p2 * 2^e
15055 // = p2 / 2^-e
15056 // = d[-1] / 10^1 + d[-2] / 10^2 + ...
15057 //
15058 // Now generate the digits d[-m] of p1 from left to right (m = 1,2,...)
15059 //
15060 // p2 * 2^e = d[-1]d[-2]...d[-m] * 10^-m
15061 // + 10^-m * (d[-m-1] / 10^1 + d[-m-2] / 10^2 + ...)
15062 //
15063 // using
15064 //
15065 // 10^m * p2 = ((10^m * p2) div 2^-e) * 2^-e + ((10^m * p2) mod 2^-e)
15066 // = ( d) * 2^-e + ( r)
15067 //
15068 // or
15069 // 10^m * p2 * 2^e = d + r * 2^e
15070 //
15071 // i.e.
15072 //
15073 // M+ = buffer + p2 * 2^e
15074 // = buffer + 10^-m * (d + r * 2^e)
15075 // = (buffer * 10^m + d) * 10^-m + 10^-m * r * 2^e
15076 //
15077 // and stop as soon as 10^-m * r * 2^e <= delta * 2^e
15078
15079 JSON_ASSERT(p2 > delta);
15080
15081 int m = 0;
15082 for (;;)
15083 {
15084 // Invariant:
15085 // M+ = buffer * 10^-m + 10^-m * (d[-m-1] / 10 + d[-m-2] / 10^2 + ...) * 2^e
15086 // = buffer * 10^-m + 10^-m * (p2 ) * 2^e
15087 // = buffer * 10^-m + 10^-m * (1/10 * (10 * p2) ) * 2^e
15088 // = buffer * 10^-m + 10^-m * (1/10 * ((10*p2 div 2^-e) * 2^-e + (10*p2 mod 2^-e)) * 2^e
15089 //
15090 JSON_ASSERT(p2 <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint64_t>::max)() / 10);
15091 p2 *= 10;
15092 const std::uint64_t d = p2 >> -one.e; // d = (10 * p2) div 2^-e
15093 const std::uint64_t r = p2 & (one.f - 1); // r = (10 * p2) mod 2^-e
15094 //
15095 // M+ = buffer * 10^-m + 10^-m * (1/10 * (d * 2^-e + r) * 2^e
15096 // = buffer * 10^-m + 10^-m * (1/10 * (d + r * 2^e))
15097 // = (buffer * 10 + d) * 10^(-m-1) + 10^(-m-1) * r * 2^e
15098 //
15099 JSON_ASSERT(d <= 9);
15100 buffer[length++] = static_cast<char>('0' + d); // buffer := buffer * 10 + d
15101 //
15102 // M+ = buffer * 10^(-m-1) + 10^(-m-1) * r * 2^e
15103 //
15104 p2 = r;
15105 m++;
15106 //
15107 // M+ = buffer * 10^-m + 10^-m * p2 * 2^e
15108 // Invariant restored.
15109
15110 // Check if enough digits have been generated.
15111 //
15112 // 10^-m * p2 * 2^e <= delta * 2^e
15113 // p2 * 2^e <= 10^m * delta * 2^e
15114 // p2 <= 10^m * delta
15115 delta *= 10;
15116 dist *= 10;
15117 if (p2 <= delta)
15118 {
15119 break;
15120 }
15121 }
15122
15123 // V = buffer * 10^-m, with M- <= V <= M+.
15124
15125 decimal_exponent -= m;
15126
15127 // 1 ulp in the decimal representation is now 10^-m.
15128 // Since delta and dist are now scaled by 10^m, we need to do the
15129 // same with ulp in order to keep the units in sync.
15130 //
15131 // 10^m * 10^-m = 1 = 2^-e * 2^e = ten_m * 2^e
15132 //
15133 const std::uint64_t ten_m = one.f;
15134 grisu2_round(buffer, length, dist, delta, p2, ten_m);
15135
15136 // By construction this algorithm generates the shortest possible decimal
15137 // number (Loitsch, Theorem 6.2) which rounds back to w.
15138 // For an input number of precision p, at least
15139 //
15140 // N = 1 + ceil(p * log_10(2))
15141 //
15142 // decimal digits are sufficient to identify all binary floating-point
15143 // numbers (Matula, "In-and-Out conversions").
15144 // This implies that the algorithm does not produce more than N decimal
15145 // digits.
15146 //
15147 // N = 17 for p = 53 (IEEE double precision)
15148 // N = 9 for p = 24 (IEEE single precision)
15149 }
15150
15156 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(1)
15157 inline void grisu2(char* buf, int& len, int& decimal_exponent,
15158 diyfp m_minus, diyfp v, diyfp m_plus)
15159 {
15160 JSON_ASSERT(m_plus.e == m_minus.e);
15161 JSON_ASSERT(m_plus.e == v.e);
15162
15163 // --------(-----------------------+-----------------------)-------- (A)
15164 // m- v m+
15165 //
15166 // --------------------(-----------+-----------------------)-------- (B)
15167 // m- v m+
15168 //
15169 // First scale v (and m- and m+) such that the exponent is in the range
15170 // [alpha, gamma].
15171
15172 const cached_power cached = get_cached_power_for_binary_exponent(m_plus.e);
15173
15174 const diyfp c_minus_k(cached.f, cached.e); // = c ~= 10^-k
15175
15176 // The exponent of the products is = v.e + c_minus_k.e + q and is in the range [alpha,gamma]
15177 const diyfp w = diyfp::mul(v, c_minus_k);
15178 const diyfp w_minus = diyfp::mul(m_minus, c_minus_k);
15179 const diyfp w_plus = diyfp::mul(m_plus, c_minus_k);
15180
15181 // ----(---+---)---------------(---+---)---------------(---+---)----
15182 // w- w w+
15183 // = c*m- = c*v = c*m+
15184 //
15185 // diyfp::mul rounds its result and c_minus_k is approximated too. w, w- and
15186 // w+ are now off by a small amount.
15187 // In fact:
15188 //
15189 // w - v * 10^k < 1 ulp
15190 //
15191 // To account for this inaccuracy, add resp. subtract 1 ulp.
15192 //
15193 // --------+---[---------------(---+---)---------------]---+--------
15194 // w- M- w M+ w+
15195 //
15196 // Now any number in [M-, M+] (bounds included) will round to w when input,
15197 // regardless of how the input rounding algorithm breaks ties.
15198 //
15199 // And digit_gen generates the shortest possible such number in [M-, M+].
15200 // Note that this does not mean that Grisu2 always generates the shortest
15201 // possible number in the interval (m-, m+).
15202 const diyfp M_minus(w_minus.f + 1, w_minus.e);
15203 const diyfp M_plus (w_plus.f - 1, w_plus.e );
15204
15205 decimal_exponent = -cached.k; // = -(-k) = k
15206
15207 grisu2_digit_gen(buf, len, decimal_exponent, M_minus, w, M_plus);
15208 }
15209
15215 template<typename FloatType>
15216 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(1)
15217 void grisu2(char* buf, int& len, int& decimal_exponent, FloatType value)
15218 {
15219 static_assert(diyfp::kPrecision >= std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::digits + 3,
15220 "internal error: not enough precision");
15221
15222 JSON_ASSERT(std::isfinite(value));
15223 JSON_ASSERT(value > 0);
15224
15225 // If the neighbors (and boundaries) of 'value' are always computed for double-precision
15226 // numbers, all float's can be recovered using strtod (and strtof). However, the resulting
15227 // decimal representations are not exactly "short".
15228 //
15229 // The documentation for 'std::to_chars' (https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/utility/to_chars)
15230 // says "value is converted to a string as if by std::sprintf in the default ("C") locale"
15231 // and since sprintf promotes float's to double's, I think this is exactly what 'std::to_chars'
15232 // does.
15233 // On the other hand, the documentation for 'std::to_chars' requires that "parsing the
15234 // representation using the corresponding std::from_chars function recovers value exactly". That
15235 // indicates that single precision floating-point numbers should be recovered using
15236 // 'std::strtof'.
15237 //
15238 // NB: If the neighbors are computed for single-precision numbers, there is a single float
15239 // (7.0385307e-26f) which can't be recovered using strtod. The resulting double precision
15240 // value is off by 1 ulp.
15241#if 0
15242 const boundaries w = compute_boundaries(static_cast<double>(value));
15243#else
15244 const boundaries w = compute_boundaries(value);
15245#endif
15246
15247 grisu2(buf, len, decimal_exponent, w.minus, w.w, w.plus);
15248 }
15249
15255 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(1)
15256 JSON_HEDLEY_RETURNS_NON_NULL
15257 inline char* append_exponent(char* buf, int e)
15258 {
15259 JSON_ASSERT(e > -1000);
15260 JSON_ASSERT(e < 1000);
15261
15262 if (e < 0)
15263 {
15264 e = -e;
15265 *buf++ = '-';
15266 }
15267 else
15268 {
15269 *buf++ = '+';
15270 }
15271
15272 auto k = static_cast<std::uint32_t>(e);
15273 if (k < 10)
15274 {
15275 // Always print at least two digits in the exponent.
15276 // This is for compatibility with printf("%g").
15277 *buf++ = '0';
15278 *buf++ = static_cast<char>('0' + k);
15279 }
15280 else if (k < 100)
15281 {
15282 *buf++ = static_cast<char>('0' + k / 10);
15283 k %= 10;
15284 *buf++ = static_cast<char>('0' + k);
15285 }
15286 else
15287 {
15288 *buf++ = static_cast<char>('0' + k / 100);
15289 k %= 100;
15290 *buf++ = static_cast<char>('0' + k / 10);
15291 k %= 10;
15292 *buf++ = static_cast<char>('0' + k);
15293 }
15294
15295 return buf;
15296 }
15297
15307 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(1)
15308 JSON_HEDLEY_RETURNS_NON_NULL
15309 inline char* format_buffer(char* buf, int len, int decimal_exponent,
15310 int min_exp, int max_exp)
15311 {
15312 JSON_ASSERT(min_exp < 0);
15313 JSON_ASSERT(max_exp > 0);
15314
15315 const int k = len;
15316 const int n = len + decimal_exponent;
15317
15318 // v = buf * 10^(n-k)
15319 // k is the length of the buffer (number of decimal digits)
15320 // n is the position of the decimal point relative to the start of the buffer.
15321
15322 if (k <= n && n <= max_exp)
15323 {
15324 // digits[000]
15325 // len <= max_exp + 2
15326
15327 std::memset(buf + k, '0', static_cast<size_t>(n) - static_cast<size_t>(k));
15328 // Make it look like a floating-point number (#362, #378)
15329 buf[n + 0] = '.';
15330 buf[n + 1] = '0';
15331 return buf + (static_cast<size_t>(n) + 2);
15332 }
15333
15334 if (0 < n && n <= max_exp)
15335 {
15336 // dig.its
15337 // len <= max_digits10 + 1
15338
15339 JSON_ASSERT(k > n);
15340
15341 std::memmove(buf + (static_cast<size_t>(n) + 1), buf + n, static_cast<size_t>(k) - static_cast<size_t>(n));
15342 buf[n] = '.';
15343 return buf + (static_cast<size_t>(k) + 1U);
15344 }
15345
15346 if (min_exp < n && n <= 0)
15347 {
15348 // 0.[000]digits
15349 // len <= 2 + (-min_exp - 1) + max_digits10
15350
15351 std::memmove(buf + (2 + static_cast<size_t>(-n)), buf, static_cast<size_t>(k));
15352 buf[0] = '0';
15353 buf[1] = '.';
15354 std::memset(buf + 2, '0', static_cast<size_t>(-n));
15355 return buf + (2U + static_cast<size_t>(-n) + static_cast<size_t>(k));
15356 }
15357
15358 if (k == 1)
15359 {
15360 // dE+123
15361 // len <= 1 + 5
15362
15363 buf += 1;
15364 }
15365 else
15366 {
15367 // d.igitsE+123
15368 // len <= max_digits10 + 1 + 5
15369
15370 std::memmove(buf + 2, buf + 1, static_cast<size_t>(k) - 1);
15371 buf[1] = '.';
15372 buf += 1 + static_cast<size_t>(k);
15373 }
15374
15375 *buf++ = 'e';
15376 return append_exponent(buf, n - 1);
15377 }
15378
15379 } // namespace dtoa_impl
15380
15391 template<typename FloatType>
15392 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(1, 2)
15393 JSON_HEDLEY_RETURNS_NON_NULL
15394 char* to_chars(char* first, const char* last, FloatType value)
15395 {
15396 static_cast<void>(last); // maybe unused - fix warning
15397 JSON_ASSERT(std::isfinite(value));
15398
15399 // Use signbit(value) instead of (value < 0) since signbit works for -0.
15400 if (std::signbit(value))
15401 {
15402 value = -value;
15403 *first++ = '-';
15404 }
15405
15406 if (value == 0) // +-0
15407 {
15408 *first++ = '0';
15409 // Make it look like a floating-point number (#362, #378)
15410 *first++ = '.';
15411 *first++ = '0';
15412 return first;
15413 }
15414
15415 JSON_ASSERT(last - first >= std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::max_digits10);
15416
15417 // Compute v = buffer * 10^decimal_exponent.
15418 // The decimal digits are stored in the buffer, which needs to be interpreted
15419 // as an unsigned decimal integer.
15420 // len is the length of the buffer, i.e. the number of decimal digits.
15421 int len = 0;
15422 int decimal_exponent = 0;
15423 dtoa_impl::grisu2(first, len, decimal_exponent, value);
15424
15425 JSON_ASSERT(len <= std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::max_digits10);
15426
15427 // Format the buffer like printf("%.*g", prec, value)
15428 constexpr int kMinExp = -4;
15429 // Use digits10 here to increase compatibility with version 2.
15430 constexpr int kMaxExp = std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::digits10;
15431
15432 JSON_ASSERT(last - first >= kMaxExp + 2);
15433 JSON_ASSERT(last - first >= 2 + (-kMinExp - 1) + std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::max_digits10);
15434 JSON_ASSERT(last - first >= std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::max_digits10 + 6);
15435
15436 return dtoa_impl::format_buffer(first, len, decimal_exponent, kMinExp, kMaxExp);
15437 }
15438
15439 } // namespace detail
15440} // namespace nlohmann
