24602
24604 // JSON Patch functions //
24606
24609
24657 basic_json patch(const basic_json& json_patch) const
24658 {
24659 // make a working copy to apply the patch to
24660 basic_json result = *this;
24661
24662 // the valid JSON Patch operations
24663 enum class patch_operations {add, remove, replace, move, copy, test, invalid};
24664
24665 const auto get_op = [](const std::string & op)
24666 {
24667 if (op == "add")
24668 {
24669 return patch_operations::add;
24670 }
24671 if (op == "remove")
24672 {
24673 return patch_operations::remove;
24674 }
24675 if (op == "replace")
24676 {
24677 return patch_operations::replace;
24678 }
24679 if (op == "move")
24680 {
24681 return patch_operations::move;
24682 }
24683 if (op == "copy")
24684 {
24685 return patch_operations::copy;
24686 }
24687 if (op == "test")
24688 {
24689 return patch_operations::test;
24690 }
24691
24692 return patch_operations::invalid;
24693 };
24694
24695 // wrapper for "add" operation; add value at ptr
24696 const auto operation_add = [&result](json_pointer & ptr, basic_json val)
24697 {
24698 // adding to the root of the target document means replacing it
24699 if (ptr.empty())
24700 {
24701 result = val;
24702 return;
24703 }
24704
24705 // make sure the top element of the pointer exists
24706 json_pointer top_pointer = ptr.top();
24707 if (top_pointer != ptr)
24708 {
24709 result.at(top_pointer);
24710 }
24711
24712 // get reference to parent of JSON pointer ptr
24713 const auto last_path = ptr.back();
24714 ptr.pop_back();
24715 basic_json& parent = result[ptr];
24716
24717 switch (parent.m_type)
24718 {
24719 case value_t::null:
24720 case value_t::object:
24721 {
24722 // use operator[] to add value
24723 parent[last_path] = val;
24724 break;
24725 }
24726
24727 case value_t::array:
24728 {
24729 if (last_path == "-")
24730 {
24731 // special case: append to back
24732 parent.push_back(val);
24733 }
24734 else
24735 {
24736 const auto idx = json_pointer::array_index(last_path);
24737 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(idx > parent.size()))
24738 {
24739 // avoid undefined behavior
24740 JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(401, "array index " + std::to_string(idx) + " is out of range"));
24741 }
24742
24743 // default case: insert add offset
24744 parent.insert(parent.begin() + static_cast<difference_type>(idx), val);
24745 }
24746 break;
24747 }
24748
24749 // if there exists a parent it cannot be primitive
24750 default: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
24751 JSON_ASSERT(false); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
24752 }
24753 };
24754
24755 // wrapper for "remove" operation; remove value at ptr
24756 const auto operation_remove = [&result](json_pointer & ptr)
24757 {
24758 // get reference to parent of JSON pointer ptr
24759 const auto last_path = ptr.back();
24760 ptr.pop_back();
24761 basic_json& parent = result.at(ptr);
24762
24763 // remove child
24764 if (parent.is_object())
24765 {
24766 // perform range check
24767 auto it = parent.find(last_path);
24768 if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(it != parent.end()))
24769 {
24770 parent.erase(it);
24771 }
24772 else
24773 {
24774 JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(403, "key '" + last_path + "' not found"));
24775 }
24776 }
24777 else if (parent.is_array())
24778 {
24779 // note erase performs range check
24780 parent.erase(json_pointer::array_index(last_path));
24781 }
24782 };
24783
24784 // type check: top level value must be an array
24785 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!json_patch.is_array()))
24786 {
24787 JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(104, 0, "JSON patch must be an array of objects"));
24788 }
24789
24790 // iterate and apply the operations
24791 for (const auto& val : json_patch)
24792 {
24793 // wrapper to get a value for an operation
24794 const auto get_value = [&val](const std::string & op,
24795 const std::string & member,
24796 bool string_type) -> basic_json &
24797 {
24798 // find value
24799 auto it = val.m_value.object->find(member);
24800
24801 // context-sensitive error message
24802 const auto error_msg = (op == "op") ? "operation" : "operation '" + op + "'";
24803
24804 // check if desired value is present
24805 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(it == val.m_value.object->end()))
24806 {
24807 JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(105, 0, error_msg + " must have member '" + member + "'"));
24808 }
24809
24810 // check if result is of type string
24811 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(string_type && !it->second.is_string()))
24812 {
24813 JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(105, 0, error_msg + " must have string member '" + member + "'"));
24814 }
24815
24816 // no error: return value
24817 return it->second;
24818 };
24819
24820 // type check: every element of the array must be an object
24821 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!val.is_object()))
24822 {
24823 JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(104, 0, "JSON patch must be an array of objects"));
24824 }
24825
24826 // collect mandatory members
24827 const auto op = get_value("op", "op", true).template get<std::string>();
24828 const auto path = get_value(op, "path", true).template get<std::string>();
24829 json_pointer ptr(path);
24830
24831 switch (get_op(op))
24832 {
24833 case patch_operations::add:
24834 {
24835 operation_add(ptr, get_value("add", "value", false));
24836 break;
24837 }
24838
24839 case patch_operations::remove:
24840 {
24841 operation_remove(ptr);
24842 break;
24843 }
24844
24845 case patch_operations::replace:
24846 {
24847 // the "path" location must exist - use at()
24848 result.at(ptr) = get_value("replace", "value", false);
24849 break;
24850 }
24851
24852 case patch_operations::move:
24853 {
24854 const auto from_path = get_value("move", "from", true).template get<std::string>();
24855 json_pointer from_ptr(from_path);
24856
24857 // the "from" location must exist - use at()
24858 basic_json v = result.at(from_ptr);
24859
24860 // The move operation is functionally identical to a
24861 // "remove" operation on the "from" location, followed
24862 // immediately by an "add" operation at the target
24863 // location with the value that was just removed.
24864 operation_remove(from_ptr);
24865 operation_add(ptr, v);
24866 break;
24867 }
24868
24869 case patch_operations::copy:
24870 {
24871 const auto from_path = get_value("copy", "from", true).template get<std::string>();
24872 const json_pointer from_ptr(from_path);
24873
24874 // the "from" location must exist - use at()
24875 basic_json v = result.at(from_ptr);
24876
24877 // The copy is functionally identical to an "add"
24878 // operation at the target location using the value
24879 // specified in the "from" member.
24880 operation_add(ptr, v);
24881 break;
24882 }
24883
24884 case patch_operations::test:
24885 {
24886 bool success = false;
24887 JSON_TRY
24888 {
24889 // check if "value" matches the one at "path"
24890 // the "path" location must exist - use at()
24891 success = (result.at(ptr) == get_value("test", "value", false));
24892 }
24893 JSON_INTERNAL_CATCH (out_of_range&)
24894 {
24895 // ignore out of range errors: success remains false
24896 }
24897
24898 // throw an exception if test fails
24899 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!success))
24900 {
24901 JSON_THROW(other_error::create(501, "unsuccessful: " + val.dump()));
24902 }
24903
24904 break;
24905 }
24906
24907 default:
24908 {
24909 // op must be "add", "remove", "replace", "move", "copy", or
24910 // "test"
24911 JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(105, 0, "operation value '" + op + "' is invalid"));
24912 }
24913 }
24914 }
24915
24916 return result;
24917 }
24918
24952 JSON_HEDLEY_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT
24953 static basic_json diff(const basic_json& source, const basic_json& target,
24954 const std::string& path = "")
24955 {
24956 // the patch
24957 basic_json result(value_t::array);
24958
24959 // if the values are the same, return empty patch
24960 if (source == target)
24961 {
24962 return result;
24963 }
24964
24965 if (source.type() != target.type())
24966 {
24967 // different types: replace value
24968 result.push_back(
24969 {
24970 {"op", "replace"}, {"path", path}, {"value", target}
24971 });
24972 return result;
24973 }
24974
24975 switch (source.type())
24976 {
24977 case value_t::array:
24978 {
24979 // first pass: traverse common elements
24980 std::size_t i = 0;
24981 while (i < source.size() && i < target.size())
24982 {
24983 // recursive call to compare array values at index i
24984 auto temp_diff = diff(source[i], target[i], path + "/" + std::to_string(i));
24985 result.insert(result.end(), temp_diff.begin(), temp_diff.end());
24986 ++i;
24987 }
24988
24989 // i now reached the end of at least one array
24990 // in a second pass, traverse the remaining elements
24991
24992 // remove my remaining elements
24993 const auto end_index = static_cast<difference_type>(result.size());
24994 while (i < source.size())
24995 {
24996 // add operations in reverse order to avoid invalid
24997 // indices
24998 result.insert(result.begin() + end_index, object(
24999 {
25000 {"op", "remove"},
25001 {"path", path + "/" + std::to_string(i)}
25002 }));
25003 ++i;
25004 }
25005
25006 // add other remaining elements
25007 while (i < target.size())
25008 {
25009 result.push_back(
25010 {
25011 {"op", "add"},
25012 {"path", path + "/-"},
25013 {"value", target[i]}
25014 });
25015 ++i;
25016 }
25017
25018 break;
25019 }
25020
25021 case value_t::object:
25022 {
25023 // first pass: traverse this object's elements
25024 for (auto it = source.cbegin(); it != source.cend(); ++it)
25025 {
25026 // escape the key name to be used in a JSON patch
25027 const auto key = json_pointer::escape(it.key());
25028
25029 if (target.find(it.key()) != target.end())
25030 {
25031 // recursive call to compare object values at key it
25032 auto temp_diff = diff(it.value(), target[it.key()], path + "/" + key);
25033 result.insert(result.end(), temp_diff.begin(), temp_diff.end());
25034 }
25035 else
25036 {
25037 // found a key that is not in o -> remove it
25038 result.push_back(object(
25039 {
25040 {"op", "remove"}, {"path", path + "/" + key}
25041 }));
25042 }
25043 }
25044
25045 // second pass: traverse other object's elements
25046 for (auto it = target.cbegin(); it != target.cend(); ++it)
25047 {
25048 if (source.find(it.key()) == source.end())
25049 {
25050 // found a key that is not in this -> add it
25051 const auto key = json_pointer::escape(it.key());
25052 result.push_back(
25053 {
25054 {"op", "add"}, {"path", path + "/" + key},
25055 {"value", it.value()}
25056 });
25057 }
25058 }
25059
25060 break;
25061 }
25062
25063 default:
25064 {
25065 // both primitive type: replace value
25066 result.push_back(
25067 {
25068 {"op", "replace"}, {"path", path}, {"value", target}
25069 });
25070 break;
25071 }
25072 }
25073
25074 return result;
25075 }
25076
25078
25080 // JSON Merge Patch functions //
25082
25085
25128 void merge_patch(const basic_json& apply_patch)
25129 {
25130 if (apply_patch.is_object())
25131 {
25132 if (!is_object())
25133 {
25134 *this = object();
25135 }
25136 for (auto it = apply_patch.begin(); it != apply_patch.end(); ++it)
25137 {
25138 if (it.value().is_null())
25139 {
25140 erase(it.key());
25141 }
25142 else
25143 {
25144 operator[](it.key()).merge_patch(it.value());
25145 }
25146 }
25147 }
25148 else
25149 {
25150 *this = apply_patch;
25151 }
25152 }
25153
25155 };
25156
25166 NLOHMANN_BASIC_JSON_TPL_DECLARATION
25167 std::string to_string(const NLOHMANN_BASIC_JSON_TPL& j)
25168 {
25169 return j.dump();
25170 }
25171} // namespace nlohmann
